{"title_page": "2020 coronavirus pandemic in Italy", "text_new": "{{pp-protected|small=yes}}\n{{short description|Ongoing viral pandemic in Italy}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{EngvarB|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name            = 2020 coronavirus pandemic in Italy\n| map1            = COVID-19 outbreak Italy per capita cases map.svg\n| legend1         = Confirmed cases per million inhabitants by province\n| map2            = COVID-19 Outbreak Cases in Italy (Density).svg\n| legend2         = Number of confirmed cases by province<br>(as of 28 March): {{legend|#FCEED3|1\u20139 confirmed}}{{legend|#F2A88D|10\u201399 confirmed}}{{legend|#E36654|100\u2013499 confirmed}}{{legend|#E5354B|500\u2013999 confirmed}}{{legend|#87353F|1,000\u20139,999 confirmed}}<!--{{legend|#630606|\u226510,000 confirmed}}-->\n| disease         = [[COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain    = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location        = Italy\n| first_case      = [[Rome]]\n| arrival_date    = 31 January 2020<br/>({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month1=01|day1=31|year1=2020|month2=|day2=|year2=}})\n| first_outbreak  = [[Wuhan]], [[Hubei]], China\n| index_case      = ''unknown''\n| deaths          = 12,428<ref name=\"Min_Salute_Situazione\"/>\n| recovery_cases  = 15,729<ref name=\"Min_Salute_Situazione\"/>\n| severe_cases    = 4,023<ref name=\"Min_Salute_Situazione\"/>\n| active_cases    = 77,635<ref name=\"Min_Salute_Situazione\"/>\n| confirmed_cases = 105,792<ref name=\"Min_Salute_Situazione\"/>\n| suspected_cases = \n| total_ili       = \n| website         = {{URL|http://www.salute.gov.it/nuovocoronavirus}}\n}}\n\nAn ongoing [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|worldwide pandemic]] of [[coronavirus disease 2019]] ({{nowrap|COVID-19}}), a novel infectious disease caused by [[severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus&nbsp;2]] ({{nowrap|SARS-CoV-2}}), was first confirmed to have spread to [[Italy]] on 31 January 2020, when two Chinese tourists in [[Rome]] tested positive for the virus.<ref name=\"Corriere_20Jan\">{{cite web |title=Coronavirus: Primi due casi in Italia|url=https://www.corriere.it/cronache/20_gennaio_30/coronavirus-italia-corona-9d6dc436-4343-11ea-bdc8-faf1f56f19b7.shtml |website=Corriere della sera |accessdate=31 January 2020 |date=31 January 2020|language=it}}</ref> One week later an Italian man repatriated back to Italy from the city of [[Wuhan]], China, was hospitalised and confirmed as the third case in Italy.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-italy-idUSKBN20F0UI|title=First Italian dies of coronavirus as outbreak flares in north|date=2020-02-21|work=Reuters|access-date=2020-03-06|language=en}}</ref> A cluster of cases was later detected, starting with 16 confirmed cases in [[Lombardy]] on 21 February,<ref name=\"ThomReut_IT_16cluster_21Feb\">{{cite news | last1= Anzolin | first1= Elisa | last2= Amante | first2= Angelo | title= Coronavirus outbreak grows in northern Italy, 16 cases reported in one day | date=21 February 2020 | agency=[[Thomson Reuters]] | url= https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-italy/coronavirus-outbreak-grows-in-northern-italy-16-cases-reported-in-one-day-idUSKBN20F0UI |accessdate=21 February 2020 |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20200221225322/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-italy/coronavirus-outbreak-grows-in-northern-italy-16-cases-reported-in-one-day-idUSKBN20F0UI |archivedate= 21 February 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> and 60 additional cases and the first deaths on 22 February.<ref name=\"CorrieredSera_76_recent_cases\" /> By the beginning of March, the virus had spread to all regions of Italy.<ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus. Colpite tutte le regioni. La Protezione civile: ecco i numeri aggiornati |url=https://www.avvenire.it/attualita/pagine/coronavirus-aggiornamento-5-marzo-2020 |accessdate=19 March 2020 |work=www.avvenire.it |date=5 March 2020 |language=it}}</ref>\n\nOn 31 January, the Italian government suspended all flights to and from China and declared a state of emergency. In February, eleven municipalities in [[northern Italy]] were identified as the centres of the two main Italian clusters and placed under quarantine. The majority of positive cases in other regions traced back to these two clusters.<ref name=\":8\">{{cite web|url=https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/22/news/coronavirus_in_italia_aggiornamento_ora_per_ora-249241616/|title=Coronavirus in Italia: aggiornamento ora per ora|date=2020-02-22|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref> On 8 March 2020, [[Prime Minister of Italy|Prime Minister]] [[Giuseppe Conte]] expanded the quarantine to all of Lombardy and 14 other northern provinces, and on the following day to all of Italy, [[2020 Italy coronavirus lockdown|placing more than 60 million people in quarantine]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Coronavirus: Northern Italy quarantines 16 million people |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-51787238 |website=BBC |accessdate=8 March 2020 |date=8 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"auto\">{{cite news |title=All of Italy to be placed on coronavirus lockdown |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-51810673 |accessdate=9 March 2020 |work=BBC News |date=9 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.sky.com/story/coronavirus-italy-sees-largest-daily-rise-in-deaths-and-confirmed-cases-11953192|title=Coronavirus: Italy deaths jump to 463, with 300 in just one region|website=Sky News|accessdate=10 March 2020}}</ref> On 11 March 2020, Conte prohibited nearly all commercial activity except for supermarkets and pharmacies.<ref name=\":12\">{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/europe/merkel-coronavirus-germany/2020/03/11/e276252a-6399-11ea-8a8e-5c5336b32760_story.html|title=Italy ramps up coronavirus lockdown, Merkel warns virus could infect two-thirds of Germany|last=Harlan|first=Chico|last2=Morris|first2=Loveday|website=Washington Post|language=en|access-date=2020-03-12}}</ref><ref name=\":13\">{{Cite news|last=Rome|first=Eric Sylvers in Milan and Giovanni Legorano in|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/italy-hardens-nationwide-quarantine-11583962093|title=Italy Hardens Nationwide Quarantine|date=2020-03-12|work=Wall Street Journal|access-date=2020-03-12|language=en-US|issn=0099-9660}}</ref> On 21 March, the Italian government closed all non-essential businesses and industries, with additional restrictions to movement of people.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Safi |first1=Michael |last2=Giuffrida |first2=Angela |last3=Farrer |first3=Martin |title=Coronavirus: Italy bans any movement inside country as toll nears 5,500 |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/22/italian-pm-warns-of-worst-crisis-since-ww2-as-coronavirus-deaths-leap-by-almost-800 |accessdate=22 March 2020 |work=The Guardian |date=22 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 6 March 2020, the Italian College of Anesthesia, Analgesia, Resuscitation and Intensive Care (SIAARTI) published [[medical ethics]] recommendations regarding [[triage]] protocols that might be employed.<ref>{{cite techreport|url=http://www.siaarti.it/SiteAssets/News/COVID19%20-%20documenti%20SIAARTI/SIAARTI%20-%20Covid19%20-%20Raccomandazioni%20di%20etica%20clinica.pdf|title=Raccomandazioni di etica clinica per l\u2019ammissione a trattamenti intensivi e per la loro sospensione, in condizioni eccezionali di squilibrio tra necessit\u00e0 e risorse disponibili|institution=Italian College of Anesthesia, Analgesia, Resuscitation and Intensive Care (SIAARTI)|language=it|date=6 March 2020|access-date=12 March 2020|url-status=live|format=PDF|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200312202813/http://www.siaarti.it/SiteAssets/News/COVID19%20-%20documenti%20SIAARTI/SIAARTI%20-%20Covid19%20-%20Raccomandazioni%20di%20etica%20clinica.pdf|archive-date=12 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/ideas/archive/2020/03/who-gets-hospital-bed/607807/|title=The Extraordinary Decisions Facing Italian Doctors|last=Mounk|first=Yascha|date=11 March 2020|work=[[The Atlantic]]|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200312233745/https://www.theatlantic.com/ideas/archive/2020/03/who-gets-hospital-bed/607807/|archive-date=12 March 2020|access-date=12 March 2020|quote=Now the Italian College of Anesthesia, Analgesia, Resuscitation and Intensive Care (SIAARTI) has published guidelines for the criteria that doctors and nurses should follow in these extraordinary circumstances. The document begins by likening the moral choices facing Italian doctors to the forms of wartime triage that are required in the field of \"catastrophe medicine.\"}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.politico.eu/article/coronavirus-italy-doctors-tough-calls-survival/|title=Italian doctors on coronavirus frontline face tough calls on whom to save|last=Privitera|first=Greta|date=11 March 2020|work=[[Politico]]|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200312125640/https://www.politico.eu/article/coronavirus-italy-doctors-tough-calls-survival/|archive-date=12 March 2020|access-date=12 March 2020|quote=\u2026the Italian Society of Anesthesia, Analgesia, Resuscitation and Intensive Care, who co-authored new guidelines on how to prioritize treatment of coronavirus cases in hospitals\u2026}}</ref> By 31 March, Italy had conducted about 507,000 tests for the virus.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.salute.gov.it/imgs/C_17_pagineAree_5351_26_file.pdf|title=AGGIORNAMENTO 21/03/2020 ORE 17.00|date=21 March 2020|url-status=live|access-date=19 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n{{As of|2020|03|31}}, Italy is one of the world's centres of active coronavirus cases with 77,635 active cases.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://gisanddata.maps.arcgis.com/apps/opsdashboard/index.html#/bda7594740fd40299423467b48e9ecf6|title=Coronavirus COVID-19 Global Cases by the Center for Systems Science and Engineering (CSSE) at Johns Hopkins |access-date=2020-03-25}}</ref> The total of confirmed cases is 105,792, with 12,428 deaths, and 15,729 recoveries.<ref name=\"Min_Salute_Situazione\">{{cite web|url=http://www.salute.gov.it/portale/nuovocoronavirus/dettaglioContenutiNuovoCoronavirus.jsp?lingua=italiano&id=5351&area=nuovoCoronavirus&menu=vuoto|title=Covid-19 \u2013 Situazione in Italia|website=www.salute.gov.it|publisher=Ministero della Salute|language=it|accessdate=13 March 2020}}</ref> On 19 March, Italy became the country with the highest number of confirmed deaths in the world.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/world/2020/03/19/coronavirus-italy-now-has-more-covid-19-deaths-than-china/2873835001/|title=Grim milestone: Italy's coronavirus deaths surpass China's|first=Eric J. Lyman and Kim|last=Hjelmgaard|website=USA TODAY}}</ref>\n\n==Background==\nOn 31 December 2019, the Health Commission of [[Wuhan]], [[Hubei]], [[China]], informed the [[World Health Organization|WHO]] about a cluster of acute pneumonia cases with unknown origin in its province. On 9 January 2020, the [[Chinese Center for Disease Control and Prevention]] (CCDC) reported the identification of a [[novel coronavirus]] (later identified as the [[SARS-CoV-2]]) as the cause.<ref>{{cite web |title=Covid-19 - Situazione nel mondo |url=http://www.salute.gov.it/portale/nuovocoronavirus/dettaglioContenutiNuovoCoronavirus.jsp?lingua=italiano&id=5338&area=nuovoCoronavirus&menu=vuoto |website=www.salute.gov.it |accessdate=4 March 2020 |language=IT}}</ref> In late January 2020, following the [[Mainland China during the 2019\u201320 coronavirus outbreak|developments of COVID-19 outbreak in mainland China]], on 3 February, Italy set up enhanced screening measures, including thermal cameras and medical staff at airports.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n==Timeline==\n{{Update section |date=March 2020}}\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/Italy medical cases chart}}\n\n===First confirmed cases===\nOn 31 January, the first two cases of COVID-19 were confirmed in [[Rome]]. A Chinese couple, originally from Wuhan, who had arrived in Italy on 23 January via [[Milan Malpensa Airport]], travelled from the airport to [[Verona]], then to Parma, arriving in Rome on 28 January. The next afternoon, they developed a cough, and by evening the man had a fever; the couple were taken to [[Lazzaro Spallanzani National Institute for Infectious Diseases]] where they tested positive for SARS-CoV-2 and were hospitalised.<ref name=\"prima\">{{cite web|url=https://www.corriere.it/cronache/20_gennaio_31/virus-primi-due-casi-italia-due-cinesi-marito-moglie-italia-dieci-giorni-e365df1c-43b3-11ea-bdc8-faf1f56f19b7.shtml|title=Prima a Milano, poi l'hotel a Roma: le tappe dei 7 giorni di viaggio della coppia contagiata|last=Frignani|first=Rinaldo|date=2020-01-31|website=Corriere della Sera|language=it|access-date=2020-03-07}}</ref><ref name=\"Corriere_20Jan\"/> On 31 January, the Italian government suspended all flights to and from China and declared a state of emergency with the duration of six months. Prime Minister [[Giuseppe Conte]] said Italy was the first EU country to take this kind of precautionary measure.<ref name=\"thelocal-flight\">{{cite web|url=https://www.thelocal.it/20200131/italy-suspends-all-china-flights-after-coronavirus-cases-confirmed-in-rome/|title=Italy suspends all China flights as coronavirus cases confirmed in Rome|date=2020-01-31|website=THELOCAL|access-date=2020-02-26}}</ref> The government also introduced thermal scanners and temperature checks on international passengers arriving at Italian airports.<ref name=\":0\">{{cite web|url=https://www.corriere.it/cronache/20_febbraio_04/coronavirus-controlli-gli-scanner-termici-aeroporti-italiani-c10b73d2-4796-11ea-bec1-6ac729c309c6.shtml|title=Coronavirus, controlli con gli scanner termici negli aeroporti italiani|last=Berberi|first=Leonard|date=2020-04-02|website=Corriere della Sera|language=it|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref>\n\nOn 6 February, an Italian repatriated from Wuhan tested positive for COVID-19, bringing the total number of cases in Italy to three.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.cnn.com/asia/live-news/coronavirus-outbreak-02-06-20-intl-hnk/index.html|title=February 6 coronavirus news|first1=Jessie |last1=Yeung |first2=Adam |last2=Renton |first3=Steve|last3=George|date=6 February 2020|publisher=CNN}}</ref>\n\nOn 22 February, the repatriated Italian recovered and was discharged from the hospital.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.open.online/2020/02/22/coronavirus-bollettino-dello-spallanzani-guarito-il-ricercatore-italiano-verra-dimesso-oggi/|title=Coronavirus, bollettino dello Spallanzani: guarito il ricercatore italiano, verr\u00e0 dimesso oggi. Niccol\u00f2 \"sta benissimo\" \u2013 Il video|date=22 February 2020|website=Open|language=it-IT|access-date=23 February 2020}}</ref> On 22 and 26 February, the two previously infected Chinese tourists tested negative for COVID-19 at Lazzaro Spallanzani National Institute in Rome.<ref name=\":2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.ilmessaggero.it/mondo/coronavirus_diretta_morti_contagi_oggi_ultime_notizie_26_febbraio_2020-5075865.html|title=Coronavirus, diretta. Contagi a quota 424, primo caso in Puglia, 12 morti. Lombardia, Fontana \u00e8 negativo, ma resta in isolamento per 14 giorni|website=www.ilmessaggero.it}}</ref>\n\n===Lombardy cluster===\nThe [[Lombardy]] outbreak came to light when a 38-year-old Italian tested positive in [[Codogno]], a [[comune]] in the [[province of Lodi]]. On 14 February, he felt unwell and went to a doctor in [[Castiglione d'Adda]]. He was prescribed treatments for influenza.<ref name=\"Repubblica_Codogno_doctors\" /> On 16 February, as the man's condition worsened, he went to Codogno Hospital, reporting respiratory problems.<ref name=\"Repubblica_Codogno_doctors\">{{Cite news |title=Codogno, i medici dell'ospedale in trincea: \"Quelle accuse del premier fanno pi\u00f9 male della malattia\"|language=Italian |publisher=la Repubblica |date=2020-02-26 |url= https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/26/news/codogno_i_medici_dell_ospedale_in_trincea_quelle_accuse_del_premier_fanno_piu_male_della_malattia_-249593374/ |accessdate=2020-02-26}}</ref> Initially there was no suspicion of COVID-19, so no additional precautionary measures were taken, and the virus was able to infect other patients and health workers.<ref name=\"urlMailand:NZZ\">{{cite web |url=https://www.nzz.ch/international/mailand-coronavirus-epidemie-begann-in-spital-ld.1542330 |title=Mailand: Coronavirus-Epidemie begann in Spital |accessdate=24 February 2020 |website= www.nzz.ch (Neue Zurcher Zeitung)}}</ref> On 19 February, the wife of the patient revealed he had met an Italian friend who had returned from China on 21 January, who subsequently tested negative.<ref name=\"Repubblica_Codogno_doctors\" /> Later, the patient, his pregnant wife and a friend tested positive.<ref name=\"Repubblica_Codogno_doctors\" /> On 20 February, three more cases were confirmed after the patients reported symptoms of [[pneumonia]].<ref name=\":1\">{{cite news |title=Coronavirus, primi tre contagi in Italia: 38enne, sua moglie e un amico in terapia intensiva. La donna insegna in un liceo |language=Italian |publisher=La Repubblica |url= https://milano.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/21/news/coronavirus_a_milano_contaggiato_38enne_e_un_italiano_ricoverato_a_codogno-249121707/?ref=RHPPTP-BH-I249146878-C12-P1-S1.12-T1 |accessdate=21 February 2020 |date=21 February 2020}}</ref> Thereafter, extensive screenings and checks were performed on everyone that had possibly been in contact with or near the infected subjects.<ref name=\"Messaggero_22Feb\">{{cite news |url= https://www.ilmessaggero.it/italia/coronavirus_diretta_lombardia_codogno_italiano_ultime_notizie-5064423.html |title=Coronavirus, diretta: morto uomo di 78 anni a Padova, \u00e8 la prima vittima italiana |website=Il Messaggero |date=22 February 2020 |accessdate=22 February 2020 |language=Italian}}</ref> It has been subsequently reported that the origin of these cases has a possible connection to the first European local transmission that occurred in [[Munich]], Germany, on 19 January 2020, consistent with phylogenetic analysis of viral genome.<ref name=\"Repubblica_Munich_Codogno\">{{cite news |last1=Luna |first1=Riccardo |title=Coronavirus: il paziente tedesco |url=https://rep.repubblica.it/pwa/generale/2020/03/05/news/coronavirus-250377117/ |accessdate=11 March 2020 |work=La Repubblica |date=5 March 2020 |language=it}}</ref><ref name=\"nextstrain\">{{cite web|url=https://nextstrain.org/ncov?dmax=2020-03-08&dmin=2019-12-15&fbclid=IwAR3UreH6NMoS8IjQqWOJpYdTX_Ygc5bW4gcBBf2gWe_QTDwxIL0oLMuwSgY|title=Genomic epidemiology of novel coronavirus (hCoV-19)| website=nextstrain.org|accessdate=10 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=pmid32003551>{{cite journal |last1=Rothe |first1=Camilla |last2=Schunk |first2=Mirjam |last3=Sothmann |first3=Peter |last4=Bretzel |first4=Gisela |last5=Froeschl |first5=Guenter |last6=Wallrauch |first6=Claudia |last7=Zimmer |first7=Thorbj\u00f6rn |last8=Thiel |first8=Verena |last9=Janke |first9=Christian |last10=Guggemos |first10=Wolfgang |last11=Seilmaier |first11=Michael |last12=Drosten |first12=Christian  |author-link12=Christian Drosten |last13=Vollmar |first13=Patrick |last14=Zwirglmaier |first14=Katrin |last15=Zange |first15=Sabine |last16=W\u00f6lfel |first16=Roman |last17=Hoelscher |first17=Michael |title=Transmission of 2019-nCoV Infection from an Asymptomatic Contact in Germany |journal=New England Journal of Medicine |date=5 March 2020 |volume=382 |issue=10 |pages=970\u2013971 |doi=10.1056/NEJMc2001468 |pmid=32003551 }}</ref> The 38-year-old man was asymptomatic for weeks, reportedly led an active social life and potentially interacted with dozens of people before spreading the virus at Codogno Hospital.<ref name=\"Repubblica_Codogno_doctors\" /><ref name=\"urlMailand:NZZ\" /> Afterward, he was transferred to [[Policlinico San Matteo]] in [[Pavia]],<ref>{{Cite news |url= https://www.liberoquotidiano.it/news/italia/13566825/coronavirus-paziente-uno-codogno-trasferimento-pavia.html |title=Coronavirus, il 38enne paziente uno di Codogno trasferito nella notte a Pavia |website=liberoquotidiano.it |accessdate=2020-02-25}}</ref> and his wife to [[Ospedale Luigi Sacco|Sacco Hospital]] in Milan.<ref>{{Cite news |url= https://edition.cnn.com/asia/live-news/coronavirus-outbreak-02-25-20-hnk-intl/h_485832164169510b66e7bb07479c75b0 |title=Italian authorities identify first known patient to have caught coronavirus in Lombardy |first1=Helen |last1=Regan |first2=Adam |last2=Renton |date=2020-02-25 |website=CNN |accessdate=2020-02-25}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url= https://milano.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/25/news/coronavirus_paziente_1_ancora_grave_ma_stazionario_la_moglie_incinta_sta_bene-249550115/ |title=Coronavirus, \"paziente 1\" ancora grave ma stazionario, la moglie incinta sta bene |language=Italian |date=2020-02-25 |publisher=la Repubblica |accessdate=2020-02-25}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Emergenza coronavirus (49496308758).jpg|thumb|upright=1.13|[[Protezione Civile|Civil Protection]] volunteers carrying out health checks at [[Guglielmo Marconi Airport]]]]\nOn 21 February 16 more cases were confirmed \u2013 14 in Lombardy, including the doctor who prescribed treatments to the 38-year-old Codogno man,<ref name=\"Repubblica_Codogno_doctors\" /> and two in [[Veneto]]. On 22 February, a 77-year-old woman from [[Casalpusterlengo]], who suffered from pneumonia and visited the same emergency room as the 38-year-old from Codogno, died in Lombardy.<ref>{{Cite news |url= https://www.tgcom24.mediaset.it/cronaca/lombardia/coronavirus-morta-una-donna-in-lombardia-seconda-vittima-italiana_15150431-202002a.shtml|title=Coronavirus, morta una donna in Lombardia: seconda vittima italiana |website=Tgcom24 |language=Italian |accessdate=22 February 2020}}</ref> Including the 78-year-old man who died in Veneto, the number of cases in Italy rose to 79.<ref name=\"CorrieredSera_76_recent_cases\" /><ref>{{Cite news |title=Coronavirus, in Veneto la prima vittima, Adriano Trevisan, 78 anni. Venti contagiati in Italia. Conte: \"Nuove misure\" |date=22 February 2020 |publisher=la Repubblica |url= https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/22/news/cina_coronavirus_italia_virus_wuhan_influenza_codogno_lombardia_veneto_adriano_trevisan-249215365/}}</ref> Of the 76 newly discovered cases, 54 were found in Lombardy, including one patient in [[San Raffaele Hospital]] in Milan<ref>{{Cite news |url= https://www.corriere.it/cronache/20_febbraio_22/coronavirus-italia-nuovi-contagi-lombardia-veneto-245e72d4-5540-11ea-8418-2150c9ca483e.shtml |title=Coronavirus, due casi a Milano |first=Simona |last=Ravizza |date=22 February 2020 |website=Corriere della Sera |language=Italian |accessdate=23 February 2020}}</ref> and eight patients in [[Policlinico San Matteo]] in [[Pavia]],<ref>{{Cite news |title=Coronavirus, a Pavia 8 pazienti ricoverati al San Matteo: anche una coppia di medici |language=Italian |website=Il Messaggero |date=2020-02-22 |url= https://www.ilmessaggero.it/italia/coronavirus_pavia_medici_contagiati_pieve_porto_morone_chignolo_po_cosa_sta_succedendo_22_febbraio_2020-5068178.html |accessdate=23 February 2020}}</ref> 17 in Veneto, two in [[Emilia-Romagna]], two in [[Lazio]] and one in [[Piedmont]].<ref>{{Cite news |first=Simona |last=Ravizza |title=Coronavirus, due casi a Milano |date=22 February 2020 |language=Italian |website=Corriere della Sera |url= https://www.corriere.it/cronache/20_febbraio_22/coronavirus-italia-nuovi-contagi-lombardia-veneto-245e72d4-5540-11ea-8418-2150c9ca483e.shtml |accessdate=22 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 23 February, a 68-year-old woman with cancer from [[Trescore Cremasco]] died in [[Crema, Lombardy|Crema]]. The number of cases in Italy rose to 152, including fourteen patients being treated at Policlinico San Matteo in Pavia.<ref>{{Cite news |url= https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/23/news/coronavirus_italia-249329434/ |title=Coronavirus, terza vittima in Italia: \u00e8 una donna ricoverata a Crema. 152 casi positivi |date=23 February 2020 |website=la Repubblica |language=Italian |access-date=23 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.globalist.it/news/2020/02/23/coronavirus-sale-a-14-il-numero-dei-casi-ricoverati-a-pavia-2053548.html |title=Coronavirus, sale a 14 il numero dei casi ricoverati a Pavia |publisher=globalist.it |language=Italian |accessdate=24 February 2020}}</ref> On 24 February, an 84-year-old man with pre-existing medical conditions from [[Villa di Serio]] died in [[Bergamo]] while hospitalised in the Papa Giovanni XXIII Hospital.<ref>{{Cite news |url= https://www.huffingtonpost.it/entry/quarto-morto-in-italia-per-il-coronavirus-aveva-84-anni_it_5e5381b7c5b6b82aa65555f4 |title=Quarto morto in Italia per il coronavirus, aveva 84 anni |date=24 February 2020 |website=L'HuffPost |language=Italian |accessdate=24 February 2020}}</ref> An 88-year-old man from [[Caselle Landi]], who resided in Codogno, died on the same day.<ref>{{Cite news |url= https://www.tgcom24.mediaset.it/cronaca/coronavirus-quarta-vittima-a-bergamo-in-lombardia-scoperti-150-casi_15242453-202002a.shtml |title=Coronavirus, in Italia si contano sei vittime e 230 contagi &#124; In Lombardia il numero maggiore dei casi |website=Tgcom24}}</ref><ref name=\"Repubblica_24Jan\" /> An 80-year-old man from [[Castiglione d\u2019Adda]] died at the Luigi Sacco Hospital in Milan. He was previously hospitalised in Lodi because of a heart attack, and then transferred to Milan when confirmed as positive.<ref name=\"Repubblica_24Jan\">{{Cite news |title=Coronavirus, sei morti in Italia, 229 contagi. Le vittime di oggi hanno tutte pi\u00f9 di 80 anni |language=Italian |website=la Repubblica |date=24 February 2020 |url= https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/24/news/coronavirus_149_i_casi_confermati_conte_i_contagi_possono_crescere_-249427098/ |accessdate=24 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.ansa.it/canale_saluteebenessere/notizie/sanita/2020/02/24/coronavirus-_60aae600-8535-44d9-86de-48c4b71478ef.html |title=Coronavirus: sesta vittima in Italia, morto 80enne a Milano. Smentita dalla Regione Lombardia la morte della donna a Brescia - Salute & Benessere |date=22 February 2020 |website=ANSA.it}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url= https://www.corriere.it/cronache/20_febbraio_24/coronavirus-chi-sono-vittime-italia-74e27360-56f6-11ea-b89d-a5ca249e9e1e.shtml |title=L'ex muratore , gli anziani ricoverati: chi sono le vittime |last=Del Frate |first=Claudio |date=24 February 2020 |website=Corriere della Sera |language=Italian |accessdate=24 February 2020}}</ref> A 62-year-old man with pre-existing medical conditions from Castiglione d'Adda died in [[Ospedale Sant'Anna|Sant'Anna Hospital]] in [[Como]].<ref>{{cite web |location=Italy |url= https://www.fanpage.it/attualita/corona-la-settima-vittima-e-un-62enne-di-castiglione-dadda-era-ricoverato-allospedale-di-como/ |title=Coronavirus, c'\u00e8 la settima vittima italiana: un 62enne di Castiglione d'Adda, era ricoverato a Como |website=Fanpage}}</ref> Lombardy governor [[Attilio Fontana]] announced that the number of cases in Lombardy had risen to 172, with a total of 229 confirmed in Italy.<ref name=\"Corriere_24Feb\">{{cite web|url=https://www.corriere.it/cronache/20_febbraio_24/coronavirus-italia-ultime-notizie-oggi-nord-23035e06-56ce-11ea-b89d-a5ca249e9e1e.shtml|title=Coronavirus in Italia, i contagi sono pi\u00f9 di 200: gli ultimi aggiornamenti|last=Online|first=Chiara Severgnini e Redazione|date=24 February 2020|website=Corriere della Sera|language=it|access-date=24 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |title=Coronavirus, quarto morto, \u00e8 un 84enne di Bergamo. |language=Italian |publisher=la Repubblica |date=24 February 2020 |url= https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/24/news/coronavirus_149_i_casi_confermati_conte_i_contagi_possono_crescere_-249427098/ |accessdate=24 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |title=Coronavirus, sette morti in Italia, 229 contagi |language=Italian |publisher=la Repubblica |date=2020-02-24 |url= https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/24/news/coronavirus_149_i_casi_confermati_conte_i_contagi_possono_crescere_-249427098/ |accessdate=2020-02-25}}</ref> On 25 February, an 84-year-old man from [[Nembro]], a 91-year-old man from [[San Fiorano]] and an 83-year-old woman from Codogno died from complications caused by the infections.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Del Frate |first=Claudio |title=L'ex muratore , gli anziani ricoverati: chi sono le vittime |language=Italian |publisher=Corriere della Sera |date=2020-02-24 |url= https://www.corriere.it/cronache/20_febbraio_24/coronavirus-chi-sono-vittime-italia-74e27360-56f6-11ea-b89d-a5ca249e9e1e.shtml |accessdate=2020-02-25}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |title=Coronavirus in Lombardia, salgono a 206 le persone contagiate |language=Italian |publisher=la Repubblica |date=2020-02-25 |url= https://milano.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/25/news/coronavirus_in_lombardia_salgono_a_206_le_persone_contagiate-249527654/ |accessdate=2020-02-25}}</ref><ref name=\"Repubblica_25Feb_count\">{{Cite news |url= https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/25/news/coronavirus_toscana-249520102/ |title=Coronavirus, 325 casi in Italia. Altri tre morti in Lombardia e uno in Veneto, le vittime diventano 11 |date=2020-02-25 |publisher=la Repubblica |language=Italian |access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref>\n\nThe number of cases in Emilia-Romagna rose to 23, spreading through the provinces of [[Province of Piacenza|Piacenza]], [[Province of Parma|Parma]], [[Province of Modena|Modena]] and [[Province of Rimini|Rimini]]. These were all linked to the Lombardy cluster.<ref>{{Cite news |url= https://parma.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/24/news/coronavirus_primi_due_casi_in_provincia_di_parma-249436934/ |title=Coronavirus, primi due casi in provincia di Parma|date=2020-02-24 |website=la Repubblica |language=Italian |accessdate=2020-02-26}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.ilrestodelcarlino.it/cronaca/coronavirus-oggi-1.5043974 |title=Coronavirus oggi Emilia Romagna: 19 contagiati, uno \u00e8 a Modena. Numero verde 800033033 |first=il Resto del |last=Carlino |date=24 February 2020 |publisher=il Resto del Carlino}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url= https://bologna.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/25/news/coronavirus_23_contagiati_in_emilia_romagna-249540542/ |title=Coronavirus: 23 contagiati in Emilia Romagna. Accertamenti su un riminese tornato dall'estero |date=2020-02-25 |website=la Repubblica |language=Italian |accessdate=2020-02-25}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |title=Coronavirus, salgono a quattro i casi positivi nel territorio di Parma |language=Italian |publisher=la Repubblica |date=2020-02-25 |url= https://parma.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/25/news/coronavirus_parma_altri_due_casi_a-249527788/ |accessdate=2020-02-26}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |title=Coronavirus, caso positivo a Bardi. Il sindaco: \"Non ci sono criticit\u00e0\" |language=Italian |publisher=la Repubblica |date=2020-02-26 |url= https://parma.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/26/news/coronavirus_caso_positivo_a_bardi_il_sindaco_non_esiste_al_momento_nessuna_criticita_-249613641/ |accessdate=2020-02-26}}</ref> A new case linked to the outbreak in Lombardy appeared in [[Palermo]], [[Sicily]], when a 60-year-old woman from Bergamo tested positive and was admitted to Cervello Hospital.<ref>{{Cite news |url= https://www.corriere.it/cronache/20_febbraio_25/coronavirus-turista-bergamasca-positiva-palermo-isolata-comitiva-d492dee2-57a7-11ea-a2d7-f1bec9902bd3.shtml |title=Coronavirus, turista bergamasca positiva a Palermo. Isolata la comitiva |first=Salvo |last=Toscano |date=25 February 2020 |publisher=Corriere della Sera}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url= https://palermo.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/25/news/palermo_caso_sospetto_a_palermo_turista_di_bergamo_ricoverata_al_cervello-249516268/ |title=Il coronavirus arriva a Palermo: turista di Bergamo positiva ai primi test |date=2020-02-25 |publisher=la Repubblica |language=Italian |access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref> A 49-year-old man who previously visited Codogno tested positive in [[Pescia]], Tuscany.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Coronavirus Toscana, niente panico: ecco cosa fare |language=Italian |website=la Repubblica |date=2020-02-25 |url= https://firenze.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/25/news/coronavirus_toscana_niente_panico_ecco_cosa_fare-249543095/ |accessdate=2020-02-25}}</ref> Officials in [[Liguria]] confirmed that a 72-year-old female tourist from Castiglione d'Adda tested positive in [[Alassio]] while she was staying in a hotel. The woman was treated at a hospital in [[Genoa]].<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.ansa.it/english/news/general_news/2020/02/25/coronavirus-first-case-in-liguria_263ab67d-5a38-4f81-80bc-4e4ca3b0cc95.html |title=Coronavirus: First case in Liguria |date=2020-02-25 |publisher=ANSA |location=Italy |accessdate=2020-02-25}}</ref> Later in the day, a second case in Liguria was confirmed, a 54-year-old man who had visited Codogno for work and tested positive in [[La Spezia]].<ref name=\"Repubblica_liveupdate\">{{cite web|url=https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/22/news/coronavirus_in_italia_aggiornamento_ora_per_ora-249241616/|title=Coronavirus in Italia: aggiornamento ora per ora|date=22 February 2020|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=24 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Le ultime notizie sul coronavirus in Italia |url=https://www.ilpost.it/2020/03/03/coronavirus-italia-ultime-notizie-aggiornamenti/ |accessdate=4 March 2020 |work=Il Post |date=3 March 2020 |language=it-IT}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |title=Coronavirus, ad Alassio il primo caso in Liguria, interdetti due alberghi, il secondo caso a Spezia |language=Italian |website=la Repubblica |date=2020-02-25 |url= https://genova.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/25/news/coronavirus_primo_caso_anche_in_liguria-249547990/ |accessdate=2020-02-25}}</ref> On 26 February, a 69-year-old man from Lodi with pre-existing medical conditions died in Emilia-Romagna.<ref name=\"TwelfthVictim\">{{Cite news |title=Coronavirus, dodicesima vittima in Italia. Primi contagi tra minori, 6 in Lombardia. Guarita la prima ammalata |language=Italian |publisher=la Repubblica |date=2020-02-26 |trans-title=Coronavirus, twelfth victim in Italy. First infections among minors, 6 in Lombardy. Heal the first sick woman |url= https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/26/news/coronavirus_contagi_in_nove_regioni_ricciardi_il_95_per_cento_dei_malati_guarisce_-249601102/ |accessdate=2020-02-26}}</ref> The mayor of [[Borgonovo Val Tidone]], Pietro Mazzocchi, tested positive for SARS-CoV-2 and underwent a voluntary isolation at home.<ref>{{Cite news |url= https://www.ctvnews.ca/health/on-the-front-lines-of-coronavirus-with-italy-s-first-sick-mayor-1.4829931 |title=On the front lines of coronavirus with Italy's first sick mayor |last=Feuillatre |first=Cecile |date=2020-02-27 |publisher=CTV News |location=Canaa |accessdate=2020-02-28}}</ref>\n\nAdditional cases involving six minors were identified in Lombardy. A 4-year-old girl from Castiglione d'Adda was admitted to Policlinico San Matteo in Pavia, and a 15-year-old was hospitalised in Seriate Hospital in Bergamo. Two 10-year-olds from [[Cremona]] and Lodi tested positive and were discharged. A 17-year-old from [[Valtellina]] who attended a school in Codogno, and a school friend from [[Sondrio]], also tested positive.<ref name=\":2\" /><ref name=\"TwelfthVictim\" /><ref name=\":3\">{{Cite news |url= https://www.tgcom24.mediaset.it/cronaca/coronavirus-325-i-casi-in-italia-il-contagio-si-allarga-a-9-regioni-11-le-vittime_15336711-202002a.shtml |title=Coronavirus, 12 le vittime in Italia: in Lombardia contagiati anche sei minori - Guarita la cinese ricoverata allo Spallanzani |website=Tgcom24 |language=Italian |accessdate=2020-02-26}}</ref> Officials in [[Apulia]] confirmed that a 33-year-old man from [[Taranto]], who returned from Codogno on 24 February, tested positive and was admitted to San Giuseppe Moscati Hospital.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Coronavirus, primo paziente positivo in Puglia. \u00c8 un uomo di 43 anni di Taranto tornato da Codogno |language=Italian |publisher=la Repubblica |date=2020-02-26 |url= https://bari.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/26/news/coronavirus_primo_paziente_positivo_in_puglia_e_un_tarantino_arrivato_da_codogno-249657611/ |accessdate=2020-02-26}}</ref> A close advisor to Lombardy governor [[Attilio Fontana]] tested positive for SARS-CoV-2. Although Fontana tested negative, he decided to put himself in preventive isolation as well.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Coronavirus, positiva collaboratrice di Fontana: il governatore in auto-isolamento. Contagiati anche minori |language=Italian |website=la Repubblica |date=2020-02-26 |url= https://milano.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/26/news/coronavirus_fontana_259_contagiati_anche_minor-249606130/ |accessdate=2020-02-26}}</ref> Officials in Campania confirmed two new cases. A 24-year-old woman from [[Caserta]], who had visited Milan, tested positive. A 25-year-old Ukrainian woman from Cremona, who previously visited Lombardy, tested positive at a hospital in [[Vallo della Lucania]]. Both were transferred to Hospital Domenico Cotugno in [[Naples]], where they underwent isolation.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Coronavirus, dalla Campania due casi positivi: sono due donne giunte dal Nord |language=Italian |publisher=la Repubblica |date=2020-02-26 |url= https://napoli.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/26/news/coronavirus_dalla_campania_un_tampone_positivo_allo_spallanzani_di_roma-249646115/ |accessdate=2020-02-26}}</ref>\n\nOn 26 February, a woman who had returned from Milan in the days before the emergency in Lombardy had started tested positive for the virus in Catania, Sicily.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Coronavirus, a Catania donna positiva. Borrelli: \"A Palermo guariti due dei tre pazienti\" |language=Italian |publisher=la Repubblica |date=2020-02-27 |url= https://palermo.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/27/news/coronavirus_a_catania_donna_positiva_tornata_da_milano-249700426/ |accessdate=2020-03-03}}</ref> On 27 February, two 88-year-olds and an 80-year-old died in Lombardy.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Coronavirus in Lombardia, 40 persone guarite. Altri anziani morti. I medici nella zona rossa: \"Noi lasciati soli\" |language=Italian |publisher=la Repubblica |date=2020-02-27 |url= https://milano.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/27/news/coronavirus_in_lombardia_vertice_tra_i_prefetti_a_fine_settimana_decisione_su_riapertura_scuole_e_stadi-249689409/ |accessdate=2020-02-27}}</ref> Officials in [[Abruzzo]] confirmed that a 50-year-old man from [[Brianza]], Lombardy tested positive and was admitted to the intensive-care unit at Giuseppe Mazzini Hospital at [[Teramo]]. He and his family were staying in his holiday home at [[Roseto degli Abruzzi]].<ref name=\"Repubblica_liveupdate\" /><ref>{{Cite news |title=Coronavirus: primo caso in Abruzzo, \u00e8 un turista Brianza |language=Italian |publisher=la Repubblica |date=2020-02-27 |url= https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/27/news/coronavirus_primo_caso_in_abruzzo_e_un_turista_brianza-249686482/ |accessdate=2020-02-27}}</ref> On 28 February, four people died, including an 85-year-old Lombardy resident in one of the quarantine zones at a hospital in Piacenza, a 77-year-old and two others over the age of 80.<ref name=\"Repubblica_liveupdate\" /> {{As of|2020|03|01|df=y}}, there were 984 confirmed cases and 73 recoveries in Lombardy.<ref name=\"Repubblica_liveupdate\" /><ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus, in Italia 1.694 casi: 41 i morti. I dati regione per regione al 1 marzo |url=https://www.corriere.it/salute/malattie_infettive/20_marzo_01/coronavirus-italia-positivi-sono-1577-34-morti-83-guariti-dati-1-marzo-215bf998-5be0-11ea-ae74-e93752023e91.shtml |accessdate=2 March 2020 |work=Corriere della Sera |date=3 January 2020 |language=it}}</ref> On 4 March, Emilia-Romagna's regional minister of health, Raffaele Donini, and minister for territories, Barbara Lori, were declared positive for COVID-19.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ilfattoquotidiano.it/2020/03/04/coronavirus-la-diretta-positivi-2-assessori-dellemilia-romagna-ce-donini-salute-pronto-nuovo-piano-durgenza-per-terapie-intensive/5724878/|title=Coronavirus, la diretta - Positivi 2 assessori dell'Emilia-Romagna: c'\u00e8 Donini (Salute). Pronto nuovo piano d'urgenza per terapie intensive|date=4 March 2020|website=Il Fatto Quotidiano}}</ref> Governor [[Stefano Bonaccini]] and the other members of the regional government tested negative.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://bologna.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/03/04/news/coronavirus_positivo_l_assessore_regionale_alla_sanita_donini-250207091/|title=Coronavirus, Emilia Romagna: positivo l'assessore regionale alla Sanit\u00e0 Donini|date=4 March 2020|website=la Repubblica}}</ref>\n\nOn 8 March, Prime Minister [[Giuseppe Conte]] extended the [[quarantine]] lockdown to cover all the region of Lombardy and 14 other [[Northern Italy|northern provinces]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-51787238|title=Coronavirus: Northern Italy quarantines 16 million people|website=BBC|date=8 March 2020}}</ref> On 10 March, Prime Minister Conte increased the quarantine lockdown to cover all of Italy, including travel restrictions and a ban on public gatherings.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-51810673|title=Coronavirus: Italy extends emergency measures nationwide|website=BBC|date=10 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 25 March, the [[Associated Press]] dubbed the [[UEFA Champions League]] match between Bergamo club [[Atalanta B.C.]] and Spanish club [[CF Valencia|Valencia]] at the [[San Siro]] in Milan on 19 February as \"Game Zero\". The match was the first time Atalanta has progressed to a [[2019\u201320 UEFA Champions League knockout phase|Champions League round of 16 match]], and had an attendance of over 40,000 people \u2014 about one third of Bergamo's population. By 24 March, almost 7,000 people in the [[province of Bergamo]] had tested positive for COVID-19, and more than 1,000 people had died from the virus \u2014 making Bergamo the most hard-hit province in all of Italy during the pandemic.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://apnews.com/ae59cfc0641fc63afd09182bb832ebe2|title=Game Zero: Spread of virus linked to Champions League match|publisher=Associated Press|date=25 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== Veneto cluster ===\n[[File:Emergenza Covid19 Ospedale di Padova.jpg|thumb|upright=1.13|[[Protezione Civile|Civil Protection]]'s first aid spot in [[Padua]]]]\nA secondary cluster of infections occurred in the region of Veneto, initially thought to be the result of a farmer being infected when visiting the primary source in Codogno.<ref name=\"urlMailand:NZZ\"/> The farmer was tested, and the following day, the test was confirmed negative.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.padova24ore.it/negativo-al-test-sul-corona-virus-contadino-albettone-joe-formaggio-occorre-senso-responsabilita/|title=Negativo al test sul corona virus il contadino di Albettone. Joe Formaggio: \"Occorre senso di responsabilit\u00e0\"|date=2020-02-24|website=Padova24Ore|language=it-IT|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref>\n\nOn 21 February 2020, two people tested positive in Veneto. The next day, one of them, a 78-year-old man, died at the Schiavonia Hospital in [[Monselice]], making him the first fatality in Italy. The man lived in the municipality of [[V\u00f2]], which was put under quarantine.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/22/news/adriano_trevisan_la_prima_vittima_di_coronavirus_in_italia-249260446/|title=Adriano Trevisan, la prima vittima di coronavirus in Italia|date=2020-02-22|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref>\n\nOn 25 February, a 76-year-old woman with pre-existing medical conditions died in [[Treviso]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tribunatreviso.gelocal.it/treviso/cronaca/2020/02/25/news/primo-caso-di-coronavirus-a-treviso-donna-di-76-anni-in-rianimazione-1.38516066|title=Primo caso di coronavirus a Treviso. Donna di 76 anni in rianimazione|date=2020-02-25|website=Tribuna di Treviso|language=it-IT|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref>\n\nOn 26 February, an additional case involving a minor was identified. An 8-year-old girl who lived in [[Codevigo]] tested positive.<ref name=\":2\" /><ref name=\":3\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ilgazzettino.it/nordest/venezia/coronavirus_veneto_casi_mappa_contagio_diretta_ultime_notizie-5074003.html|title=Coronavirus: i contagiati sono saliti a 87: nuovi pazienti a Limena, Treviso e Chioggia|website=www.ilgazzettino.it}}</ref>\n\nOn 28 February, Veneto governor Luca Zaia mentioned that after the first two cases, he ordered all 3,300 V\u00f2 residents to be tested. Of 6,800 swabs, 1.7% were confirmed positive. This epidemiological study would be used for outbreak investigation by the [[University of Padua]].<ref name=\":10\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ansa.it/sito/notizie/cronaca/2020/02/28/zaia-da-test-vo-studio-epidemiologico_2c3d88f3-6a4a-4e00-b255-9e1e2feb2768.html|title=Zaia, da test Vo' studio epidemiologico - Cronaca|date=2020-02-28|website=Agenzia ANSA|language=it|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref>\n\nAs of 28 February, there were 151 confirmed cases in Veneto, with 70 cases in the municipality of V\u00f2, including the two fatalities.<ref name=\"Repubblica_liveupdate\" /><ref name=\":10\" />\n\nBy 14 March, no new cases were detected in the municipality of [[V\u00f2]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus, a Vo' Euganeo nessun nuovo caso positivo |url=https://www.tgcom24.mediaset.it/cronaca/veneto/coronavirus-a-vo-euganeo-nessun-nuovo-caso-positivo_16143366-202002a.shtml |accessdate=18 March 2020 |work=Tgcom24 |date=14 March 2020 |language=IT}}</ref>\n\n=== Other regions ===\n{{Update section |date=March 2020}}\n[[File:Trasporto di pazienti in bio-contenimento - 7.jpg|thumb|right|upright=1.13|Paramedics carrying a patient under [[biocontainment]], in [[Cervia]]]]\n\nA number of cases have emerged in multiple regions that might be isolated and not associated with the Northern Italy clusters.\n\nOn 25 February, the first case in [[Florence]], [[Tuscany]] involved a 63-year-old entrepreneur with companies in Asia who had returned from the [[Philippines]] and [[Singapore]] on 6 January. He tested positive and was admitted to Santa Maria Annunziata Hospital.<ref name=\":2\" /><ref name=\"Repubblica_25Feb_Tuscany\">{{cite web|url=https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/25/news/coronavirus_toscana-249520102/|title=Coronavirus, primi casi a Firenze e a Palermo. 270 casi in Italia. Salgono a 206 in Lombardia e 38 in Veneto|date=2020-02-25|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref>\n\nThe first case in [[Rimini]] involved a 71-year-old man from [[Cattolica]] who returned from Romania on 22 February. He tested positive and was admitted to Infermi Hospital.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://bologna.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/26/news/coronavirus_il_71enne_riminese_risultato_positivo_e_rientrato_dalla_romania-249606750/|title=Coronavirus, il paziente 1 in Romagna \u00e8 un cuoco riminese. Chiuso il ristorante|date=2020-02-26|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=2020-02-26}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.chiamamicitta.it/coronavirus-a-rimini-venturi-caso-spinoso-paziente-ha-avuto-molti-contatti/|title=Coronavirus, a Rimini caso anomalo. Venturi: \"Paziente ha viaggiato molto\"|date=2020-02-25|website=Chiamamicitta|language=it-IT|access-date=2020-02-26}}</ref> A 51-year-old man from [[Piandimeleto]] who went to Romania with the man also tested positive and underwent self-quarantine at home.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.digi24.ro/stiri/actualitate/un-italian-care-l-a-insotit-in-romania-pe-barbatul-de-71-de-ani-infectat-are-si-el-coronavirus-1266637|title=Primul italian venit \u00een Rom\u00e2nia ar fi infectat cu coronavirus trei persoane \u00een Italia|website=www.digi24.ro|language=ro|access-date=2020-02-26}}</ref> On 26 February, one of people with whom he had interacted in [[Romania]] tested positive.<ref name=\":5\">{{cite web|url=https://www.digi24.ro/stiri/actualitate/primul-caz-de-coronavirus-in-romania-1266806|title=Primul caz de coronavirus \u00een Rom\u00e2nia. Suspiciuni despre un al doilea caz \u00een Gorj|trans-title=First coronavirus case in Romania. Suspicions about a second case in Gorj|language=ro|website=Digi24|access-date=26 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 26 February, the [[Norwegian Institute of Public Health]] confirmed that a 26-year-old Norwegian man living in Florence tested positive and was admitted to Santa Maria Annunziata Hospital. He had stayed in [[Norway]] for 14 days and returned to Florence five days before.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lanazione.it/firenze/cronaca/coronavirus-toscana-1.5046897|title=Coronavirus in Toscana: quattro positivi, altri due casi di contagio a Firenze / DIRETTA|last=Nazione|first=La|date=26 February 2020|website=La Nazione|language=Italian|access-date=2020-02-26}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thelocal.no/20200226/norwegian-student-tests-positive-for-coronavirus-in-italy|title=Norwegian student tests positive for coronavirus in Italy|website=www.thelocal.no|access-date=2020-02-26}}</ref>\n\nThe passenger ferry ''GNV Rhapsody'' was placed under isolation in the port of Genoa with 58 crew members on board after a passenger tested positive for the virus after having sailed to [[Tunisia]] on the ship.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.portnews.it/en/coronavirus-gnv-rhapsody-in-isolation/|title=Coronavirus, GNV Rhapsody in isolation|date=2020-03-04|website=PortNews|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-10}}</ref>\n\nOn 7 March, [[President of Lazio]] and leader of the [[Democratic Party (Italy)|Democratic Party]], [[Nicola Zingaretti]], tested positive for COVID-19.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ilmessaggero.it/roma/news/coronavirus_zingaretti_positivo_nicola_lazio_isolamento_famiglia-5096996.html|title=Coronavirus, Zingaretti positivo: sto bene, sono in isolamento. Controlli sullo staff. La solidariet\u00e0 della politica|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref> Ten days before, he was in Milan attending public events.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://milano.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/27/foto/coronavirus_zingaretti_pd_milano-249756747/1/#1|title=\"Milano non si ferma per il coronavirus\": spritz e tramezzini con il segretario Pd Zingaretti|date=27 February 2020|accessdate=22 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.msn.com/en-us/news/world/italy-pandemic-s-new-epicenter-has-lessons-for-the-world/ar-BB11vMrO?ocid=msedgdhp|title=Italy, Pandemic's New Epicenter, Has Lessons for the World|accessdate=22 March 2020}}</ref> The following day, [[List of presidents of Piedmont|President of Piedmont]] [[Alberto Cirio]] also tested positive.<ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus, anche il governatore del Piemonte positivo - La Stampa |url=https://www.lastampa.it/cronaca/2020/03/08/news/anche-il-governatore-del-piemonte-alberto-cirio-positivo-al-coronavirus-1.38566278 |accessdate=8 March 2020 |work=[[La Stampa]] |date=8 March 2020 |language=it-IT}}</ref>\n\nA US Navy sailor stationed in [[Naples]] tested positive on 6 March. Health officials in the US military began \"a thorough contact investigation\" to determine if any other personnel may have been exposed to the virus.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.cnn.com/2020/03/07/politics/us-navy-sailor-coronavirus-europe/index.html|title=US Navy sailor in Italy tests positive for coronavirus|website=CNN|accessdate=8 March 2020|date=7 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 11 March, it was announced that [[Juventus F.C.|Juventus]] and [[Italy national football team|national team]] footballer [[Daniele Rugani]] had tested positive for COVID-19.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/51844945|title=Coronavirus: Juventus centre-back Daniele Rugani tests positive for virus|publisher=British Broadcasting Corporation|accessdate=11 March 2020|date=11 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nGIMBE (Italy's Group for Evidence-based Medicine), in a report from 18 March, analysed data from the [[Istituto Superiore di Sanit\u00e0]] and found that healthcare workers represented over 8% of all detected coronavirus cases.<ref name=\"aj-oddone-rising-number\">{{cite web |last1=Oddone |first1=Elisa |title=Rising number of medical staff infected with coronavirus in Italy |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/03/rising-number-medical-staff-infected-coronavirus-italy-200318183939314.html |publisher=[[Al Jazeera]] |accessdate=19 March 2020 |date=18 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 26 March 2020, [[Italica Grondona]] became the world's oldest person to recover successfully from the [[coronavirus]] at the age of 102.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://themalaysianreserve.com/2020/03/30/covid-19-102-year-old-italian-woman-survives-the-virus/|title=COVID-19: 102-year-old Italian woman survives the virus|date=2020-03-30|website=The Malaysian Reserve|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nypost.com/2020/03/29/102-year-old-woman-from-italy-recovers-from-coronavirus/|title=102-year-old woman from Italy recovers from coronavirus|last=Salo|first=Jackie|date=2020-03-29|website=New York Post|language=en|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref> She was successfully recovered from the coronavirus after being tested positive with mild symptoms and was hospitalized in [[Genoa]] on 9 March for 20 days.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://abc7news.com/6063077/|title=102-year-old woman recovers from COVID-19 after 20-day hospitalization in Italy|date=2020-03-30|website=ABC7 San Francisco|language=en|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref>\n\nOn 22 March, it was announced that Juventus forward [[Paulo Dybala]] and former [[Italy national football team|Italy national team]] captain [[Paolo Maldini]] had tested positive for COVID-19.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/51991426|title=Coronavirus: Paulo Dybala and Paolo Maldini test positive|publisher=British Broadcasting Corporation|accessdate=22 March 2020|date=22 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Management==\nOn 31 January 2020, the [[Council of Ministers of Italy|Italian Council of Ministers]] appointed [[Angelo Borrelli]], head of the [[Protezione Civile|Civil Protection]], as Special Commissioner for the COVID-19 emergency.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tg24.sky.it/politica/approfondimenti/angelo-borrelli-chi-e.html|title=Chi \u00e8 Angelo Borrelli, capo della protezione civile nominato commissario per l'emergenza coronavirus &#124; Sky TG24|website=tg24.sky.it}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fanpage.it/politica/coronavirus-angelo-borrelli-nominato-commissario-straordinario-ecco-chi-e/|title=Coronavirus, Angelo Borrelli commissario straordinario: potr\u00e0 anche requisire gli hotel|website=Fanpage}}</ref>\n\n[[File:2020 coronavirus task force.jpg|thumb|upright=1.13|[[Conte II Cabinet|Italian government]] task force to face the COVID-19 outbreak in the [[Protezione Civile|Civil Protection]] situation room on 23 February. Prime Minister [[Giuseppe Conte]] and Health Minister [[Roberto Speranza]] are in the foreground, from behind.]]\n\n===First measures===\nOn 22 February, [[Conte II Cabinet|the government]] announced a new decree imposing the quarantine of more than 50,000 people from 11 different municipalities in [[Northern Italy]]. The quarantine zones are called the Red Zones and the areas in Lombardy and Veneto outside of them are called the Yellow Zones.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://milano.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/21/news/coronavirus_codogno_castiglione_d_adda_contagiati_misure_sicurezza-249154447/|title=Coronavirus, in dieci comuni lombardi: 50 mila persone costrette a restare in casa. Quarantena all'ospedale milanese di Baggio|date=21 February 2020|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=23 February 2020}}</ref> Penalties for violations range from a \u20ac206 fine to three months of imprisonment.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/coronavirus-chi-viola-quarantena-rischia-l-arresto-fino-tre-mesi-ACrcnLLB|title=Coronavirus, come funziona la quarantena e cosa rischia chi la viola (l'arresto)|website=Il Sole 24 ORE}}</ref> The [[Italian army|Italian military]] and law enforcement agencies were instructed to secure and implement the lockdown.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-51602007|title=Venice Carnival closes amid coronavirus outbreak|date=23 February 2020|publisher=BBC}}</ref>\n\nSchools were closed in ten municipalities in Lombardy, one in Veneto and one in Emilia Romagna. All public events were cancelled and some commercial activities{{which|date=February 2020}} were halted or were allowed to resume only until 6&nbsp;p.m.<ref name=\"Facebook_Pavia\">{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/comunePV/posts/2439843176121889|title=Comune di Pavia|website=facebook.com|access-date=23 February 2020}}{{Primary source inline|date=February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.corriere.it/cronache/20_febbraio_21/scuole-chiuse-il-coronavirus-lombardia-lodi-piacenza-codogno-a190ccee-54bd-11ea-9196-da7d305401b7.shtml|title=Quali sono i Comuni che hanno chiuso le scuole per il Coronavirus|last=online|first=Redazione|date=21 February 2020|website=Corriere della Sera|language=it|access-date=23 February 2020}}</ref> All religious services were cancelled.<ref name=\"Repubblica_23Feb_Carnival\">{{cite web|url=https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/23/news/coronavirus_scuole_chiuse_e_niente_carnevale_tutti_i_provvedimenti-249355737/|title=Coronavirus, scuole chiuse e niente Carnevale di Venezia. I provvedimenti Regione per Regione|date=2020-02-23|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref> Regional train services to the most affected areas were suspended, with trains skipping stops at Codogno, [[Maleo, Lombardy|Maleo]] and Casalpusterlengo stations.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.corriere.it/cronache/20_febbraio_22/coronavirus-treni-fermi-ore-lecce-milano-nessuno-stop-comuni-rischio-lodigiano-431e997c-553d-11ea-8418-2150c9ca483e.shtml|title=Coronavirus, treni fermi per ore a Lecce e Milano. I convogli non-fermano nei Comuni a rischio del Lodigiano|last=online|first=Redazione|date=22 February 2020|website=Corriere della Sera|language=it|access-date=23 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://milano.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/22/news/coronavirus_il_comune_di_milano_sospende_dal_lavoro_i_dipendenti_che_abitano_delle_zone_coinvolte-249252812/|title=Coronavirus, per una settimana didattica sospesa nelle universit\u00e0 lombarde. Comune di Milano e grandi aziende: i lavoratori a rischio restano a casa|date=22 February 2020|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=23 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nPeople with symptoms were advised to call the [[112 (emergency telephone number)|112]] emergency number, instead of going directly to hospitals, in an effort to limit the disease's spread.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sanmatteo.org/site/home/area-comunicazione/in-primo-piano.html|title=Coronavirus, aggiornamenti ed avvisi \u2013 Policlinico San Matteo Pavia Fondazione IRCCS|website=sanmatteo.org|language=it|access-date=23 February 2020}}</ref> The [[Ministry of Health (Italy)|Ministry of Health]] provided a website and a direct line (1500) from which people could obtain the latest updates and information, as well as report suspected cases.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.salute.gov.it/nuovocoronavirus|title=Nuovo coronavirus|last=Salute|first=Ministero della|website=salute.gov.it|language=IT|access-date=23 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nEducational trips to destinations in Italy and abroad were suspended. Universities in Lombardy, Veneto, [[Trentino Alto-Adige]], [[Piedmont]] and [[Emilia-Romagna]] suspended all activities from 23 February until 1 March.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.unipv.it/?p=46130|title=news.unipv \u2013 Coronavirus: Sospensione delle attivit\u00e0 didattiche dal 24/2 all'1/03|website=news.unipv|language=it-IT|access-date=23 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.unimi.it/it/coronavirus-misure-urgenti-la-comunita-universitaria|title=Coronavirus: misure urgenti per la comunit\u00e0 universitaria {{!}} Universit\u00e0 degli Studi di Milano Statale|website=unimi.it|access-date=23 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.unibg.it/node/9238|title=Sospensione precauzionale delle attivit\u00e0 didattiche |publisher=Universit\u00e0 degli studi di Bergamo |access-date=23 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.unive.it/pag/14024/?tx_news_pi1%5Bnews%5D=8621&cHash=aa65321bb25bdccbf08c0c18299d48de|title=Coronavirus: lezioni ed esami sospesi dal 24/02 al 29/02|website=Universit\u00e0 Ca' Foscari Venezia|language=it|access-date=23 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.unito.it/avvisi/coronavirus-aggiornamenti-sulla-gestione-della-situazione|title=Coronavirus: aggiornamenti sulla gestione della situazione|date=23 February 2020|website=Universit\u00e0 di Torino|language=it|access-date=23 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://magazine.unibo.it/archivio/2020/coronavirus-sospensione-attivita-didattica-e-misure-precauzionali-contro-la-diffusione-dell2019infezione|title=Coronavirus: Sospensione Attivit\u00e0 Didattica e misure precauzionali contro la diffusione dell'infezione|website=magazine.unibo.it|language=it|access-date=23 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 22 February 2020, [[Prime Minister of Italy|Prime Minister]] [[Giuseppe Conte]] suspended all sporting events in the regions of Lombardy and Veneto, which included three [[Serie A]] football matches in those regions, as well as one in [[Piedmont]], that were to be played the following day.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.football-italia.net/150398/serie-games-suspended-coronavirus|title=Serie A games suspended for Coronavirus|publisher=Football Italia|date=22 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.football-italia.net/150407/coronavirus-also-cancels-torino-parma|title=Coronavirus also cancels Torino-Parma|publisher=Football Italia|date=23 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2020/feb/23/three-serie-a-matches-coronavirus-outbreak-inter-milan|title=Four Serie A matches called off due to coronavirus outbreak|date=23 February 2020 |via=theguardian.com}}</ref> The following week, six Serie A matches were initially to be played behind closed doors, but all were later suspended,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/51637700|title=Coronavirus: Five Serie A matches to be played behind closed doors|publisher=bbc.com|date=February 25, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.football-italia.net/150647/official-juventus-inter-and-others-moved|title=Official: Juventus-Inter called off and others|publisher=Football Italia|date=29 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.football-italia.net/150715/official-sampdoria-verona|title=Official: Sampdoria-Verona is off|publisher=Football Italia|date=1 March 2020}}</ref> as were two [[Coppa Italia]] matches.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.football-italia.net/150787/official-juventus-milan-postponed|title=Official: Juventus-Milan postponed|publisher=Football Italia|date=3 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.football-italia.net/150804/official-napoli-inter-postponed|title=Official: Napoli-Inter postponed|publisher=Football Italia|date=4 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nAuthorities in Veneto cancelled the last two days of the [[Carnival of Venice]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-51602007|title=Venice Carnival closes amid coronavirus outbreak|date=23 February 2020|publisher=BBC News|access-date=23 February 2020}}</ref> Authorities in Piedmont cancelled the last three days of the Carnival of [[Ivrea]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.lastampa.it/cronaca/2020/02/24/news/ivrea-addio-guerra-delle-arance-e-la-quarta-volta-nella-storia-1.38507893|title=Ivrea, addio guerra delle arance. \u00c8 la quarta volta nella storia|date=23 February 2020|website=la Stampa|language=it|access-date=25 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n[[La Scala]], [[Duomo di Milano]] and [[Piccolo Teatro (Milan)|Piccolo Teatro]] in Milan, as well as [[Basilica Di San Marco]] in [[Venice]], were closed until further notice.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://milano.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/23/news/coronavirus_scala_milano_chiusure_nella_storia-249380233/|title=La Scala chiusa per il coronavirus: in pi\u00f9 di due secoli era accaduto soltanto sei volte|date=23 February 2020|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=24 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://milano.corriere.it/notizie/cronaca/20_febbraio_23/coronavirus-chiuse-scuole-palestre-locali-guida-coprifuoco-nord-00193c74-568a-11ea-b447-d9646dbdb12a.shtml|title=Cosa \u00e8 aperto, cosa no? Guida al \"coprifuoco\" da Coronavirus|last=Giannattasio|first=Maurizio|date=23 February 2020|website=Corriere della Sera|language=it|access-date=24 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.avvenire.it/chiesa/pagine/milano-l-arcivescovo-delpini-un-pensiero-di-benedizione|title=Coronavirus. Chiese aperte ma Messe sospese. La preghiera dell'arcivescovo Delpini|date=24 February 2020|website=Avvenire|language=it|access-date=24 February 2020}}</ref> A [[Giorgio Armani]] fashion show, which was scheduled on Sunday, the last day of [[Milan Fashion Week]] 2020, went ahead without any media or buyers present; it was instead streamed live online.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Luke Leitch|url=https://www.vogue.com/article/giorgio-armani-to-hold-empty-show-following-italian-coronavirus-outbreak|title=Giorgio Armani to Hold Empty Show Following Italian Coronavirus Outbreak|work=Vogue|access-date=23 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|agency=Associated Press|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2020/02/23/giorgio-armani-cancels-milan-fashion-week-show-virus-fears/|title=Giorgio Armani cancels Milan Fashion Week show over coronavirus fears|date=23 February 2020|work=The Telegraph|access-date=23 February 2020|issn=0307-1235}}</ref>\n\nIn addition to the emergency phone numbers 112 and 118, new dedicated numbers were added for the different regions \u2014 Lombardy 800894545, [[Campania]] 800909699, Veneto 800462340, Piedmont 800333444 and Emilia-Romagna 800033033.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fanpage.it/attualita/coronavirus-quali-sono-i-numeri-di-telefono-di-ministero-e-regione-da-chiamare-in-caso-di-sintomi/|title=Coronavirus, quali sono i numeri di telefono di Ministero e Regione da chiamare in caso di sintomi|website=Fanpage|language=it|access-date=23 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.regione.emilia-romagna.it/notizie/attualita/come-prevenire-il-rischio-di-contagio|title=Nuovo coronavirus, come prevenire il rischio di contagio|website=Regione Emilia-Romagna|language=it|access-date=24 February 2020}}</ref><ref name=autogenerated1>{{cite web|url=https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/23/news/coronavirus_scuole_chiuse_e_niente_carnevale_tutti_i_provvedimenti-249355737/|title=Coronavirus, scuole chiuse e niente Carnevale di Venezia. I provvedimenti Regione per Regione|date=2020-02-23|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=2020-02-24}}</ref><ref name=\"TollFree\">{{cite web|url=https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/24/news/coronavirus_i_numeri_verdi_istituiti_dalle_regioni-249494576/|title=Coronavirus, i numeri verdi istituiti dalle Regioni|date=2020-02-24|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=2020-02-25|trans-title=Coronavirus, the toll-free numbers established by the Regions}}</ref> The ''Ocean Viking'', a rescue ship operated by [[M\u00e9decins Sans Fronti\u00e8res|MSF]] and [[SOS M\u00e9diterran\u00e9e|SOS Mediteranee]] that was carrying almost 300 migrants, was quarantined for 14 days in [[Pozzallo]], [[Sicily]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.cnn.com/2020/02/23/europe/italy-novel-coronavirus-spike-intl/index.html|title=Coronavirus cases soar in Italy as authorities scramble to find patient zero|first1=Livia |last1=Borghese |first2=Tara|last2=John|publisher=CNN|access-date=23 February 2020}}</ref> [[Trenitalia]] and [[Nuovo Trasporto Viaggiatori|Italo]], the major providers for Italy's high-speed trains, ordered the installation of hand-sanitiser dispensers on all trains as well as the distribution of masks, disposable gloves and disinfectants to all onboard staff members.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.leggo.it/italia/cronache/coronavirus_protocollo_di_ferrovie_dello_stato_passeggeri_misure_iniziative-5070484.html|title=Coronavirus, i protocolli di Trenitalia e Italo per i passeggeri: misure e iniziative|website=leggo.it|language=it|access-date=23 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n[[File:EsseLunga Bergamo coronavirus 2020.jpg|thumb|left|upright=1.13|Empty shelves at the [[Esselunga]] supermarket in [[Bergamo]], 26 February 2020]]\n\nSupermarkets in Lombardy and Emilia-Romagna were emptied by customers as residents stockpiled food and supplies.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ilrestodelcarlino.it/bologna/cronaca/coronavirus-supermercati-vuoti-1.5045265|title=Coronavirus Bologna, razzia ai supermercati. Lunghe file e scaffali vuoti|last=MORONI|first=FRANCESCO|date=|website=il Resto del Carlino|language=it|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.corriere.it/cronache/20_febbraio_23/coronavirus-supermercati-assaltati-scaffali-vuoti-prove-coprifuoco-milano-zona-rossa-4f29bbd0-5681-11ea-b447-d9646dbdb12a.shtml|title=Supermercati assaltati, slittano anche le consegne a casa|last=Rosaspina|first=Elisabetta Andreis e Elisabetta|date=2020-02-23|website=Corriere della Sera|language=it|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.msn.com/en-us/video/news/supermarket-shelves-empty-as-coronavirus-fears-grip-milan/vi-BB10kd4x|title=Supermarket shelves stripped bare as coronavirus fears grip Milan|website=msn.com|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref> Streets, parks and train stations in multiple cities in Lombardy were left deserted.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.sky.com/story/ghost-towns-coronavirus-closes-parts-of-italy-11941940|title=Ghost towns: Coronavirus closes parts of Italy|website=Sky News|language=en|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tgcom24.mediaset.it/cronaca/lombardia/foto/coronavirus-milano-deserta-mezzi-pubblici-vuoti-e-mercati-abbandonati_15301555-2020.shtml|title=Coronavirus, Milano deserta: mezzi pubblici vuoti e mercati abbandonati - Foto Tgcom24|website=Tgcom24|language=IT|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref>\n\nOn 24 February 500 additional police officers were assigned to patrol the quarantined areas in [[Lodi, Lombardy|Lodi]] and Veneto.<ref name=\"Repubblica_24Feb\" /> Additional toll-free numbers were added for other regions \u2014 [[Valle D'Aosta]] 800122121, [[Trentino-Alto Adige/S\u00fcdtirol|Trentino Alto Adige]] 800751751, [[Friuli Venezia Giulia]] 800500300, [[Tuscany|Toscana]] 800556060, [[Umbria]] 800636363, [[Marche]] 800936677 and [[Lazio]] 800118800.<ref name=\"TollFree\" />\n\nThe governor of [[Basilicata]], [[Vito Bardi]], instituted a mandatory 14-day quarantine for people arriving from areas in Northern Italy affected by the outbreak.<ref name=\"Repubblica_24Feb\">{{cite web|url=https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/24/news/coronavirus_149_i_casi_confermati_conte_i_contagi_possono_crescere_-249427098/|title=Coronavirus, quarto morto, \u00e8 un 84enne di Bergamo. Sette regioni coinvolte per 30 milioni di italiani|date=24 February 2020|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=24 February 2020}}</ref> The Ministry of Health announced that it had engaged 31 laboratories in Italy to carry out the analysis of swabs from suspected COVID-19 cases.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tgcom24.mediaset.it/cronaca/coronavirus-il-ministero-della-salute-ha-aggiornato-la-circolare-con-le-nuove-disposizioni-analisi-in-31-laboratori_15196699-202002a.shtml|title=Coronavirus, il ministero della Salute ha aggiornato la circolare con le nuove disposizioni: analisi in 31 laboratori|website=Tgcom24|language=IT|access-date=24 February 2020}}</ref> Minister [[Roberto Speranza]] appointed Walter Ricciardi, a member of [[World Health Organization]]'s executive committee and former president of [[Istituto Superiore di Sanit\u00e0|Italian National Institute of Health]], as a special adviser for relations between Italy and international health organisations.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/24/news/coronavirus_speranza_nomina_walter_ricciardi_come_consigliere_e_alle_regioni_dice_no_a_scelte_unilaterali_-249447649/|title=Coronavirus, Speranza nomina Walter Ricciardi come consigliere e alle Regioni dice: \"No a scelte unilaterali\"|date=24 February 2020|website=la Repubblica}}</ref> Filming of ''[[Mission: Impossible 7]]'' starring [[Tom Cruise]] in [[Venice]] was halted.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thewrap.com/mission-impossible-vii-halts-production-in-italy-due-to-coronavirus-outbreak/|title='Mission: Impossible VII' Halts Production in Italy Due to Coronavirus Outbreak|date=2020-02-24|website=TheWrap|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref>\n\nMajor companies such as [[IBM]], [[Enel]], [[Luxottica]], [[PwC]] and [[Vodafone]] continued to allow employees to work from home. [[Generali Tower]] in Milan and [[Palazzo Madama]] in Rome installed thermal scanners to measure temperatures of visitors and employees.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.finanza.com/Finanza/Notizie_Italia/Italia/notizia/Coronavirus_Italia_Enel_ricorre_allo_smart_working_General-516928|title=Coronavirus Italia: Enel ricorre allo smart working. Generali installa scanner tecnici per misurazione febbre |website=finanza.com|access-date=24 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ilmessaggero.it/politica/coronavirus_senato_scanner_termici_scolaresche-5072334.html|title=Coronavirus, il Senato corre ai ripari: scanner termici agli ingressi e stop alle scolaresche|website=ilmessaggero.it|language=it|access-date=2020-02-24}}</ref> [[FAO Headquarters|FAO headquarters]] in Rome conducted temperature checks on visitors entering the building.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://roma.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/24/news/alla_fao_obbligatoria_la_misurazione_della_febbre_all_ingresso-249495069/|title=Alla Fao, obbligatoria la misurazione della febbre all'ingresso|date=2020-02-24|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref>\n\nMultiple regions in Italy such as [[Liguria]], Trentino Alto Adige, Friuli Venezia Giulia, [[Abruzzo]] and Marche decided to close all schools and universities for two days to a week. Court proceedings were postponed until further notice.<ref name=autogenerated1 />\n\n[[File:Is COVID-19 like a flu? ENG.png|upright=1.13|thumb|Starting from the 9th week of the year, ICU cases related to COVID-19 started to appear in the hospitals. Their spike showed a different behaviour than the cases of seasonal flu.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ilgiornale.it/news/cronache/coronavirus-non-affatto-linfluenza-ecco-grafico-che-dimostra-1837298.html|title=Il coronavirus non \u00e8 affatto come l'influenza: ecco il grafico che lo dimostra|publisher=[[Il Giornale]]|language=it|access-date=2020-03-17 |first=Federico |last=Giuliani}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ilmessaggero.it/salute/focus/coronavirus_influenza_differenze_morti_confronto_grafico_associazione_nazionale_biotecnologi_italia-5097008.html|title=Coronavirus-influenza, differenze enormi: picco dei morti oltre 4 volte superiore |language=it|access-date=2020-03-17|date=7 March 2020}}</ref>]]\n\nThe [[FTSE MIB|FTSE MIB Index]] fell by 6% and other stock market indices across Europe were also affected.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.marketwatch.com/story/italian-stocks-set-to-lead-sharp-decline-for-european-equities-as-coronavirus-spreads-2020-02-24|title=Italian stocks slump nearly 6% as European equities crumble on spreading coronavirus|last=Goldstein|first=Barbara Kollmeyer, Steve|website=MarketWatch|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref> Over 300,000 calls per day were logged on Lombardy's toll-free line as well as the emergency number 112.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://milano.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/25/news/coronavirus_milano_codogno_lombardia_contagi_morti_chiamate_numeri_emergenza-249521977/|title=L'assalto ai centralini per la paura coronavirus: 300mila chiamate in un giorno al numero di emergenza della Lombardia|date=2020-02-25|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref> Some of the residents inside the Red Zone managed to leave the quarantined areas daily, bypassing the checkpoints by going through back roads.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/25/news/la_zona_rossa_i_ribelli_di_codogno_violiamo_i_blocchi_per_sopravvivere_-249506911/|title=Codogno, i ribelli della zona rossa: \"Violiamo i blocchi per sopravvivere\"|date=2020-02-24|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dw.com/en/coronavirus-life-around-italys-quarantined-red-zone/a-52513830|title=Coronavirus: Life around Italy's quarantined 'red zone' {{!}} DW {{!}} 24.02.2020|last=Welle (www.dw.com)|first=Deutsche|website=DW.COM|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref>\n\nOn 25 February, [[Aviano Air Base]] closed all schools until 28 February.<ref name=\"Repubblica_liveupdate\" /> General [[Tod D. Wolters|Tod D. Walters]] issued a travel ban covering the areas of Italy affected by the outbreak for US service members and their families.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rollcall.com/2020/02/25/coronavirus-threatens-u-s-military-base-operations-in-europe-general-says/|title=Coronavirus threatens U.S. military base operations in Europe, general says|website=Roll Call|language=en|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref> Driver's license exams were suspended in Lombardy and Veneto.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ansa.it/lombardia/notizie/2020/02/25/coronavirus-sospesi-gli-esami-patente_82f235e4-e57a-42c7-ad4d-4e297fb259b8.html|title=Coronavirus: sospesi gli esami per la patente - Lombardia|date=2020-02-25|website=Agenzia ANSA|language=it|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref> The number of checkpoints in the Red Zones was increased from 15 to 35, and army personnel were sent to help staff the checkpoints.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ansa.it/sito/notizie/cronaca/2020/02/25/check-point-zona-rossaarriva-lesercito_651efc33-6cb3-48ff-ac84-aec43486a570.html|title=Check-point zona rossa,arriva l'Esercito - Cronaca|date=2020-02-25|website=Agenzia ANSA|language=it|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Italian Basketball Federation]] suspended all of its championship games, including [[Lega Basket Serie A]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.raisport.rai.it/articoli/2020/02/basket-A-A2-maschile-femminile-6592d551-065e-4245-931a-488e53809874.html|title=Basket: la Fip sospende la serie A, A2, B maschile, A1 e A2 donne - Rai Sport|website=RaiSport}}</ref>\n\nIstituto Tecnico Economico Enrico Tosi in [[Varese]], Istituto Comprensivo di [[Pianoro]] in Bologna and Liceo Attilio Bertolucci in Parma conducted lessons for students online while waiting for the schools to reopen.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bolognatoday.it/cronaca/coronavirus-scuole-chiuse-lezioni-onoline-bologna-pianoro.html|title=Ai tempi del Coronavirus scuole chiuse e lezioni online: \"Ecco come ci siamo organizzati per garantire il diritto allo studio\"|website=BolognaToday|language=it|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://milano.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/25/news/coronavirus_busto_arsizio_scuole_chiuse_lezioni_a_distanza-249536891/|title=Coronavirus, lezioni col tablet da casa per gli studenti del Tosi: \"La tecnologia ai tempi della quarantena\"|date=2020-02-25|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://parma.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/26/news/coronavirus_confinati_si_isolati_no_il_racconto_dei_liceali_di_parma_dalle_loro_camere-249616316/|title=Coronavirus, \"Confinati s\u00ec, isolati no\": il racconto dei liceali di Parma dalle loro camere|date=2020-02-26|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=2020-02-26}}</ref> The [[University of Palermo]] suspended all activities until 9 March.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://livesicilia.it/2020/02/25/universita-lezioni-sospese-e-lauree-a-porte-chiuse_1120700/|title=Universit\u00e0, lezioni sospese e lauree a porte chiuse|website=Live Sicilia|language=it|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref>\n\n[[Morgan Stanley]], [[Barclays]], [[Mediobanca]] and [[UniCredit]] requested their Milan staff to work from home.<ref name=\"Reuters_banks\" />\n\nMultiple fairs and exhibitions were rescheduled. Salone del Mobile, a furniture fair in Milan, was postponed to 16 to 21 June.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/coronavirus-salone-mobile-rinviato-giugno-AClPZvLB|title=Coronavirus, Salone del Mobile rinviato a giugno|website=Il Sole 24 ORE|language=it|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref> Bologna Children's Book Fair was rescheduled to 4 to 7 May.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bookfair.bolognafiere.it/|title=Bologna Children's Book Fair|last=Fiere|first=Bologna|website=Bologna Children bookfair|language=en|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref> Cosmoprof Worldwide Bologna, a cosmetic fair, was rescheduled to 11 to 15 June.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cosmoprof.com/en/official-updates/|title=Official updates|last=COSMOPROF|website=COSMOPROF|language=en|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref> Expocasa, a furniture fair in Turin, was rescheduled initially to 28 March to 5 April but later to future date to be announced later.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://torino.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/25/news/coronavirus_expocasa_rinviata_la_fiera_dell_arredamento_si_terra_dal_28_marzo_al_5_aprile-249565043/|title=Coronavirus, Expocasa rinviata, la fiera dell'arredamento si terr\u00e0 dal 28 marzo al 5 aprile|date=2020-02-25|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=AGGIORNAMENTI CORONA VIRUS - RINVIO MANIFESTAZIONE |url=https://www.expocasa.it/3796/aggiornamenti-corona-virus |website=EXPOCASA |accessdate=20 March 2020}}</ref> Roma Motodays was postponed to 17 to 19 April.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.repubblica.it/motori/sezioni/moto/2020/02/25/news/motodays_coronavirus_rinvio-249562967/|title=Effetto Coronavirus: rinviato a Roma il Motodays|date=2020-02-25|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref>\n\nItaly opened a probe into skyrocketing online prices for masks and sanitising gels. Police issued warnings that criminals were using false identities and posing as health inspectors to gain access to people's homes to steal money, jewellery and other valuables.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/china-health-italy-probe-idUSL5N2AP37X|title=Italy probes \"insane\" prices for coronavirus masks, sanitizers|date=2020-02-25|work=Reuters|access-date=2020-02-25|language=en}}</ref>\n\nOn 26 February, Director of the Italian National Institute of Health Franco Locatelli announced that swabbing would only be performed on symptomatic patients, as 95% of the swabs previously tested were negative.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tg24.sky.it/cronaca/2020/02/26/coronavirus-tamponi-solo-su-sintomatici.html|title=Coronavirus, Consiglio superiore sanit\u00e0: tamponi solo su sintomatici {{!}} Sky TG24|website=tg24.sky.it|access-date=2020-02-26}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Italian Minister of University and Research]], [[Gaetano Manfredi]], announced that online lessons would be delivered to students in areas affected by the outbreak starting on 2 March.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.miur.gov.it/web/guest/-/coronavirus-manfredi-universita-da-lunedi-lezioni-on-line-per-gli-studenti-delle-aree-colpite-primo-passo-verso-la-normalita-|title=Coronavirus, Manfredi, Universit\u00e0: \"Da luned\u00ec lezioni on line per gli studenti delle aree colpite, primo passo verso la normalit\u00e0\" - Coronavirus, Manfredi, Universit\u00e0: \"Da luned\u00ec lezioni on line per gli studenti delle aree colpite, primo passo verso la normalit\u00e0\"|website=Miur - Ministero dell'istruzione - Ministero dell'universit\u00e0 e della ricerca|language=it-IT|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref> [[Palermo]] and [[Naples]] closed all schools until 29 February.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://napoli.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/26/news/coronavirus_a_napoli_scuole_chiuse_fino_a_sabato-249615433/|title=Coronavirus: a Napoli scuole chiuse fino a sabato 29 febbraio|date=2020-02-26|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=2020-02-26}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.blogsicilia.it/palermo/coronavirus-scuole-chiuse-palermo-ordinanza-regione/520347/|title=Scuole chiuse fino a luned\u00ec a Palermo e Provincia, arriva l'ordinanza regionale|date=2020-02-25|website=BlogSicilia - Ultime notizie dalla Sicilia|language=it-IT|access-date=2020-02-26}}</ref> The [[University of Basilicata]] installed a thermal scanner and continued all teaching activities as per normal.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ansa.it/basilicata/notizie/2020/02/26/coronavirus-scanner-termico-allunibas_1147963f-0e34-4dbe-96a9-4e76a15b5264.html|title=Coronavirus: scanner termico all'Unibas - Basilicata|date=2020-02-26|website=Agenzia ANSA|language=it|access-date=2020-02-26}}</ref> The [[University of Bari]] suspended all medical- and health-related internships for medical and healthcare students.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://bari.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/26/news/coronavirus_sospesi_i_tirocini_per_gli_studenti_di_medicina_di_bari-249627906/|title=Coronavirus, sospesi i tirocini di Medicina a Bari. Gli studenti: \"Spiegateci il perch\u00e9\"|date=2020-02-26|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=2020-02-26}}</ref> [[Polytechnic University of Milan|Politecnico di Milano]] conducted thesis mentoring for more than one thousand students graduating the following week using [[Skype]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://milano.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/26/news/coronavirus_in_lombardia_al_politecnico_di_milano_la_tesi_di_laurea_si_discute_via_skype-249628719/|title=Coronavirus in Lombardia, al Politecnico di Milano la tesi di laurea si discute via Skype|date=2020-02-26|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=2020-02-26}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Covid Sign.jpg|thumb|upright=1.13|A sign in [[Bologna]], advising the closure of all museums in the city due to the outbreak]]\nThe [[Italian Winter Sports Federation]] decided to proceed with the Women's World Cup alpine skiing races at [[La Thuile, Aosta Valley]] on 29 February.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://torino.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/26/news/coronavirus_confermate_le_gare_della_coppa_del_mondo_di_sci_femminile_a_la_thuile-249617192/|title=Coronavirus, confermate le gare della coppa del mondo di sci femminile a La Thuile|date=2020-02-26|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=2020-02-26}}</ref> The MIDO Milan Eyewear Show was rescheduled to 5 to 7 July.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wmido.com/ita-la-50a-edizione-di-mido-si-terra-dal-5-al-7-luglio/|title=MIDO 2020 will take place from July 5 to the 7 at Rho Fiera Milano - WMido|website=www.wmido.com|access-date=2020-02-26}}</ref>\n\nOn 27 February, [[Taranto]], [[Apulia]] closed all schools until 29 February.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.primocircolotaranto.gov.it/wordpress/ordinanza-n-13-comune-di-taranto-chiusura-scuole-per-le-giornate-del-27-28-e-29-febbraio-2020/|title=Ordinanza n. 13 -Comune di Taranto chiusura scuole per le giornate del 27 28 e 29 febbraio 2020 \u2013 Istituto Comprensivo Renato Moro|language=it-IT|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref> Multiple schools were closed in Roseto degli Abruzzi.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.abruzzolive.it/coronavirus-turista-positivo-chiuse-scuole-a-roseto-in-ricostruzione-movimenti-del-paziente-brianzolo/|title=Coronavirus, turista positivo: chiuse scuole a Roseto. In ricostruzione movimenti del paziente brianzolo|website=AbruzzoLive|language=it-IT|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref> [[D'Annunzio University of Chieti\u2013Pescara|D'Annunzio University]] suspended all activities until 29 February.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.scuolainforma.it/2020/02/26/aggiornamento-coronavirus-al-26-2-per-ogni-regione-altre-scuole-chiuse-nuovo-decreto.html|title=Aggiornamento Coronavirus al 26/2 per ogni regione: altre scuole chiuse, decreto con nuove misure|date=2020-02-26|website=ScuolaInforma|language=it-IT|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref> Cartoocomics Fair in Milan was rescheduled to 2 to 4 October.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://it.finance.yahoo.com/notizie/coronavirus-fiera-milano-posticipa-cartoomics-al-2-4-104522157.html|title=Coronavirus, Fiera Milano posticipa Cartoomics al 2-4 ottobre|website=it.finance.yahoo.com|language=it-IT|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref> The Winter Rescue Race in [[Piedmont]] was cancelled.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.unionemonregalese.it/2020/02/27/annullata-coronavirus-winter-rescue-race-artesina/|title=Artesina: le gare di Soccorso alpino annullate per l'emergenza coronavirus|last=Monregalese|first=Redazione Unione|date=2020-02-27|website=L'Unione Monregalese|language=it-IT|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref> [[University of Bologna]] planned to set up a remote teaching project in which exams and lessons would be delivered to students online, to be partially completed on 2 March.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://bologna.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/27/news/coronavirus_universita_di_bologna_lezioni_esami_e_lauree_on_line-249716958/|title=Coronavirus, Universit\u00e0 di Bologna: lezioni, esami e lauree on line|date=2020-02-27|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref> [[Messina]] closed all schools from 29 February to 3 March.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.strettoweb.com/2020/02/coronavirus-messina-scuole/976298/|title=Messina, scuole chiuse per il Coronavirus: ecco l'ordinanza del sindaco|date=2020-02-27|website=Stretto Web|language=it-IT|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref>\n\nOn 28 February, during an interview with [[Rai News24]], Professor Massimo Galli from the Luigi Sacco Hospital in Milan suggested that the majority of newly recorded cases were pre-existing cases that were finally detected during the extensive tests performed on people (and their relatives) who had come in contact with confirmed patients.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rainews.it/dl/rainews/media/ContentItem-81824682-be63-4c83-a220-ae2b5630732b.html|title=Massimo Galli: il virus circolava gi\u00e0 prima dei casi conclamati|website=Rainews|language=italian|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref> The rapid increase of positive cases was the result of the blanket testing approach that was deployed following the first confirmed case in Codogno.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/28/news/_polmoniti_anomale_a_meta_gennaio_cosi_e_nato_il_focolaio_di_codogno_-249759796/|title=Coronavirus, polmoniti anomale a met\u00e0 gennaio: \"Cos\u00ec \u00e8 nato il focolaio di Codogno\"|date=2020-02-27|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref>\n\nThe Ministry of Health announced new guidelines for reporting cases. It would no longer report asymptomatic cases (positive swabs taken from patients who were not showing symptoms), which had counted as 40 to 50% of all reported cases at the time. These people would undergo isolation at home and would be followed up with new tests until they were negative.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/28/news/cambia_il_metodo_di_conteggio_esclusi_i_positivi_asintomatici-249765660/|title=Cambia il metodo di conteggio: esclusi i positivi asintomatici|date=2020-02-27|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://abcnews.go.com/Health/wireStory/italy-virus-count-methods-agencys-urging-69254949|title=Italy blasts virus panic as it eyes new testing criteria|last=News|first=A. B. C.|website=ABC News|language=en|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref> Universities in Lombardy extended their closure until 7 March.<ref name=\"Repubblica_liveupdate\" />\n\n===Nationwide measures===\nOn 1 March, the Council of Ministers approved a decree to organise the containment of the outbreak. In the decree, the Italian national territory was divided into three areas:<ref>{{cite news |title=Il governo firma il decreto coronavirus: l'Italia divisa in 3 zone |url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2020/03/01/news/coronavirus_misure_governo-249980561/ |accessdate=2 March 2020 |work=la Repubblica |date=1 March 2020 |language=it}}</ref>\n* A red zone (composed of the municipalities of Bertonico, Casalpusterlengo, Castelgerundo, Castiglione D'Adda, Codogno, Fombio, Maleo, San Fiorano, Somaglia and Terranova dei Passerini in Lombardy, and the municipality of V\u00f2 in Veneto), where the whole population is in quarantine.\n* A yellow zone (composed of the regions of Lombardy, Veneto and Emilia-Romagna), where social and sport events are suspended and schools, theatres, clubs and cinemas are closed.\n* The rest of the national territory, where safety and prevention measures are advertised in public places and special sanitisations are performed on means of public transport.\n\n[[File:COVID19 avvisi a Bologna.jpg|left|thumb|Montage of notices on shops in Bologna declaring their temporary closure, or requiring people to stay at least one metre apart]]\nOn 4 March, the Italian government imposed the shutdown of all schools and universities nationwide for two weeks as the country reached 100 deaths from the outbreak.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Guerzoni |first1=Monica |title=Scuole e universit\u00e0 di tutta Italia chiuse fino a met\u00e0 marzo per il coronavirus |url=https://www.corriere.it/scuola/20_marzo_04/coronavirus-scuole-chiuse-tutta-italia-decisione-governo-entro-stasera-e7ba0614-5e12-11ea-8e26-25d9a5210d01.shtml |accessdate=4 March 2020 |work=Corriere della Sera |date=3 April 2020 |language=it}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=Palermo|first=Angela Giuffrida Lorenzo Tondo in|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/04/italy-orders-closure-of-schools-and-universities-due-to-coronavirus|title=Italy orders closure of all schools and universities due to coronavirus|date=2020-03-04|work=The Guardian|access-date=2020-03-05|last2=Beaumont|first2=Peter|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref> The same day, the government ruled that all sporting events in Italy would be played behind closed doors until 3 April.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.football-italia.net/150823/official-behind-closed-doors-until-april-3|title=Official: Behind closed doors until April 3|publisher=Football Italia|date=4 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 5 March, when the newly appointed [[Emilia-Romagna]] regional minister of health, Raffale Donini, tested positive for COVID-19, Governor [[Stefano Bonaccini]] appointed Sergio Venturi as commissioner for the emergency. Venturi was the regional minister of health until February 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://gazzettadireggio.gelocal.it/reggio/cronaca/2020/03/05/news/coronavirus-positivo-l-assessore-donini-torna-in-campo-l-ex-venturi-1.38553828|title=Coronavirus, positivo l'assessore Donini: torna in campo l'ex Venturi &#124; Limitazioni per gli accompagnatori nei pronto soccorso &#124; A Reggio Emilia undici casi in pi\u00f9: adesso sono 31|date=5 March 2020|website=Gazzetta di Reggio|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn the night between 7 and 8 March, the government approved a decree to lock down Lombardy and 14 other provinces in Veneto, Emilia-Romagna, Piedmont and Marche, involving more than 16 million people.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-51787238|title=Northern Italy quarantines 16 million people|work=BBC News|date=8 March 2020|accessdate=8 March 2020|via=www.bbc.com}}</ref> The decree \"absolutely avoided any movement into and out of the areas\" and, like the previous one, it provided sanctions of up to three months in prison for those who violated the lockdown.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/italy-plans-large-scale-lockdown-in-countrys-north-to-fight-coronavirus-11583613874|title=Italy Locks Down the Country's North to Fight Coronavirus|first=Eric Sylvers and Giovanni|last=Legorano|date=8 March 2020|accessdate=8 March 2020|via=www.wsj.com}}</ref> It was possible to move into and out of the areas only for emergencies or \"proven working needs\", which must be authorised by the [[prefect]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/03/08/news/coronavirus_i_decreti_del_governo-250617415/|title=Coronavirus, il decreto del governo: tutte le misure per la zona arancione e quelle per il resto d'Italia|date=8 March 2020|website=la Repubblica|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref> The decree also established the closure of all gyms, swimming pools, spas and wellness centres. Shopping centres had to be closed on weekends, while other commercial activities could remain open if a distance of one metre between customers could be guaranteed.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.romatoday.it/attualita/coronavirus-pub-cinema-teatri-locali-chiusi-nuovo-decreto.html|title=Coronavirus: stop a pub, cinema, teatro e discoteche anche a Roma. Ecco cosa prevede il nuovo decreto|website=RomaToday|language=it|access-date=2020-03-08}}</ref> The decree imposed the closure of museums, cultural centres and ski resorts in the lockdown areas and the closure of cinemas, theatres, pubs, dance schools, game rooms, betting rooms and [[bingo]] halls, [[disco]]s and similar places in the entire country.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.romatoday.it/attualita/coronavirus-pub-cinema-teatri-locali-chiusi-nuovo-decreto.html|title=Coronavirus: stop a pub, cinema, teatro e discoteche anche a Roma. Ecco cosa prevede il nuovo decreto|website=RomaToday|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref> Civil and religious ceremonies, including [[funeral]] ceremonies, were suspended. All organised events were also suspended, as well as events in public or private places, including those of a cultural, recreational, sporting and religious nature, even if held in closed places.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://corrieredellumbria.corr.it/news/coronavirus/1516428/emergenza-coronavirus-bozza-decreto-sospesi-anche--funerali-in-lombardia-e-11-province-covi19-epidemia-contagio.html|title=Emergenza Coronavirus, bozza decreto: sospesi anche i funerali in Lombardia e 11 province|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref> This measure was described as the largest lockdown in the history of Europe,<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/08/world/europe/italy-coronavirus-quarantine.html|title=On Day 1 of Lockdown, Italian Officials Urge Citizens to Abide by Rules|first1=Jason|last1=Horowitz|first2=Emma|last2=Bubola|date=8 March 2020|accessdate=10 March 2020|via=NYTimes.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theverge.com/2020/3/7/21169637/italy-lockdown-lombardy-coronavirus-outbreak|title=Italy locks down northern region in response to coronavirus outbreak|first=Kim|last=Lyons|date=7 March 2020|website=The Verge|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref> as well as the most aggressive response taken in any region beyond China, and paralysed the wealthiest parts of the country as Italy attempted to constrain the rapid spread of the disease.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Horowitz |first1=Jason |title=Italy Locks Down Much of the Country's North Over the Coronavirus |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/07/world/europe/coronavirus-italy.html|accessdate=8 March 2020 |work=The New York Times |date=7 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Italia>[https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/europe/italy-coronavirus-milan-lombardy-lockdowns/2020/03/07/403fcea2-60b3-11ea-ac50-18701e14e06d_story.html To contain coronavirus, Italy will restrict movement across much of its northern region, including the city of Milan], ''[[Washington Post]]'', Chico Harlan and Stefano Pitrelli, 7 March 2020. Retrieved 8 March 2020.</ref>\n\nRiots broke out in many penitentiaries throughout Italy after restrictions on [[conjugal visit]]s were imposed by the government in the 8 March decree.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.timesofisrael.com/liveblog_entry/italian-prisoners-riot-over-coronavirus-restrictions/|title=Italian prisoners riot over coronavirus restrictions|website=www.timesofisrael.com|accessdate=10 March 2020}}</ref> Nine prisoners died in [[Modena]] and three in [[Rieti]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://bologna.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/03/09/news/modena_sei_morti_nella_rivolta_in_carcere-250719903/|title=Modena, sette detenuti morti nella rivolta in carcere e sei in prognosi riservata|date=9 March 2020|website=la Repubblica|accessdate=10 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/03/10/news/coronavirus_carceri_ancora_proteste_tre_detenuti_morti_a_rieti-250829816/|title=Coronavirus, carceri, ancora proteste. Tre detenuti morti a Rieti, le vittime salgono a dodici|date=10 March 2020|website=la Repubblica|accessdate=11 March 2020}}</ref> while 76 detainees escaped from [[Foggia]]'s penitentiary.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ansa.it/sito/notizie/cronaca/2020/03/09/rivolta-in-carcere-foggiaalcuni-evadono_1e2d031d-d354-4076-8129-bdccaed5fa23.html|title=Rivolta in carcere Foggia,alcuni evadono - Cronaca|date=9 March 2020|website=Agenzia ANSA|accessdate=10 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://bari.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/03/09/news/coronavirus_detenuti_evadono_dal_carcere_di_foggia_e_vengono_bloccati_all_esterno-250720580/|title=Coronavirus, rivolta nelle carceri: a Foggia evasione di massa. A Trani e Bari strade bloccate|date=9 March 2020|website=la Repubblica|accessdate=10 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://abcnews.go.com/Health/wireStory/italian-inmates-die-protest-virus-measures-69482325|title=Prison riots hit Italy amid virus; 6 die in overdose|date=9 March 2020|work=ABC News|accessdate=10 March 2020}}</ref> Two prison agents were assaulted and kidnapped in [[Pavia]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ilfattoquotidiano.it/2020/03/08/coronavirus-rivolta-nelle-carceri-a-pavia-sequestrati-2-agenti-modena-morto-un-detenuto-proteste-pure-a-frosinone-napoli-e-palermo/5729730/|title=Coronavirus, rivolta nelle carceri: a Pavia sequestrati 2 agenti. Modena, morti tre detenuti. Proteste pure a Frosinone, Napoli e Palermo|date=8 March 2020|website=Il Fatto Quotidiano|accessdate=10 March 2020}}</ref> On 9 March in [[Bologna]], detainees took control of the Dozza penitentiary, forcing personnel to exit the building.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/search/top/?q=\u00e8tv&epa=SEARCH_BOX|title=Rivolta anche al carcere di Bologna|accessdate=10 March 2020}}</ref> On 11 March, two prisoners were found dead in Bologna's penitentiary.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://bologna.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/03/11/news/detenuto_morto_dozza-250944868/|title=Rivolta nel carcere di Bologna: morto un detenuto|date=11 March 2020|website=la Repubblica|accessdate=12 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 9 March, the government announced that all sporting events in Italy would be cancelled until at least 3 April, but the ban does not include Italian clubs or national teams participating in international competitions.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/51808683|title=Coronavirus: All sport in Italy to be suspended because of outbreak|date=2020-03-09|work=BBC Sport|access-date=2020-03-09|language=en-GB}}</ref> In the evening, Conte announced in a press conference that all measures previously applied only in the so-called \"red zones\" had been extended to the whole country, putting approximately 60 million people in lockdown. Conte later proceeded to officially sign the new executive decree.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Reynolds |first1=Emma |last2=Picheta |first2=Rob |title=All of Italy is in lockdown as coronavirus cases rise |url=https://edition.cnn.com/2020/03/09/europe/coronavirus-italy-lockdown-intl/index.html |accessdate=9 March 2020 |work=CNN |date=9 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Tondo |first1=Lorenzo |title=Coronavirus: Italian PM extends lockdown to entire country |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/09/coronavirus-italy-prime-minister-country-lockdown?utm_term=Autofeed&CMP=twt_gu&utm_medium&utm_source=Twitter#Echobox=1583793579 |accessdate=9 March 2020 |work=The Guardian |date=9 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Ian Art Photography - Italy 100 people queuing at a supermarket during coronavirus outbreak mar-2020.jpg|thumb|upright=1.13|Queue in front of a supermarket after the introduction of [[social distancing]] rules]]\nOn 11 March, the government allocated 25 billion euros for the emergency.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.repubblica.it/economia/2020/03/11/news/emergenza_coronavirus_conferenza_stampa_conte_misure_economiche-250924846/|title=Emergenza coronavirus, il piano del governo sale a 25 miliardi. Gualtieri alla Ue: 'Servono stimoli'|date=11 March 2020|website=la Repubblica|accessdate=12 March 2020}}</ref> In the evening, Conte announced a tightening of the lockdown, with all commercial and retail businesses except those providing essential services, like grocery shops and pharmacies, closed down.<ref name=\":13\" /><ref name=\":12\" /><ref>{{cite web |title=Coronavirus Measures |url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2020/03/11/news/coronavirus_conte_italia_governo_misure-250988471/?ref=RHPPTP-BL-I250988111-C12-P1-S1.12-T1 |website=La Repubblica |date = 11 March 2020|accessdate=11 March 2020}}</ref> He also appointed Domenico Arcuri as Delegated Commissioner for the Emergency. Arcuri will cooperate with Commissioner [[Angelo Borrelli]] with the aim of strengthening the distribution of [[intensive care unit|intensive care]] equipment.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fanpage.it/attualita/coronavirus-il-governo-nominera-domenico-arcuri-commissario-delegato-per-lemergenza/|title=Coronavirus: chi \u00e8 Domenico Arcuri, il commissario delegato per l'emergenza scelto da Conte|website=Fanpage|accessdate=12 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 19 March, the [[Italian Army|Army]] was deployed to the city of [[Bergamo]], the worst hit [[Italy|Italian]] city by the coronavirus, as the local authorities can no longer process the number of dead residents. The city's mayor [[Giorgio Gori]] said the true number of dead could be much higher than reported.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.adnkronos.com/fatti/cronaca/2020/03/18/coronavirus-gori-tanti-muoiono-casa-non-vengono-contati_tLagSTNm9fczG1a59ZhosI.html|title=Coronavirus, Gori: \"Tanti muoiono in casa, non vengono contati\"|website=Adnkronos}}</ref> Army trucks transported bodies to [[crematorium]]s in several other cities, as cemeteries in the city were full.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.sky.com/story/coronavirus-italian-army-called-in-to-carry-away-corpses-as-citys-crematorium-is-overwhelmed-11959994|title=Coronavirus: Italian army called in as crematorium struggles to cope with deaths|website=Sky News}}</ref> On the following day, the Army was called in to assist the police forces in enforcing the lockdown.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Di Donato |first1=Valentina |last2=Ruotolo |first2=Nicola |last3=Smith-Spark |first3=Laura |title=Italy calls in military to enforce lockdown as 627 people die in 24 hours |url=https://edition.cnn.com/2020/03/20/europe/italy-military-coronavirus-intl/index.html |accessdate=21 March 2020 |work=CNN |date=20 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 20 March, the Ministry of Health ordered tighter regulations on free movement. The new measures banned open-air sports and running, except individually and in close proximity of one's residence. Parks, playgrounds and public green were closed down. Furthermore, movement across the country was further restricted, by banning \"any movement towards a residence different from the main one\", including holiday homes, during weekends and holidays.<ref>{{cite news |title=Le nuove restrizioni decise dal governo |url=https://www.ilpost.it/2020/03/20/ordinanza-coronavirus-attivita-sportiva-correre/ |accessdate=21 March 2020 |work=Il Post |date=20 March 2020 |language=it-IT}}</ref>\n\nOn 21 March, Conte announced further restrictions within the nationwide lockdown, by halting all non-essential production, industries and businesses in Italy, following the rise in the number of new cases and deaths in the previous days.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Farrer |first1=Martin |title=Italy: PM warns of worst crisis since WW2 as coronavirus deaths leap by almost 800 |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/22/italian-pm-warns-of-worst-crisis-since-ww2-as-coronavirus-deaths-leap-by-almost-800 |accessdate=22 March 2020 |work=The Guardian |date=22 March 2020}}</ref> This measure had also been strongly asked for by multiple institutions, including trade unions, mayors, and regional presidents, as well as medical professionals, but was initially opposed by the industrialists.<ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus, i sindaci toscani scrivono a Conte: \"Chiudere tutto ci\u00f2 che non \u00e8 essenziale\" |url=https://www.lanazione.it/cronaca/coronavirus-sindaci-toscana-chiudere-tutto-1.5076824 |accessdate=22 March 2020 |work=La Nazione |date=21 March 2020 |language=it}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title='Chiudere fabbriche', 41 sindaci a Conte - Abruzzo |url=http://www.ansa.it/abruzzo/notizie/2020/03/17/chiudere-fabbriche-41-sindaci-a-conte_2b8aaf8a-15de-46a2-ae61-5baa6389fb36.html |accessdate=22 March 2020 |work=Agenzia ANSA |date=17 March 2020 |language=it}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Chiudere le fabbriche? La lettera dei sindacati |url=https://www.repubblica.it/economia/2020/03/21/news/chiudere_le_fabbriche_la_lettera_dei_sindacati-251916540/ |accessdate=22 March 2020 |work=la Repubblica |date=21 March 2020 |language=it}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=I medici della Lombardia: \"Chiudere tutte le attivit\u00e0 non essenziali\". Il no degli industriali |url=https://www.huffingtonpost.it/entry/gli-industriali-dicono-no-alla-chiusura-delle-fabbriche_it_5e68d0eec5b60557280e9304 |accessdate=22 March 2020 |work=L'HuffPost |date=11 March 2020 |language=it}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus, Milano trema: 634 casi in un giorno. Fontana chiama Conte: chiudere tutto, Esercito per strada |url=https://www.ilmessaggero.it/italia/coronavirus_milano_casi_contagi_lombardia_ultime_notizie-5121166.html |accessdate=22 March 2020 |work=www.ilmessaggero.it |language=it}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=De Angelis |first1=Alessandro |title=\"Chiudete tutto, anche le fabbriche\" (di A. De Angelis) |url=https://www.huffingtonpost.it/entry/giorgio-gori-chiudete-tutto-anche-le-fabbriche_it_5e74ad81c5b63c3b648e6263 |accessdate=22 March 2020 |work=L'HuffPost |date=20 March 2020 |language=it}}</ref>\n\nOn 24 March, in a live-streamed press conference, Conte announced a new decree approved by the Council of Ministers. The decree imposed higher fines for the violation of the restrictive measures, and a regulation of the relationship between government and Parliament during the emergency. It included also the possibility of reducing or suspending public and private transport, and gave the regional governments power to impose additional restrictive regulations in their Regions for a maximum of seven days before being confirmed by national decree.<ref>{{cite news |title=Italy announces fines of up to \u20ac3,000 for breaking quarantine rules |url=https://www.thelocal.it/20200324/italy-announces-fines-of-up-to-3000-for-breaking-quarantine-rules |accessdate=25 March 2020 |work=thelocal.it |date=24 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Cosa ha detto Giuseppe Conte |url=https://www.ilpost.it/2020/03/24/decreto-restrizioni-sanzioni-coronavirus/ |accessdate=25 March 2020 |work=Il Post |date=24 March 2020 |language=it-IT}}</ref>\n\n===Local measures===\n====Campania====\nOn 15 March, President of Campania [[Vincenzo De Luca]] imposed a strict quarantine on [[Ariano Irpino]], in the province of Avellino, and four other municipalities in the province of Salerno, [[Atena Lucana]], [[Caggiano]], [[Polla, Italy|Polla]], and [[Sala Consilina]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus, De Luca \"chiude\" altri quattro Comuni |url=https://napoli.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/03/15/news/de_luca_chiude_altri_4_comuni-251388474/ |accessdate=16 March 2020 |work=la Repubblica |date=15 March 2020 |language=it}}</ref>\n\n====Emilia-Romagna====\nOn 16 March, the government of Emilia-Romagna imposed a strengthened quarantine on the municipality of [[Medicina]], near Bologna, since it had developed an intense outbreak. People were not allowed to enter or exit the town for any reason.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bologna.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/03/16/news/coronavirus_medicina_e_zona_rossa_vietato_entrare_e_uscire-251412467/ |title=Coronavirus, Medicina \u00e8 zona rossa, vietato entrare e uscire|date=16 March 2020|website=la Repubblica}}</ref>\n\n===Screening and testing policies===\n{{Expand section |date=March 2020}}\nThe strategy of mass-testing [[asymptomatic carriers]] was proven to be successful in stopping the spread of the virus in one Italian town.<ref name=Horowitz2020-03-21>{{cite web |last1=Horowitz |first1=Jason |last2=Bubola |first2=Emma |last3=Povoledo |first3=Elisabetta |title=Italy, Pandemic's New Epicenter, Has Lessons for the World |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/21/world/europe/italy-coronavirus-center-lessons.html |website=[[The New York Times]] |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20200322023527/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/21/world/europe/italy-coronavirus-center-lessons.html |archivedate=23 March 2020 |date=21 March 2020 |url-status=live |quote=steps to isolate the coronavirus and limit people\u2019s movement need to be put in place early, with absolute clarity, then strictly enforced}}</ref><ref name=McCall2020-03-19>{{cite web |last1=McCall |first1=Rosie |title=Coronavirus mass testing experiment in Italian town appears to have halted COVID-19 outbreak |url=https://www.newsweek.com/coronavirus-mass-testing-experiment-italian-town-covid-19-outbreak-1493183 |website=[[Newsweek]] |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20200321131113/https://www.newsweek.com/coronavirus-mass-testing-experiment-italian-town-covid-19-outbreak-1493183 |archivedate=21 March 2020 |language=en |date=19 March 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=Crisanti2020-03-20>{{cite web |last1=Crisanti |first1=Andrea |authorlink=Andrea Crisanti (scientist) |last2=Cassone |first2=Antonio |title=In one Italian town, we showed mass testing could eradicate the coronavirus |url=https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2020/mar/20/eradicated-coronavirus-mass-testing-covid-19-italy-vo |website=[[The Guardian]] / [[University of Padua]] |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20200323203803/https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2020/mar/20/eradicated-coronavirus-mass-testing-covid-19-italy-vo |archivedate=23 March 2020 |date=20 March 2020 |url-status=live |quote=asymptomatic or quasi-symptomatic subjects represent a good 70% of all virus-infected people and, still worse, an unknown, yet impossible to ignore portion of them can transmit the virus to others}}</ref> This strategy in Italy was supported by the region of [[Veneto]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ilfattoquotidiano.it/2020/03/18/coronavirus-zaia-vanno-chiusi-supermercati-nel-weekend-e-vietate-passeggiate-si-al-controllo-su-celle-telefoniche-ma-ci-vuole-norma/5740615/|title=Coronavirus, Zaia: \"Vanno chiusi supermercati nel weekend e vietate passeggiate. S\u00ec al controllo su celle telefoniche ma ci vuole norma\"|language=italian|publisher=[[Il Fatto Quotidiano]]|first= Gisella|last=Ruccia|date=18 March 2020|access-date=23 March 2020|quote=L\u2019esperienza insegna che ogni asintomatico positivo pu\u00f2 contagiare fino a 10 altre persone. Quindi, la caccia all\u2019asintomatico positivo \u00e8 fondamentale, tanto \u00e8 vero che oggi abbiamo 8500 persone in isolamento, letteralmente trovate con questa modalit\u00e0}}</ref>\n\n==Lockdown areas==\n{{main|2020 Italy coronavirus lockdown}}\nOn 22 February, the government established a lockdown for eleven municipalities in [[Lombardy]] and [[Veneto]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.la7.it/nonelarena/video/lelenco-dei-comuni-in-quarantena-a-causa-del-coronavirus-23-02-2020-308963|title=L'elenco dei comuni in quarantena a causa del coronavirus|accessdate=8 March 2020|via=www.la7.it}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Quarantined areas of LodiProvince.png|thumb|upright=1.36|Map of the ten Lombard municipalities under lockdown since 22 February]]\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" font-size:90%;\"\n|+\nMunicipalities under quarantine, 22 February<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://metro.co.uk/2020/02/25/towns-italy-lockdown-coronavirus-12298246/|title=What towns in Italy are on lockdown because of coronavirus?|date=2020-02-25|work=Metro News|access-date=2020-02-25|language=en}}</ref>\n!''Comune''\n!Province\n!Region\n!Population\n|-\n|[[Bertonico]]\n|[[Province of Lodi|Lodi]]\n|[[Lombardy]]\n| style=\"text-align:right;\" |1,118\n|-\n|[[Casalpusterlengo]]\n|[[Province of Lodi|Lodi]]\n|[[Lombardy]]\n| style=\"text-align:right;\" |15,293 \n|-\n|[[Castelgerundo]]\n|[[Province of Lodi|Lodi]]\n|[[Lombardy]]\n| style=\"text-align:right;\" |1,498\n|-\n|[[Castiglione d\u2019Adda]]\n|[[Province of Lodi|Lodi]]\n|[[Lombardy]]\n| style=\"text-align:right;\" |4,646\n|-\n|[[Codogno]]\n|[[Province of Lodi|Lodi]]\n|[[Lombardy]]\n| style=\"text-align:right;\" |15,907\n|-\n|[[Fombio]]\n|[[Province of Lodi|Lodi]]\n|[[Lombardy]]\n| style=\"text-align:right;\" |2,317\n|-\n|[[Maleo, Lombardy|Maleo]]\n|[[Province of Lodi|Lodi]]\n|[[Lombardy]]\n| style=\"text-align:right;\" |3,098\n|-\n|[[San Fiorano]]\n|[[Province of Lodi|Lodi]]\n|[[Lombardy]]\n| style=\"text-align:right;\" |1,839\n|-\n|[[Somaglia]]\n|[[Province of Lodi|Lodi]]\n|[[Lombardy]]\n| style=\"text-align:right;\" |3,837\n|-\n|[[Terranova dei Passerini|Terranova]]\n|[[Province of Lodi|Lodi]]\n|[[Lombardy]]\n| style=\"text-align:right;\" |927\n|-\n|[[V\u00f2]]\n|[[Province of Padua|Padua]]\n|[[Veneto]]\n| style=\"text-align:right;\" |3,305\n|-\n| colspan=\"3\" |'''Quarantine total'''\n| style=\"text-align:right;\" |'''53,785'''\n|}\n\nOn 7 March, the government prepared to extend until 3 April the restricted zone to all of Lombardy, plus fourteen other provinces in Veneto (3), [[Emilia-Romagna]] (5), [[Marche]] (1) and [[Piedmont]] (5).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.corriere.it/politica/20_marzo_07/coronavirusin-lombardia-si-potra-entrare-uscire-solo-gravi-motivi-chiuse-discoteche-palestre-impianti-sci-0478cd9c-609a-11ea-8d61-438e0a276fc4.shtml|title=Coronavirus, il governo isola la Lombardia e 14 province|first=Fiorenza|last=Sarzanini|website=Corriere della Sera|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref> The lockdown affects over 16 million people, roughly a quarter of Italy's total population, and prevents people from entering or leaving the zone, except \"for proven occupational needs or situations of need or for health reasons\",<ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus, treni, aeroporti, blocchi stradali: ecco come funzionano le nuove regole del decreto del 7 marzo\n |url=https://www.corriere.it/cronache/20_marzo_08/coronavirus-ecco-come-funzionano-nuove-regole-rispettare-d657e654-611c-11ea-8f33-90c941af0f23.shtml|accessdate=8 March 2020 |work=Corriere della Sera |date=8 March 2020|language=it}}</ref> under threat of fines.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Davidson |first1=Helen |last2=Tondo |first2=Lorenzo |last3=Yu |first3=Verna |title=Coronavirus: quarter of Italy's population put in quarantine as virus reaches Washington DC |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/08/coronavirus-italy-quarantine-virus-reaches-washington-dc |accessdate=8 March 2020 |work=The Guardian |date=8 March 2020}}</ref> The [[enclave]] nation of [[San Marino]], which is nestled between two of the provinces, has been effectively locked down as well.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.romagnauno.it/san-marino/san-marino-isolato-dal-decreto-italiano-diventa-automaticamente-zona-rossa/?fbclid=IwAR3qu4hqUMBCXoaqtV-2OPtGRBN3ggIHA68_MhfHkP1FQy9Xkre82Rgog98|title=San Marino isolato dal decreto italiano diventa automaticamente Zona rossa|website=Romagna Uno|date=7 March 2020|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n[[File:COVID-19 outbreak - provinces with restrictions as for DPCM 8 March.svg|thumb|upright=1.36|Provinces under quarantine since 8 March]]\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" font-size:90%;\"\n|+\nProvinces under quarantine, 8 March<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/03/07/news/coronavirus_chiusa_la_lombardia_e_11_province_-250570150/?ref=RHPPTP-BH-I250571072-C12-P2-S1.12-T1|title=Coronavirus, chiusa la Lombardia e altre 11 province|date=2020-03-07|work=La Repubblica|access-date=2020-03-07|language=it}}</ref>\n!Province\n!Region\n!Population\n|-\n|[[Province of Alessandria|Alessandria]]\n|[[Piedmont]]\n| style=\"text-align:right;\" |420,017\n|-\n|[[Province of Asti|Asti]]\n|[[Piedmont]]\n| style=\"text-align:right;\" |214,342\n|-\n|[[Province of Bergamo|Bergamo]]\n|[[Lombardy]]\n| style=\"text-align:right;\" |1,115,536\n|-\n|[[Province of Brescia|Brescia]]\n|[[Lombardy]]\n| style=\"text-align:right;\" |1,265,954\n|-\n|[[Province of Como|Como]]\n|[[Lombardy]]\n| style=\"text-align:right;\" |599,204\n|-\n|[[Province of Cremona|Cremona]]\n|[[Lombardy]]\n| style=\"text-align:right;\" |358,955\n|-\n|[[Province of Lecco|Lecco]]\n|[[Lombardy]]\n| style=\"text-align:right;\" |337,380\n|-\n|[[Province of Lodi|Lodi]]\n|[[Lombardy]]\n| style=\"text-align:right;\" |230,198\n|-\n|[[Province of Mantua|Mantua]]\n|[[Lombardy]]\n| style=\"text-align:right;\" |411,958\n|-\n|[[Metropolitan City of Milan|Milan]]\n|[[Lombardy]]\n| style=\"text-align:right;\" |3,263,206\n|-\n|[[Province of Modena|Modena]]\n|[[Emilia-Romagna]]\n| style=\"text-align:right;\" |705,422\n|-\n|[[Province of Monza and Brianza|Monza and Brianza]]\n|[[Lombardy]]\n| style=\"text-align:right;\" |875,769\n|-\n|[[Province of Novara|Novara]]\n|[[Piedmont]]\n| style=\"text-align:right;\" |368,607\n|-\n|[[Province of Padua|Padua]]\n|[[Veneto]]\n| style=\"text-align:right;\" |938,957\n|-\n|[[Province of Parma|Parma]]\n|[[Emilia-Romagna]]\n| style=\"text-align:right;\" |452,022\n|-\n|[[Province of Pavia|Pavia]]\n|[[Lombardy]]\n| style=\"text-align:right;\" |545,888\n|-\n|[[Province of Pesaro and Urbino|Pesaro and Urbino]]\n|[[Marche]]\n| style=\"text-align:right;\" |358,886\n|-\n|[[Province of Piacenza|Piacenza]]\n|[[Emilia-Romagna]]\n| style=\"text-align:right;\" |287,152\n|-\n|[[Province of Reggio Emilia|Reggio Emilia]]\n|[[Emilia-Romagna]]\n| style=\"text-align:right;\" |531,891\n|-\n|[[Province of Rimini|Rimini]]\n|[[Emilia-Romagna]]\n| style=\"text-align:right;\" |339,437\n|-\n|[[Province of Sondrio|Sondrio]]\n|[[Lombardy]]\n| style=\"text-align:right;\" |180,811\n|-\n|[[Province of Treviso|Treviso]]\n|[[Veneto]]\n| style=\"text-align:right;\" |888,293\n|-\n|[[Province of Varese|Varese]]\n|[[Lombardy]]\n| style=\"text-align:right;\" |890,768\n|-\n|[[Metropolitan City of Venice|Venice]]\n|[[Veneto]]\n| style=\"text-align:right;\" |857,841\n|-\n|[[Province of Verbano-Cusio-Ossola|Verbano-Cusio-Ossola]]\n|[[Piedmont]]\n| style=\"text-align:right;\" |157,844\n|-\n|[[Province of Vercelli|Vercelli]]\n|[[Piedmont]]\n| style=\"text-align:right;\" |170,298\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" |'''Quarantine total'''\n| style=\"text-align:right;\" |'''16,466,636'''\n|}\n\nOn 9 March, Prime Minister Conte announced that the lockdown would be extended to the entire country.<ref name=\"auto\"/>\n\n==Reactions abroad==\n===Travel restrictions===\n{{See|Travel restrictions related to the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic}}\n{{Update section |date=March 2020}}\n[[File:Restrizioni per gli Italiani COVID19.png|thumb|upright=2.27|\nRestrictions to travel from Italy, as of 31 March 2020\n{{legend|#008000|Italy}}\n{{legend|#AA0000|Entrance refused to people from Italy}}\n{{legend|#003380|Imposed quarantine on people arriving from Italy}}]]\nOn 23 February 2020, [[Austria]] suspended all trains to and from Italy for a few hours because of suspected cases.<ref name=\"Repubblica_liveupdate\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.sky.com/story/coronavirus-towns-in-lockdown-as-italy-races-to-contain-europes-biggest-outbreak-11941438|title=Coronavirus: Austria stops all trains to and from Italy amid Europe's biggest coronavirus outbreak|publisher=Sky News|access-date=23 February 2020}}</ref> [[Romania]] instituted a quarantine for people arriving from Lombardy and Veneto.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.news1.news/2020/02/coronavirus-romania-quarantine-for-those-returning-from-lombardy-and-veneto-ischia-northern-tourists-stop-landing.html|title=Coronavirus, Romania: quarantine for those returning from Lombardy and Veneto {{!}} Ischia, Northern tourists stop landing |work=News1 English |access-date=23 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 24 February, an [[Alitalia]] flight from Rome to [[Mauritius]] was blocked at the [[Sir Seewoosagur Ramgoolam International Airport]] by the local authorities, who imposed quarantine or repatriation for 212 Italian passengers.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.corriere.it/cronache/20_febbraio_24/coronavirus-volo-alitalia-fermo-mauritius-quarantena-o-rimpatrio-aa38bc60-56e5-11ea-b89d-a5ca249e9e1e.shtml|title=Coronavirus, volo Alitalia con 300 persone a bordo fermo a Mauritius|last=Salvia|first=Flavio Haver e Lorenzo|date=24 February 2020|website=Corriere della Sera}}</ref> Of the 212 passengers, 172 were allowed to disembark while 40 passengers from Lombardy and Veneto decided to go back to Italy.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/china-health-italy-flight-idUSL5N2AO35K|title=UPDATE 1-Mauritius blocks some Italian visitors over coronavirus concerns -Alitalia|date=2020-02-24|work=Reuters|access-date=2020-02-25|language=en}}</ref> An intercity bus operated by [[Flixbus]] from Milan to [[Lyon]] was quarantined at [[Gare de Lyon-Perrache]] station so that its passengers could undergo health checks.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.askanews.it/esteri/2020/02/24/coronavirus-flixbus-arrivato-da-milano-confinato-a-stazione-lione-pn_20200224_00123|title=Coronavirus, Flixbus arrivato da Milano confinato a stazione Lione|date=24 February 2020|website=Askanews|language=it-IT|access-date=24 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n[[Brazil]] added Italy to its COVID-19 alert list, meaning that passengers entering Brazil from Italy showing flu symptoms would undergo medical checkups.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usnews.com/news/world/articles/2020-02-24/brazil-to-check-arrivals-from-italy-france-germany-for-coronavirus-symptoms|title=Brazil to Check Arrivals From Italy, France, Germany for Coronavirus Symptoms|last=|first=|date=|website=Usnews|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> [[Argentina]], [[France]], [[Croatia]], [[Egypt]], [[Greece]], [[Ireland]], [[Israel]], [[Latvia]], [[Lithuania]], [[Ukraine]], [[Serbia]] and [[South Africa]] issued multiple recommendations that included postponement of school trips to Italy, a 14-day quarantine for people arriving from Lombardy and Veneto and a warning for all citizens to not to travel to regions of Italy affected by the outbreak.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.srbija.gov.rs/vest/en/150543/foreign-ministry-advises-serbian-citizens-against-travelling-to-italy.php|title=Foreign Ministry advises Serbian citizens against travelling to Italy|last=srbija.gov.rs|website=srbija.gov.rs|language=en|access-date=24 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.lemonde.fr/planete/article/2020/02/24/coronavirus-mesures-de-precaution-hausse-de-la-mobilisation-comment-la-france-se-prepare-a-une-possible-epidemie_6030677_3244.html|title=Coronavirus : la France prend des mesures de pr\u00e9caution pour les personnes revenant d'Italie|date=2020-02-24|work=Le Monde.fr|access-date=2020-02-24|language=fr}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.euronews.com/2020/02/24/covid-19-outbreak-in-italy-what-are-other-eu-countries-doing|title=COVID-19 outbreak in Italy: What are other EU countries doing?|last=Monella|first=Lillo Montalto|date=2020-02-24|website=euronews|language=en|access-date=2020-02-24}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/24/news/coronavirus_viaggi_turismo_italia-249495072/|title=Coronavirus, sempre pi\u00f9 paesi sconsigliano i viaggi in Italia: \"Una mazzata per il turismo e il pil\"|date=2020-02-24|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=2020-02-24}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lrt.lt/en/news-in-english/19/1145534/coronavirus-lithuania-may-declare-state-emergency|title=Coronavirus: Lithuania may declare state emergency|date=2020-02-24|website=lrt.lt|language=lt|access-date=2020-02-26}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.corriere.it/esteri/20_febbraio_25/coronavirus-stati-che-impongono-restrizioni-all-italia-404a91e6-57e6-11ea-a2d7-f1bec9902bd3.shtml|title=Ingressi vietati, quarantena e invito all'isolamento: le restrizioni imposte agli italiani all'estero|last=Frate|first=Claudio Del|date=2020-02-25|website=Corriere della Sera|language=it|access-date=2020-02-26}}</ref> A joint [[World Health Organization|WHO]] and [[European Centre for Disease Prevention and Control|ECDC]] mission arrived in Italy to support COVID-19 control and prevention efforts.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.euro.who.int/en/countries/italy/news/news/2020/2/joint-who-and-ecdc-mission-in-italy-to-support-covid-19-control-and-prevention-efforts|title=Joint WHO and ECDC mission in Italy to support COVID-19 control and prevention efforts|date=2020-02-24|website=euro.who.int|language=en|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref> Following the discovery of a case involving an Italian citizen, the H10 Costa Adeje Palace in Tenerife was put on lockdown.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.cnn.com/2020/02/25/europe/tenerife-coronavirus-hotel-intl/index.html|title=Tenerife hotel on partial lockdown as Italian tests positive for coronavirus|author1=Laura Perez Maestro |first2=Niamh |last2=Kennedy |first3=Amy|last3=Woodyatt|website=CNN|access-date=2020-02-29}}</ref>\n\nThe [[European Parliament]]'s Director General for Personnel, Kristian Knudsen, requested that staff who had travelled to areas affected by the COVID-19 outbreak, including parts of Italy, China, Singapore and South Korea, to self-quarantine and work from home for 14 days.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.politico.eu/article/parliament-tells-staff-to-stay-home-if-they-visited-places-hit-by-coronavirus/|title=Parliament tells staff to stay home if they visited places hit by coronavirus|last=Deutsch|first=Jillian|date=2020-02-24|website=POLITICO|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/26/news/conoravirus_bruxelles_bartolo-249655095/|title=Coronavirus, il racconto in prima persona di Bartolo: \"Io, deputato europeo in quarantena, fuori dal Parlamento\"|date=26 February 2020|website=la Repubblica}}</ref>\n\nOn 25 February, the [[United Kingdom]] and [[Malta]] recommended that travellers coming from Italy self-quarantine for 14 days and for all citizens not to travel to regions of Italy affected by the outbreak.<ref name=\"Repubblica_liveupdate\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.maltatoday.com.mt/news/national/100587/corona_virus_health_ministry|title=No coronavirus cases in Malta, Health Ministry says|website=MaltaToday.com.mt|language=en|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-51625733|title=New coronavirus advice for Britons back from Italy|date=2020-02-25|work=BBC News|access-date=2020-02-25|language=en-GB}}</ref> Malta installed thermal-scanning devices to monitor passengers arriving via [[Malta International Airport]], as well as passengers disembarking from vessels at the [[Grand Harbour]] and the [[Virtu Ferries]] catamaran terminal in [[Marsa, Malta|Marsa]], which had direct connections to [[Pozzallo|Pozzalo]] and [[Catania]] in [[Sicily]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofmalta.com/articles/view/no-covid-19-cases-in-malta-at-this-point-health-ministry.773582|title=No coronavirus cases in Malta but country is well prepared, say authorities|website=Times of Malta|language=en-gb|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref> [[Prague International Airport]] introduced special arrival gates for selective screening of passengers arriving on flights from Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.radio.cz/en/section/news/coronavirus-prague-airport-designates-special-gates-for-arrivals-from-italy|title=Coronavirus: Prague Airport designates special gates for arrivals from Italy|website=Radio Prague International|language=en|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ceskenoviny.cz/zpravy/letiste-praha-ma-specialni-brany-pro-prilety-z-italie/1858394|title=Leti\u0161t\u011b Praha m\u00e1 speci\u00e1ln\u00ed br\u00e1ny pro p\u0159\u00edlety z It\u00e1lie {{!}} \u010cesk\u00e9Noviny.cz|website=www.ceskenoviny.cz|language=cs|access-date=2020-02-26}}</ref> [[Kuwait]], [[Iraq]], [[Jordan]] and [[Seychelles]] suspended all flights to and from Italy.<ref name=\"Repubblica_25Feb_Europe\">{{cite web|url=https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/25/news/coronavirus_cina_trump-249513033/|title=Coronavirus, dall'Italia si spande in Europa. Conte: \"Inaccettabili limitazioni agli italiani\". Ma molti Paesi prendono misure|date=2020-02-25|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-kuwait-idUSKCN20I2F9|title=Kuwait suspends flights to and from South Korea, Thailand, Italy over coronavirus fears|date=2020-02-24|work=Reuters|access-date=2020-02-25|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.repubblica.it/esteri/2020/02/27/news/coronavirus_stati_restrizioni_viaggio_italia_12_divieti_ingresso-249720846/|title=Coronavirus, ecco gli Stati dove gli italiani non possono viaggiare o hanno restrizioni|date=2020-02-27|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref> [[Bulgaria]] suspended all flights to and from Milan until 27 March. [[Australia]], [[Saudi Arabia]], [[Netherlands]] and the [[United States]] issued a travel advisory for all citizens not to travel to parts of Italy affected by the outbreak.<ref name=\"Repubblica_25Feb_Europe\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.businessinsider.com/cdc-issues-travel-warning-italy-covid-19-concerns-2020-2|title=The US is telling Americans with preexisting conditions to avoid trips to Italy|last=Al-Arshani|first=Sarah|website=Business Insider|access-date=2020-02-26}}</ref>\n\nTwo intercity buses operated by Flixbus, one travelling from Lyon to [[Rijeka]] via [[Turin]], the other travelling from Turin to [[Zagreb]], were stopped at the Croatian border for a few hours as the passengers underwent health checks.<ref name=\"Repubblica_liveupdate\" />\n\n[[Goldman Sachs]], [[Deloitte]], [[Citigroup|Citigroup Inc]], [[Credit Suisse]], [[Lazard Capital Markets|Lazard]], [[Cr\u00e9dit Agricole|Credit Agricole]], [[Nomura Holdings|Nomura]], [[Banque Populaire]] and [[BNP Paribas]] requested that staff who had recently returned from Italy to work from home for at least 14 days and deferred non-essential travel to Italy.<ref name=\"Reuters_banks\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-banks-idUSKCN20I2LW|title=Goldman, Citi among banks curbing Italy trips over coronavirus fears - sources|date=2020-02-25|work=Reuters|access-date=2020-02-25|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofmalta.com/articles/view/deloitte-malta-asks-staff-returning-from-italy-to-work-from-home.773615|title=Coronavirus: Deloitte Malta asks staff returning from Italy to work from home|website=Times of Malta|language=en-gb|access-date=2020-02-25}}</ref>\n\nOn 26 February, the European Parliament postponed internships until 1 October for 35 trainees who declared residence addresses in areas affected by the COVID-19 outbreak, including Lombardy, Piedmont, Emilia-Romagna and Veneto.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://edition.cnn.com/asia/live-news/coronavirus-outbreak-02-26-20-intl-hnk/h_5964fbd1f32ef875b399c3461de9c200|title=European Parliament cancels internships for people from coronavirus affected areas|first1=Jessie |last1=Yeung |first2=Adam |last2=Renton |first3=Meg |last3=Wagne |first4=Mike |last4=Hayes |first5=Rachel|last5=Bowman|date=2020-02-26|website=CNN|language=en|access-date=2020-02-26}}</ref> Six American universities \u2014 [[Elon University]], [[Fairfield University]], [[Florida International University]], [[New York University]], [[Stanford University]] and [[Syracuse University]] \u2014 postponed or cancelled their study-abroad programmes in Italy, mainly in Florence.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.cnn.com/2020/02/26/us/colleges-canceling-study-abroad-coronavirus-trnd/index.html|title=A growing list of US colleges are canceling study abroad programs because of the coronavirus|last=Sutton|first=Francisco Guzman and Joe|website=CNN|access-date=2020-02-26}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lanazione.it/firenze/cronaca/coronavirus-toscana-1.5046897|title=Coronavirus in Toscana: quattro positivi, altri due casi di contagio a Firenze / DIRETTA|last=Nazione|first=La|date=26 February 2020|website=La Nazione|language=it|access-date=26 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n[[Russia]], Spain and [[Turkey]] issued a recommendation for all citizens not to travel to regions of Italy affected by the outbreak.<ref name=\":2\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theolivepress.es/spain-news/2020/02/25/spain-issues-travel-warning-for-italy-over-coronavirus-outbreak-as-it-steps-up-protocols/|title=Spain issues travel warning for Italy over coronavirus outbreak as it steps up protocols|last=Dollimore|first=Laurence|date=2020-02-25|website=Olive Press News Spain|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-02-26}}</ref> [[El Salvador]] barred the entry of travellers arriving from Italy.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-el-salvador-idUSKBN20J2UB|title=El Salvador bars visitors from Italy and South Korea, citing coronavirus|date=2020-02-25|work=Reuters|access-date=2020-02-26|language=en}}</ref>\n\nThe chief executive of the [[Irish Rugby Football Union]], Philip Browne, cancelled [[Six Nations Championship]] rugby matches between Ireland and Italy from 6 to 8 March in [[Dublin]].<ref>{{Cite news|last=Carroll|first=Rory|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2020/feb/26/ireland-v-italy-six-nations-match-postponed-due-to-coronavirus|title=Ireland v Italy in Six Nations postponed and may be cancelled due to coronavirus|date=2020-02-26|work=The Guardian|access-date=2020-02-26|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref>\n\nOn 27 February, [[Israel]] barred entry to foreign nationals travelling from Italy. Officials at [[Ramon Airport]] refused to let 25 foreign nationals arriving on a Ryanair flight from Bergamo to disembark. Israeli passengers were allowed to enter the country and were quarantined at home for 14 days.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.timesofisrael.com/israeli-returning-from-italy-has-coronavirus-visitors-from-there-to-be-barred/|title=Israeli diagnosed with virus after Italy trip; visitors from there to be barred |website=www.timesofisrael.com|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ynetnews.com/article/ryXHlBB4I|title=Dozens of travelers from Italy refused entry to Israel|date=2020-02-27|website=ynetnews|language=en|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.jpost.com/Breaking-News/Israeli-who-came-back-from-Italy-diagnosed-with-coronavirus-619053|title=Coronavirus confirmed in Israeli who returned from Italy|website=The Jerusalem Post {{!}} JPost.com|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref> After being denied permission to dock in [[Ocho Rios]], [[Jamaica]] and [[George Town, Cayman Islands|George Town]], [[Cayman Islands]] on 26 February, the ''[[MSC Meraviglia]]'', operated by [[MSC Cruises]], was finally able to dock in [[Cozumel]], [[Mexico]]. The cruise liner was carrying 4,500 passengers and 1,600 crew members, one of whom was reportedly showing flu-like symptoms.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.foxnews.com/travel/cruise-ship-msc-meraviglia-coronavirus-concerns|title=Cruise ship MSC Meraviglia turned away from two Caribbean ports amid coronavirus concerns|last=Puhak|first=Janine|date=2020-02-26|website=Fox News|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-26}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-mexico-port-idUSKCN20K33F|title=Mexican port denies cruise ship permission to dock over coronavirus fears|date=2020-02-26|work=Reuters|access-date=2020-02-26|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.foxnews.com/travel/coronavirus-concerns-cruise-ship-msc-meraviglia-mexico|title=MSC cruise ship docks in Mexico following coronavirus scare; company says ill crew member diagnosed with flu|last=Puhak|first=Janine|date=2020-02-27|website=Fox News|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://apnews.com/5dd186d96385f7621182cbe5466901a8|title=Cruise ship docks at Mexico's Cozumel amid virus fears|date=2020-02-27|website=AP NEWS|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref> Another Italian cruise liner, the [[Costa Favolosa]], which was denied permission to dock at [[Tortola]], [[British Virgin Islands]] on 26 February, was finally able to berth in [[Sint Maarten]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cruisehive.com/cruise-ship-with-sick-passengers-denied-to-dock-in-the-british-virgin-islands/38014|title=Cruise Ship With Sick Passengers Denied to Dock in the British Virgin Islands|date=2020-02-26|website=Cruise Hive|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.loopcayman.com/content/italian-cruise-ship-blocked-tortola-berths-st-maarten-1|title=Italian cruise ship blocked from Tortola berths in St Maarten|website=www.loopcayman.com|language=en|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref> The final two stages of the [[UAE Tour]] were cancelled after two Italian staff members of one of the teams tested positive for SARS-CoV-2. Following this discovery, the W Abu Dhabi and the Crowne Plaza Abu Dhabi, both on [[Yas Island]], were put on lockdown.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cyclingnews.com/news/final-uae-tour-stages-called-off-over-coronavirus-fears/|title=Final UAE Tour stages called off after two coronavirus cases confirmed|date=February 2020 |website=Cyclingnews.com|language=en|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref>\n\nOn 28 February, Germany enacted new health security measures to include regulations for air and sea travel, requiring passengers from multiple countries, including Italy, to report their health status before entry. Train railway companies must report passengers with symptoms to authorities and the federal police would step up checks within 30 kilometres of the border.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-germany-idUSKCN20M34J|title=Germany enacts new health security measures against coronavirus infections|date=2020-02-28|work=Reuters|access-date=2020-02-29|language=en}}</ref>\n\nOn 29 February, the United States [[Centers for Disease Control and Prevention]] upgraded the status of Italy to Level 3 (guidance to avoid non-essential travel because of widespread community transmission).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://wwwnc.cdc.gov/travel/notices/warning/coronavirus-italy|title=Coronavirus in Italy - Warning - Level 3, Avoid Nonessential Travel - Travel Health Notices {{!}} Travelers' Health {{!}} CDC|website=wwwnc.cdc.gov|access-date=2020-02-29}}</ref> Multiple companies such as [[Amazon (company)|Amazon]], [[Google]], [[Toronto-Dominion Bank|TD Bank Group]], [[Bank of Nova Scotia]], [[London Stock Exchange Group]] and [[Cargill|Cargill, Inc.]] deferred all non-essential travel to countries affected by major virus outbreak, including Italy.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-amazon-com-idUSKCN20M2TZ|title=Amazon defers 'non-essential' moves even in U.S. as corporate travel bans spread|date=2020-02-28|work=Reuters|access-date=2020-02-29|language=en}}</ref> The [[University of Notre Dame]] ended its Rome Global Gateway programme and evacuated 106 students from Rome.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://emergency.nd.edu/|title=Emergency Information |website=University of Notre Dame Emergency Information|language=en|access-date=2020-02-29}}</ref>\n\nOn 3 March, [[India]] suspended all visas to nationals of Italy, as well as visa to foreign nationals who have travelled to Italy on or after 1 February 2020. Passengers arriving directly or indirectly from Italy must undergo medical screening at port of entry.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://boi.gov.in/content/advisory-travel-and-visa-restrictions-related-covid-19|title=Advisory: Travel and Visa restrictions related to COVID-19|date=3 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 4 March, [[Thailand]] declared that people travelling from Italy must be quarantined for 14 days after arriving, with no exceptions.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://mgronline.com/qol/detail/9630000021535|title=\"\u0e2d\u0e19\u0e38\u0e17\u0e34\u0e19\" \u0e40\u0e0b\u0e47\u0e19\u0e1b\u0e23\u0e30\u0e01\u0e32\u0e28 \u0e2a\u0e18.\u0e01\u0e33\u0e2b\u0e19\u0e14 9 \u0e1b\u0e23\u0e30\u0e40\u0e17\u0e28\u0e40\u0e1b\u0e47\u0e19\u0e40\u0e02\u0e15\u0e15\u0e34\u0e14\u0e42\u0e23\u0e04\u0e15\u0e34\u0e14\u0e15\u0e48\u0e2d\u0e2d\u0e31\u0e19\u0e15\u0e23\u0e32\u0e22 \u0e17\u0e38\u0e01\u0e04\u0e19\u0e17\u0e35\u0e48\u0e40\u0e14\u0e34\u0e19\u0e17\u0e32\u0e07\u0e21\u0e32\u0e15\u0e49\u0e2d\u0e07\u0e01\u0e31\u0e01\u0e15\u0e31\u0e27 14 \u0e27\u0e31\u0e19 \u0e2a\u0e01\u0e31\u0e14\u0e42\u0e04\u0e27\u0e34\u0e14-19|date=4 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 8 March, [[Romania]] declared that people travelling from Italy must be quarantined for 14 days after arriving on a connecting flight or by road, with no exceptions, and suspended flights from Italy from 9 to 23 March.<ref>{{cite news |title=Update - Coronavirus: Romania suspends flights, buses and trains to Italy, additional measures in place |url=https://www.romania-insider.com/italy-flights-suspended-march-23-coronavirus |accessdate=10 March 2020 |publisher=Romania-Insider |date=9 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 10 March, [[Slovenia]] barred entry to foreign nationals travelling from Italy.<ref>[https://orf.at/stories/3157329/ ORF.at: Slowenien k\u00fcndigt Schlie\u00dfung der Grenze zu Italien an (German)], March 10, 2020</ref> On same day also Austria barred entry to foreign nationals travelling from Italy with exception for people with medical documents and people who travel only through Austria to Germany without stop in Austria.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.br.de/nachrichten/deutschland-welt/oesterreich-will-einreisen-aus-italien-weitgehend-stoppen,RspR1PZ|title=\u00d6sterreich will Einreisen aus Italien weitgehend stoppen|date=10 March 2020|website=BR24|accessdate=11 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 18 March, [[Nigeria]] placed an indefinite suspension on all flights coming from Italy with immediate effect.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://punchng.com/breaking-fg-places-travel-ban-on-china-italy-us-uk-others|title=UPDATED: FG places travel ban on China, Italy, US, UK, nine others|last=Ogundele|first=Kamarudeen|date=18 March 2020|accessdate=26 March 2020|publisher=[[The Punch|The Punch Newspaper]]}}</ref>\n\n===Export restrictions and aid received===\n[[File:Samaritan's Purse in Verona airport - Scarico materiale.jpg|thumb|left|upright=1.13|[[Samaritan's Purse]] airplane with medical aids at the [[Verona Villafranca Airport]]]]\nThe Italian government asked for medical equipment from the European Union mechanism of civil protection, and on 11 March complained about the slow response of the other European countries.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Daniel Boffey |title=Italy criticises EU for being slow to help over coronavirus epidemic |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/11/italy-criticises-eu-being-slow-help-coronavirus-epidemic |accessdate=14 March 2020 |work=The Guardian |date=11 March 2020 |quote=Italy has already asked to activate the European Union mechanism of civil protection for the supply of medical equipment for individual protection. But unfortunately not a single EU country responded}}</ref> The [[List of Permanent Representatives of Italy to the European Union|Italian Permanent Representative to the European Union]], Maurizio Massari, wrote: \"unfortunately, not a single EU country responded to the Commission\u2019s call.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Italian ambassador to the EU: Italy needs Europe's help |url=https://www.politico.eu/article/coronavirus-italy-needs-europe-help/ |accessdate=14 March 2020 |work=[[Politico]] |date=11 March 2020 |quote=\"unfortunately, not a single EU country responded to the Commission\u2019s call.\"}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Miles Johnson |title=Italy shuts all retailers except food stores and pharmacies |url=https://www.ft.com/content/b25470c0-63e6-11ea-a6cd-df28cc3c6a68 |accessdate=14 March 2020 |work=[[Financial Times]] |date=11 March 2020 |quote=Maurizio Massari, Italian permanent representative to the EU, saying that no EU member had responded to a request for medical equipment. \"Only China responded bilaterally. Certainly, this is not a good sign of European solidarity,\" he wrote}}</ref>  Eventually, Germany, France and Austria donated millions of protective masks to Italy, however aid arrived from non-EU countries like China, Russia and Cuba before it arrived from any other EU country.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Naomi O'Leary |title=Covid-19: Economic downturn worsens old EU splits |url=https://www.irishtimes.com/business/economy/covid-19-economic-downturn-worsens-old-eu-splits-1.4214059 |accessdate=30 March 2020 |work=[[The Irish Times]] |date=27 March 2020 |language=en}}</ref><ref name=\"npr_aid\">{{cite news |last1=Poggioli |first1=Sylvia |title=For Help On Coronavirus, Italy Turns To China, Russia And Cuba |url=https://www.npr.org/sections/coronavirus-live-updates/2020/03/25/821345465/for-help-on-coronavirus-italy-turns-to-china-russia-and-cuba?t=1585572391993 |accessdate=30 March 2020 |work=National Public Radio |date=25 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title='Health Silk Road:' China showers Europe with coronavirus aid as both spar with Trump |url=https://fortune.com/2020/03/19/china-europe-coronavirus-aid-trump/ |accessdate=30 March 2020 |work=Fortune |language=en}}</ref>\n\nThe lack of masks became an issue during the peak of the emergency, partly because of the requisitions of imported goods bought by Italy in transport hubs in other countries such as Poland<ref>{{cite news|url=https://roma.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/03/21/news/coronavirus_lazio_mascherine_dogana_polonia_scontro_diplomatico-251900742/|date=21 March 2020 |title= Coronavirus, le mascherine destinate a Roma e al Lazio bloccate in Polonia|publisher=[[La Repubblica]]|access-date=22 March 2020|language=italian}}</ref> and Turkey.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://roma.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/03/21/news/coronavirus_lazio_mascherine_dogana_polonia_scontro_diplomatico-251900742/|date=19 March 2020 |title= Coronavirus: Cisl, 1 mln mascherine per Trentino bloccate|publisher=[[Agenzia Nazionale Stampa Associata|ANSA]]|access-date=19 March 2020|language=italian}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Gabanelli|first=Milena|url=https://www.corriere.it/dataroom-milena-gabanelli/20_marzo_19/coronavirus-200-mila-mascherine-gli-ospedali-italiani-bloccate-ad-ankara-15-giorni-2b0ea5be-695d-11ea-913c-55c2df06d574_preview.shtml?reason=unauthenticated&cat=1&cid=cYfmThlo&pids=FR&credits=1&origin=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.corriere.it%2Fdataroom-milena-gabanelli%2F20_marzo_19%2Fcoronavirus-200-mila-mascherine-gli-ospedali-italiani-bloccate-ad-ankara-15-giorni-2b0ea5be-695d-11ea-913c-55c2df06d574.shtml|title=Coronarivus, 200 mila mascherine per gli ospedali italiani bloccate ad Ankara da 15 giorni|publisher=[[Corriere della Sera]]|access-date=19 March 2020|language=italian}}</ref> Masks were confiscated by mistake in Czechia. It was happen during a raid against Chinese reseller Zhou Lingjian.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://zpravy.aktualne.cz/domaci/confiscated-face-masks-imported-by-an-influential-representa/r~560650326f6611ea842f0cc47ab5f122/|access-date=26 March 2020|language=english |title= Confiscated face masks imported by an influential Chinese representative in Czechia|first=Luk\u00e1\u0161|last=Val\u00e1\u0161ek}}</ref>\n\nSince early March, the German government restricted the export of products essential to its national health service. Italian distributors were advised they could not be supplied with surgical gowns, protective masks, glasses, particulate respirators, nor visors.<ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus, stop export of masks: Germany \"suffocates\" Italy |url=https://www.liberoquotidiano.it/news/italia/21145392/coronavirus_germania_mascherine_italia.html |accessdate=15 March 2020 |work=[[Libero (newspaper)]] |date=13 March 2020 |language=it |quote=\"which confirms that the company will not be able to meet the demand for new surgical gowns, protective masks, glasses and visors because Germany, with a letter in early March, confirmed the restrictions on the export of essential products for the system national health service\".}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus, Germany asphyxiates Italy on masks? The case of the \"export limits\" |url=https://www.ilmessaggero.it/italia/coronavirus_mascherine_germania_italia_esportazioni_3m_lettera-5108989.html |accessdate=15 March 2020 |work=[[Il Messaggero]] |date=13 March 2020 |language=it |quote=explains to Italian customers that they cannot meet their demand for masks and the like due to export restrictions imposed by the German government. The US multinational received the letter in the first week of March. The restrictions concern: surgical gowns (sterile and non-sterile), particulate respirators (FFP2 / FFP3), surgical masks, protective goggles, visors, protective clothing.}}</ref> France also imposed similar export restrictions and the German health minister [[Jens Spahn]] defended Germany's decision.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Caizzi |first1=Ivo |title=Masks divide the EU as Germany and France block exports |url=https://www.corriere.it/esteri/20_marzo_06/mascherine-dividono-ue-germania-francia-bloccano-l-export-30087c42-5fd6-11ea-96d2-d1c7db9c0ec3.shtml |accessdate=15 March 2020 |work=[[Corriere della Sera]] |date=6 March 2020 |language=it |quote=But the German health minister, Jens Spahn, defended his government's decision to impose \"to ask the authorities for an authorization\" to export masks}}</ref> On 12 March, the German ministry issued a decree suspending the export restriction in particular emergency cases, and promised to send one million protective masks to Italy.<ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus, la Germania invier\u00e0 un milione di mascherine all'Italia |url=https://www.repubblica.it/esteri/2020/03/13/news/coronavirus_la_germania_invia_un_milione_di_mascherine_all_italia-251219227/ |accessdate=15 March 2020 |work=la Repubblica |date=13 March 2020 |language=it}}</ref>\n\nOn 13 March, a team of nine Chinese experts, among whom there was the manager of the 40,000 Chinese doctors who had been sent to Wuhan and a leading cardio-pulmonary reanimation doctor, arrived in Rome to share their expertise. The Chinese Red Cross brought 31 tons of respiratory devices, electrocardiographs, 40 ventilators, tens of thousands of masks, and other medical equipment supplied by the hospital of the School of Medicine of Shanghai Jiaotong University.<ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus, medici cinesi a Roma: anche erbe medicinali fra le 31 tonnellate di materiali |url=https://roma.corriere.it/notizie/cronaca/20_marzo_13/coronavirus-aiuti-cinesi-anche-erbe-medicinali-le-31-tonnellate-materiali-04e4543c-6512-11ea-ac89-181bb7c2e00e.shtml |work=Il Corriere della Sera |date=13 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Pelosi |first1=Gerardo |title=Coronavirus, attese per oggi un milione di mascherine |url=https://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/coronavirus-attese-oggi-milione-mascherine-ADTgUWC?refresh_ce=1 |accessdate=14 March 2020 |work=[[Il Sole 24 Ore]] |date=11 March 2020 |language=it |quote=Only China has responded bilaterally. This is not a good sign of EU solidarity}}</ref><ref name=aljazeera-china-italy>{{cite news |title=China sends essential coronavirus supplies to Italy |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/03/china-sends-essential-coronavirus-supplies-italy-200313195241031.html |accessdate=14 March 2020 |work=[[Al Jazeera]] |date=14 March 2020 }}</ref> While the head of the Italian Red Cross, Francesco Rocca said these medical supplies were donated by the Chinese Red Cross, other sources claimed that these were paid products and services.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Balmer |first1=Crispian |title=China sends medical supplies, experts to help Italy battle coronavirus |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-italy-respirators/china-sends-medical-supplies-experts-to-help-italy-battle-coronavirus-idUSKBN2101IM |accessdate=24 March 2020 |work=[[Reuters]] |publisher=Reuters |date=13 March 2020 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Giulia Pompili |title=But what help from China against the virus, it's all stuff we purchase |url=https://www.ilfoglio.it/cronache/2020/03/12/news/ma-quali-aiuti-della-cina-contro-il-virus-e-tutta-roba-che-compriamo-306324/ |accessdate=16 March 2020 |work=[[Il Foglio]] |date=12 March 2020 |language=it |quote=confermano al Foglio fonti della Farnesina e la Protezione civile, non c\u2019\u00e8 nessuna donazione, niente di gratis}}</ref> Chinese billionaire and [[Alibaba Group|Alibaba]] co-founder [[Jack Ma]] also donated 500,000 masks and other medical supplies, which landed at Liege Airport in Belgium on 13 March and were then sent to Italy.<ref name=aljazeera-china-italy /><ref>{{cite news |last1=Blenkinsop |first1=Philip |title=Jack Ma donates two million masks for coronavirus crisis in Europe |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-jack-ma-idUSKBN2110KA |accessdate=24 March 2020 |work=[[Reuters]] |publisher=Reuters |date=14 March 2020 }}</ref>\n\nOn 17 March, Undersecretary at the [[Ministry of Health (Italy)|Ministry of Health]], [[Sandra Zampa]] announced the purchase of many new [[ventilator]]s as well as the importing of one and a half million masks from [[South Africa]].<ref>{{Citation|title=Sandra Zampa: \"\u00c8 arrivata una partita di un milione e mezzo di mascherine dal Sud Africa\"|url=https://www.la7.it/laria-che-tira/video/sandra-zampa-e-arrivata-una-partita-di-un-milione-e-mezzo-di-mascherine-dal-sud-africa-17-03-2020-313803|language=it|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Agnelli family]] donated \u20ac10 million to the Government's coronavirus funds. The family's companies Fiat and Ferrari also brought 150 ventilators and offered to help make new ventilator units, in addition to providing a fleet of vehicles to be used to distribute food and medical supplies to the elderly.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.family-behind-ferrari-donates-eur10m-and-150-ventilators-to-help-fight.49I36GCiU2RZgz5i1mONJN.html |title=Family behind Ferrari donates \u20ac10m and 150 ventilators to help fight coronavirus in Italy |date=18 March 2020 |work=formula1.com |access-date=20 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Pollina |first=Elvira |url=https://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-health-coronavirus-ventilators-italy/exclusive-ferrari-and-fiat-look-at-helping-italy-make-ventilators-in-coronavirus-crisis-idUKKBN2162YR |title=Exclusive: Ferrari and Fiat look at helping Italy make ventilators in coronavirus crisis |date=19 March 2020 |access-date=20 March 2020 |agency=Reuters |last2=Piovaccari |first2=Giulio}}</ref>\n\nOn 21 March, the [[Cuba]]n government sent 52 medical staff (35 doctors and 17 nurses) specialised in infectious diseases who had dealt with the Ebola outbreak. They arrived in Milan on 22 March and entered service in [[Cremona]] on 24 March.<ref>{{cite news |title=Cuban doctors head to Italy battle coronavirus |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-cuba/cuban-doctors-head-to-italy-battle-coronavirus-idUSKBN219051 |work=Reuters |date=23 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Emergenza Coronavirus, numeri e medici cubani infondono speranz |url=https://www.ilgiorno.it/cremona/cronaca/coronavirus-medici-cubani-1.5078589 |work=Il Giorno Cremona|date=24 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 21 March, US Secretary of State [[Mike Pompeo]] said that the United States Air Force \"sent a C-130 filled with medical supplies to Italy\".<ref name=\"npr_aid\"/> On 30 March, US President [[Donald Trump]] said that the US was to send $100 million worth of medical and hospital supplies to Italy.<ref>{{cite news |title=Trump says US to send medical supplies to Italy, France, Spain |url=https://www.france24.com/en/20200330-trump-says-us-to-send-medical-supplies-to-italy-france-spain |accessdate=31 March 2020 |work=France 24 |date=30 March 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n\nAfter a phone call with Conte, Russian president [[Vladimir Putin]] arranged the Russian army to send medical help to Italy.<ref>{{cite news |title=Russian army to send coronavirus help to Italy after Putin phone call |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-russia-italy/russian-army-to-send-coronavirus-help-to-italy-after-putin-phone-call-idUSKBN219081 |accessdate=22 March 2020 |work=Reuters |date=22 March 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\nOn 22 March 2020, [[Russia]] sent nine [[Military aircraft|military planes]] stocked with medical kits and a team of specialists to Italy. The [[fuselage]] of the plane also carried a message for the nation, which read: \u201cFrom Russia with Love\u201d.<ref>{{cite_web|url=https://www.ft.com/content/b1c5681e-6cf9-11ea-89df-41bea055720b|title=Russia sends Italy coronavirus aid to underline historic ties|accessdate=23 March 2020|website=Financial Times}}</ref>\n\nThe US-based evangelical group [[Samaritan's Purse]] opened a coronavirus field hospital in the parking lot of Cremona hospital.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Sorace |first1=Stephen |title=Samaritan's Purse opens coronavirus field hospital in Italy, receives first patients |url=https://www.foxnews.com/world/italy-evangelical-coronavirus-field-hospital |accessdate=23 March 2020 |work=Fox News |date=22 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 24 March, Germany took in six coronavirus patients from the Bergamo hospital to be treated in Saxony.<ref>{{cite news |title=Germany treats first Italians as coronavirus care crosses borders |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-germany-italy-idUSKBN21B2GL |accessdate=29 March 2020 |work=Reuters |date=24 March 2020 |language=en}}</ref> Later the same week, the German health minister said that Germany would take in a total of at least 47 Italian patients.<ref>{{cite news |title=Germany Takes in 47 Coronavirus Patients From Italy |url=https://www.usnews.com/news/world/articles/2020-03-26/germany-takes-in-47-coronavirus-patients-from-italy |accessdate=29 March 2020 |work=US News |agency=Reuters |date=26 March 2020}}</ref>\nOn 25 March, a C-130 from Ramstein Air Base in Germany delivered humanitarian supplies to Aviano Air Base.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.joint-forces.com/world-news/30519-us-humanitarian-assistance-support-to-italy |title = US Humanitarian Assistance Support to Italy|date = 25 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n[[Somalia]] sent twenty volunteer doctors to Italy to help fight COVID-19.<ref>{{cite news |title=Somalia sending 20 doctors to help Italy fight virus |url=https://www.aa.com.tr/en/africa/somalia-sending-20-doctors-to-help-italy-fight-virus/1782154 |accessdate=27 March 2020 |work=www.aa.com.tr}}</ref> [[Albania]] also sent a group of thirty medical staff members to Lombardy.<ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus, l'Albania invia medici e infermieri: \"Non dimentichiamo l'Italia che ci ha aiutato\" |url=https://www.repubblica.it/esteri/2020/03/29/news/coronavirus_medici_albania_italia-252593099/?ref=RHPPTP-BH-I252538519-C12-P4-S4.4-T1 |accessdate=29 March 2020 |work=la Repubblica |date=28 March 2020 |language=it}}</ref>\n\n==Impact==\n{{Expand section |date=March 2020}}\n\n===Economy===\n{{See also|Financial impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic}}\n[[File:Emergenza coronavirus (49651209716).jpg|thumb|right|upright=1.13|Sets of [[personal protective equipment]] in a Civil Protection hub, ready to be distributed to the regions]]\nThe pandemic provoked large economic damage to the Italian economy. The sectors of tourism, accommodation and food services were among the hardest hit by foreign countries' limitations to travel to Italy, and by the nationwide lockdown imposed by the government on 8 March.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Brunton |first1=John |title='Nothing less than a catastrophe': Venice left high and dry by coronavirus |url=https://www.theguardian.com/travel/2020/mar/17/nothing-less-than-a-catastrophe-venice-left-high-and-dry-by-coronavirus |accessdate=19 March 2020 |work=The Guardian |date=17 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nMultiple factories, like [[Fiat Chrysler Automobiles|Fiat Chrysler]], halted production in some of their plants.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Ghiglione |first1=Davide |last2=Romei |first2=Valentina |last3=Hall |first3=Ben |title=Italy faces mounting economic damage from coronavirus |url=https://www.ft.com/content/d0565f72-5fcf-11ea-b0ab-339c2307bcd4 |accessdate=19 March 2020 |work=Financial Times |date=12 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 12 March, the Italian stock market was among the worst hit during [[2020 stock market crash#Black Thursday (12 March)|Black Thursday]], when the FTSE MIB index lost 17% of its value in one day.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Za |first1=Valentina |last2=Allen |first2=Nathan |title=Italy, Spain curb trading to stem coronavirus market crash |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-europe-stocks-short-selling/italy-spain-curb-trading-to-stem-coronavirus-market-crash-idUSKBN2101LN |accessdate=19 March 2020 |work=Reuters |date=13 March 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n====Conversion of production to medical supplies====\nSome Italian small and medium-sized enterprises partially or totally converted their production to supply personal protective equipment at a local scale. Many of these items could not be approved for hospital use, but they were considered useful to supply demand for the general population.<ref name=DeStefaniLaStampa>{{cite news|url=https://www.lastampa.it/economia/2020/03/18/news/la-grande-corsa-alla-riconversione-chi-creava-vestiti-ora-fa-mascherine-1.38605102|date=18 March 2020 |title= La grande corsa alla riconversione: chi creava vestiti ora fa mascherine|first1=Gabriele|last1=De Stefani|publisher=[[La Stampa]]|access-date=22 March 2020|language=italian}}</ref>\n\nIn Veneto, Grafica Veneta \u2013 the printing company of the ''Harry Potter'' books in Italian \u2013 started to mass-produce protective masks.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.repubblica.it/economia/2020/03/22/news/coronavirus_mascherine-252001308/?ref=RHPPTP-BH-I252011244-C12-P1-S3.4-T1|first=Marco |last=Patucchi|date=22 March 2020|access-date=23 March 2020|title=Coronavirus, lo stampatore di libri che dona mascherine: \"Ho conosciuto la morte, non potevo sottrarmi\"|publisher=[[La Repubblica]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ilfattoquotidiano.it/2020/03/18/coronavirus-grafica-veneta-riconverte-produzione-4-milioni-di-mascherine-al-giorno-gratis-alla-popolazione/5740755/|title=Coronavirus, Grafica Veneta riconverte produzione: 4 milioni di mascherine al giorno \"gratis alla popolazione\"|language=italian|publisher=[[Il Fatto Quotidiano]]|first= Giuseppe |last=Pietrobelli |date=18 March 2020|access-date=22 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ilgazzettino.it/nordest/padova/coronavirus_grafica_veneta_produzione_mascherine-5114284.html|title=Grafica Veneta pronta a produrre \"mascherine\", Zaia: \"Saranno le prime \"made in Veneto\"\"|language=italian|publisher=[[Il Gazzettino]]|date=16 March 2020|access-date=18 March 2020}}</ref> \nIn Piedmont, Ci.Ti.Elle, a company from [[Castiglione Torinese]] specialized in textiles for hotels, put its twelve employers to assemble surgical masks for the regional ''Protezione Civile'', and the hospitals of San Maurizio Canavese, Alessandria and Chivasso, with the support the Filmar company from Caselle for the elastics.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.lastampa.it/torino/2020/03/20/news/coronavirus-l-azienda-si-converte-dai-tessuti-per-gli-hotel-alle-mascherine-distribuite-gratis-1.38617334|date=21 March 2020 |title= Coronavirus, l'azienda si converte: dai tessuti per gli hotel alle mascherine distribuite gratis|first1=Nadia |last1=Bergamini|first2=Andrea |last2=Bucci |publisher=[[La Stampa]]|access-date=22 March 2020|language=italian}}</ref> \nIn Lombardy Cifra, a manufacturer from [[Verano Brianza]] specialized in sportswear, also converted its production line.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://rep.repubblica.it/pwa/generale/2020/03/23/news/dai_body_sportivi_alle_mascherine_la_fabbrica_che_reagisce_all_emergenza-252117447/?ref=RHPPTP-BH-I252124970-C12-P1-S4.4-T1|date=23 March 2020 |title= Dai body sportivi alle mascherine la fabbrica che reagisce all'emergenza|publisher=[[La Repubblica]]|access-date=24 March 2020|language=italian|first=Marco|last=Patucchi}}</ref>\nIn the textile district of the [[province of Prato]], the company Machattie started its production of polypropylene masks in March, and the company Dreoni in [[Vaiano]] switched its production from car upholstery to protective masks with certified standard, with the help of the local population.<ref name=DeStefaniLaStampa/>\n\nCompanies producing alcoholic beverages also underwent reconversion to produce alcohol-based hand sanitizer. In Piedmont this occurred in [[Canelli]] at the [[Ramazzotti (liqueur)|Ramazzotti]] factory (part of the [[Pernod Ricard]] group)<ref>{{cite news|url= https://torino.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/03/28/news/canelli_la_fabbrica_dell_amaro_ramazzotti_si_mette_a_produrre_igienizzanti_per_le_mani-252550031/?ref=RHPPBT-BH-I252189793-C12-P2-S3.4-T1|title= Canelli, la fabbrica dell'amaro Ramazzotti si mette a produrre l'igienizzante per le mani|language=italian|first=Camilla|last=Capulli|access-date=28 March 2020|date=28 March 2020|publisher=[[La Stampa]]}}</ref> and in [[Chieri]] at the Martini plant.<ref>{{cite news|url= https://www.lastampa.it/topnews/edizioni-locali/torino/2020/03/27/news/coronavirus-la-fabbrica-dei-cocktail-ora-fa-i-disinfettanti-1.38644037|title= Coronavirus, la fabbrica dei cocktail ora fa i disinfettanti|language=italian|first1=Gianni |last1=Giacomino |first2=Sarah |last2=Scaparone|access-date=28 March 2020|date=27 March 2020|publisher=[[La Stampa]]}}</ref>\n\nIsinnova, a local engineering startup from Brescia, provided emergency solutions to local hospitals in order to compensate the shortage of spare parts for the machines. Firstly, they produced Venturi valves for respirators using [[3D printer]]s,<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/amyfeldman/2020/03/19/talking-with-the-italian-engineers-who-3d-printed-respirator-parts-for-hospitals-with-coronavirus-patients-for-free/ |language=Italian|work=[[Forbes]]|first=Amy |last=Feldman |date=19 March 2020|access-date=22 March 2020 |title=Meet The Italian Engineers 3D-Printing Respirator Parts For Free To Help Keep Coronavirus Patients Alive}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.giornaledibrescia.it/brescia-e-hinterland/le-valvole-per-la-rianimazione-scarseggiano-si-stampano-in-3d-1.3466921|title=Le valvole per la rianimazione scarseggiano: si stampano in 3D|language=Italian|publisher=[[Giornale di Brescia]]|first= |last=|date=14 March 2020|access-date=22 March 2020}}</ref> and later (in collaboration with [[Decathlon Group]]) they adapted a snorkelling mask into a non-invasive ventilator.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.giornaledibrescia.it/brescia-e-hinterland/easy-covid-19-la-maschera-da-sub-si-trasforma-in-respiratore-1.3468476|title=Easy Covid 19, la maschera da sub si trasforma in respiratore|language=Italian|publisher=[[Giornale di Brescia]]|first= |last=|date=21 March 2020|access-date=22 March 2020}}</ref> Using 3D-printer technology as well, Elmec Informatica also started to produce for the hospital of Busto Arsizio sterilizable protective masks in [[thermoplastic polyurethanes]] that could adapt to [[Continuous positive airway pressure|CPAP]] antiviral filters.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ilgiorno.it/varese/cronaca/coronavirus-mascherine-3d-1.5083431|last=Formenti|first=Rosella|title=  Busto Arsizio, in ospedale mascherine con la stampante 3D|access-date=31 March 2020|date=27 March 2020|publisher=[[Il Giorno (newspaper)|Il Giorno]]}}</ref>\n\n====Cross-talks with the EU====\nOn 25 March, Italy, together with Belgium, France, Greece, Ireland, Luxembourg, Portugal, Slovenia, and Spain, sent a joint letter to the Council of the EU, calling for the issuing of a new common debt instrument, nicknamed in the media as \"[[Eurobond (eurozone)|eurobond]]\" or \"corona bond\", in order to help funding the measures taken against the coronavirus pandemic and the expected economic downturn to follow.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Dombey |first1=Daniel |last2=Chazan |first2=Guy |last3=Brundsen |first3=Jim |title=Nine eurozone countries issue call for \u2018coronabonds\u2019 |url=https://www.ft.com/content/258308f6-6e94-11ea-89df-41bea055720b |accessdate=30 March 2020 |work=Financial Times |date=25 March 2020}}</ref> In subsequent conference calls between the leaders of the EU member states, the proposal saw the opposition of the Netherlands and Germany.<ref>{{cite news |title=Germans and Dutch set to block EU 'corona bonds' at video summit |url=https://www.euractiv.com/section/economy-jobs/news/germans-and-dutch-set-to-block-eu-corona-bonds-at-video-summit/ |accessdate=30 March 2020 |work=www.euractiv.com |date=26 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Hornig |first1=Frank |last2=Mahler |first2=Armin |last3=M\u00fcller |first3=Peter |last4=Rainer |first4=Anton |last5=Reiermann |first5=Christian |title=Calls for Coronabonds Met with Familiar \"Nein\" - DER SPIEGEL - International |url=https://www.spiegel.de/international/europe/calls-for-corona-bonds-met-with-familiar-nein-a-6eb0e5ce-fddd-4909-95bb-ae8421ef3d2e |accessdate=30 March 2020 |work=Der Spiegel |date=27 March 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n===Society===\n[[File:Italian flag coronavirus.jpg|thumb|right|upright=1.13|An [[Italian flag]] with the slogan \"''Andr\u00e0 tutto bene''\" (\"Everything will be all right\")]]\nSubsequent to the imposing of the national lockdown, there were protests in some Italian prisons, with six deaths after clashes in the Sant'Anna penitentiary in Modena.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Gostoli |first1=Ylenia |title=Six inmates die as prison riots over coronavirus rules grip Italy |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/03/inmates-die-prison-riots-coronavirus-rules-italy-200309125813658.html |accessdate=19 March 2020 |work=www.aljazeera.com |date=9 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nWith all of Italy ordered to remain indoors, Italians took to their balconies to sing together, play music, and applaud the country's health care providers.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://time.com/5802700/lockdown-song/|title=People Quarantined in Italy Join Together In Song From Balconies During Coronavirus Lockdown|last1=Locker|first1=Melissa|last2=Hoffman|first2=Ashley|date=15 March 2020|work=Time Magazine|accessdate=21 March 2020}}</ref> Some of the demonstrations were spontaneous, others were organised by social media and radio.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.cnn.com/2020/03/20/europe/italian-radio-national-anthem-intl-scli/index.html|title=Italians sing together as radio stations unite to broadcast the national anthem|last=Spary|first=Sara|date=20 March 2020|work=CNN|accessdate=21 March 2020}}</ref> On 13 March at 6 pm, Italians throughout the country joined to sing the national anthem. At noon on 14 March, they stood on their balconies clapping to salute the nation's health care workers.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/14/world/europe/italians-find-a-moment-of-joy-in-this-moment-of-anxiety.html|title=Italians Find 'a Moment of Joy in This Moment of Anxiety': Under lockdown to prevent the spread of the coronavirus, song breaks out from rooftops, balconies and windows.|last=Horowitz|first=Jason|date=14 March 2020|work=The New York Times|accessdate=21 March 2020}}</ref> A video of opera singer Maurizio Marchini performing the aria \"[[Nessun dorma]]\" from his balcony in Florence went viral.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/news/coronavirus-italy-tenor-nessun-dorma-video-maurizio-marchini-sing-balcony-florence-a9402761.html|title=Coronavirus: Italian tenor stuns quarantined neighbours with 'Nessun Dorma' performance from balcony|last=Stolworthy|first=Jacob|date=14 March 2020|work=The Independent|accessdate=21 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Education===\n{{Main|Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on education}}\nAfter the first outbreak in Lombardy and Veneto, the regional governments of Emilia-Romagna, Friuli Venezia Giulia, Liguria, Lombardy, Piedmont, Trentino, and Veneto closed all schools and universities from 23 February to 1 March.<ref>{{cite news |title=Ufficiale: dopo Lombardia, Veneto, Trentino e Piemonte scuole chiuse anche in tutta l'Emilia-Romagna |url=https://www.open.online/2020/02/23/urgente-sala-scuole-chiuse-a-milano-e-provincia-da-domani/ |accessdate=24 March 2020 |work=Open |date=23 February 2020 |language=it-IT}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus, Nord Italia \"blindato\": scuole chiuse in 7 regioni |url=http://www.today.it/attualita/scuole-chiuse-coronavirus-dove-quando.html |accessdate=24 March 2020 |work=Today |date=23 February 2020 |language=it}}</ref> The suspension was later extended, with the agreement of the national government, up to 8 March in Emilia-Romagna, Lombardy, and Veneto.<ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus, oltre mille contagiati. Scuole chiuse fino all'8 marzo in Veneto, Lombardia, Emilia Romagna |url=https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/29/news/le_scuole_ancora_otto_giorni_di_stop_in_lombardia_emilia_e_veneto-249848004/ |accessdate=24 March 2020 |work=la Repubblica |date=28 February 2020 |language=it}}</ref>\n\nOn 4 March, the government announced the closure of all schools and colleges until 15 March.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.thetelegram.com/news/world/coronavirus-deprives-nearly-300-million-students-of-their-schooling-unesco-419714/|title=Coronavirus deprives nearly 300 million students of their schooling: UNESCO {{!}} The Telegram|last=Inc|first=Reuters|website=thetelegram.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-15}}</ref>\n\nWith the enactment of the lockdown of Lombardy and 14 more northern provinces on 8 March, the re-opening of schools in these areas was delayed to 3 April.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Tondo |first1=Lorenzo |title=Italy set to quarantine whole of Lombardy due to coronavirus |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/07/italy-set-to |accessdate=24 March 2020 |work=the Guardian |date=7 March 2020 |language=en}}</ref> On 9 March, the government extended the lockdown to the national territory, closing all schools and universities until 3 April.<ref>{{cite news |title=Italian premier locks down entire country to stop virus |url=https://apnews.com/3ff579e06d07428f0bc993c0a98c001d |accessdate=24 March 2020 |work=AP NEWS |date=9 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Religion===\n{{Main|Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on religion#Christianity}}\nIn Italy, in-person gatherings for religious worship have been suspended and as a result, many churches broadcast Mass via online live-stream, radio and television.<ref>{{cite web |title=In Italy and beyond, churches grapple with coronavirus |url=https://www.politico.eu/article/coronavirus-church-online-live-stream-congregation/ |publisher=Politico |accessdate=30 March 2020 |language=English |date=17 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nChurch funerals cannot be held given the national lockdown.<ref name=\"Scalzo2020\"/> In some northern cities, authorities have had issues in dealing with the storage of the high number of coffins, and churches have offered to care for them.<ref name=\"Scalzo2020\">{{cite web |last1=Scalzo |first1=Flavio Lo |title=Italy small town priest deals with death on industrial scale |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-italy-coffins/italy-small-town-priest-deals-with-death-on-industrial-scale-idUSKBN21F0M6 |publisher=[[Reuters]] |accessdate=30 March 2020 |language=English |date=29 March 2020}}</ref> In the towns of Seriate and Bergamo, the Italian Army has volunteered to transport some of these coffins from churches and morgues to cemeteries and crematoriums in other provinces.<ref name=\"Scalzo2020\"/><ref>{{cite news |title=Army takes Bergamo coffins away - English |url=https://www.ansa.it/english/news/general_news/2020/03/19/army-takes-bergamo-coffins-away_a6e09e12-ba62-4dc9-834b-c227c6bd1fa3.html |accessdate=30 March 2020 |work=ANSA.it |date=19 March 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n===Politics===\nOn 5 March, the Italian government decided to postpone the [[2020 Italian constitutional referendum|constitutional referendum]] that was due on 29 March. The referendum has been delayed until further notice.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Dallison |first1=Paul |title=Italy postpones referendum due to coronavirus |url=https://www.politico.eu/article/italy-postpones-referendum-due-to-coronavirus/ |accessdate=22 March 2020 |work=Politico |date=5 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Statistics==\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/Italy medical cases}}\n\n{{Graph:Chart\n|type=line\n|linewidth=1\n|showSymbols=1\n|width=750\n|colors=#FF6347,#FFC000,#87CEEB,#000000\n|showValues=\n|xAxisTitle=Date\n|xAxisAngle=-40\n|x=31 Jan, ..., 6 Feb, ...., 21 Feb, 22 Feb, 23 Feb, 24 Feb, 25 Feb, 26 Feb, 27 Feb, 28 Feb, 29 Feb, 1 Mar, 2 Mar, 3 Mar, 4 Mar, 5 Mar, 6 Mar, 7 Mar, 8 Mar, 9 Mar, 