 for work.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.malaysiakini.com/news/512562|title=After week-long lull, Malaysia records three new Covid-19 cases in 24 hours|date=2020-02-28|website=Malaysiakini|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Maldives]]''' \u2013\nThe Maldives' first cases were two staffers at Kuredu Island Resort who caught the disease from an Italian tourist who had returned to Italy and tested positive there.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/international/world-news/maldives-confirms-first-two-coronavirus-cases-two-resort-islands-locked-down/articleshow/74535526.cms|title=Maldives confirms first two coronavirus cases; two resort islands locked down|date=2020-03-08|work=The Economic Times|access-date=2020-03-08}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Oman]]''' \u2013\nA case was recorded of a patient who had travelled to Milan.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofoman.com/article/2857238/Oman/Health/One-new-case-of-coronavirus-reported-in-Oman|title=One new case of coronavirus reported in Oman|date=5 March 2020|website=Times of Oman|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Philippines]]''' \u2013\nCase 441 had travelled to Italy.<ref>{{cite news |title=Baguio City confirms first case of COVID-19 |url=https://cnnphilippines.com/news/2020/3/23/baguio-city-first-covid-19-case.html |accessdate=23 March 2020 |work=CNN Philippines |date=23 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Saudi Arabia]]''' \u2013\nOn 14 March, Saudi Arabia announced 17 new cases, including some citizens who had recently travelled to Italy.<ref>{{cite news |title=Saudi Arabia announces 17 new cases of coronavirus |url=https://www.arabnews.com/node/1641471/saudi-arabia |accessdate=15 March 2020 |work=Arab News |date=14 March 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Singapore]]''' \u2013\nCase 136 had travelled to Italy.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.moh.gov.sg/news-highlights/details/eight-more-cases-discharged-eight-more-cases-of-covid-19-infection-confirmed |title = MOH &#124; News Highlights}}</ref>\n\n'''[