o tested positive in Italy. A man from [[B\u00f6blingen]] who had had contact with the girlfriend of the patient from G\u00f6ppingen also tested positive.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sozialministerium.baden-wuerttemberg.de/de/service/presse/pressemitteilung/pid/vier-weitere-bestaetigte-corona-faelle-in-baden-wuerttemberg/|title=Vier weitere best\u00e4tigte Corona-F\u00e4lle in Baden-W\u00fcrttemberg|website=Baden-W\u00fcrttemberg.de|language=de|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref>\nOn 28 February, a man from [[Breisgau|Freiburg]] who had travelled to [[Bergamo]] tested positive and underwent isolation.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/MSI_BW/status/1233390378147074049/photo/1|title=In Baden-W\u00fcrttemberg gibt es zwei weitere best\u00e4tigte Infektionen mit dem #Coronavirus (#Freiburg und #Karlsruhe). Damit sind es aktuell 12 F\u00e4lle im Land.pic.twitter.com/x71UZZMomN|last=BW|first=Ministerium f\u00fcr Soziales und Integration|date=2020-02-28|website=@MSI_BW|language=de|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref> A man from [[Rhine-Neckar]] was admitted to the [[University Hospital Heidelberg]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/MSI_BW/status/1233333090896039936|title=In Baden-W\u00fcrttemberg gibt es seit dem sp\u00e4ten Donnerstagabend zwei neue best\u00e4tigte Corona-F\u00e4lle. Die Zahl steigt damit auf 10 F\u00e4lle im Land. #COVID2019pic.twitter.com/xBWAGlNOJC|last=BW|first=Ministerium f\u00fcr Soziales und Integration|date=2020-02-28|website=@MSI_BW|language=de|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref> A 32-year-old man in [[Heilbronn]] who was in Milan on 21 February fell ill and was admitted to a hospital.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/MSI_BW/status/1233438797477621763/photo/1|title=In Baden-W\u00fcrttemberg wurde am Freitagnachmittag ein weiterer best\u00e4tigter #COVID2019 -Fall im Landkreis #Heilbronn bekannt. Damit steigt die Zahl in Baden-W\u00fcrttemberg auf 13.pic.twitter.com/SnQ0UqctaX|last=BW|first=Ministerium f\u00fcr Soziales und Integration|date=2020-02-28|website=@MSI_BW|language=de|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Tbilisi TV Tower - March 23, Solidarity to Italy.jpg|thumb|On 23 March [[Tbilisi TV Broadcasting Tower|Tbilisi TV Tower]] was lit into the colours of the Italian flag to show Georgia's solidarity in the fight with the coronavirus.]]\n\n'''[[Georgia (country)|Georgia]]''' \u2013\nOn 28 February 2020, Georgia confirmed that a 31-year-old Georgian woman who had travelled to Italy tested positive and was admitted to Infectious Diseases Hospital in [[Tbilisi]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://agenda.ge/en/news/2020/620|title=Georgia reports second case of coronavirus|website=Agenda.ge|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Greece]]''' \u2013\nOn 26 February 2020, Greece confirmed its first case, a 38-year-old woman from [[Thessaloniki]] who had recently visited Northern Italy and was admitted to [[AHEPA University Hospital]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.naftemporiki.gr/story/1565985/covid-19-to-proto-thetiko-krousma-stin-ellada-38xroni|title=Covid-19: \u03a4\u03bf \u03c0\u03c1\u03ce\u03c4\u03bf \u03b8\u03b5\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03cc \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u0395\u03bb\u03bb\u03ac\u03b4\u03b1- 38\u03c7\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03b7 \u03b1\u03c0\u03cc \u03c4\u03b7 \u0398\u03b5\u03c3\u03c3\u03b1\u03bb\u03bf\u03bd\u03af\u03ba\u03b7 |language=el |trans-title=Covid-19: The first positive case in Greece - 38 years old from Thessaloniki |date=26 February 2020 |access-date=4 March 2020 |publisher=www.naftemporiki.gr }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cnn.gr/news/ellada/story/209034/o-koronaios-eftase-stin-ellada-proto-epivevaiomeno-kroysma-sti-thessaloniki|title=\u039f \u03ba\u03bf\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03b1\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2 \u03ad\u03c6\u03c4\u03b1\u03c3\u03b5 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u0395\u03bb\u03bb\u03ac\u03b4\u03b1: \u03a0\u03c1\u03ce\u03c4\u03bf \u03b5\u03c0\u03b9\u03b2\u03b5\u03b2\u03b1\u03b9\u03c9\u03bc\u03ad\u03bd\u03bf \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\