 is 'worried'|date=2020-02-25|work=The Telegraph|access-date=2020-02-25|last2=Kelly-Linden|first2=Jordan|language=en-GB|issn=0307-1235|last3=Team|first3=Global Health Security}}</ref><ref name=\":4\">{{cite web|url=https://www.index.hr/clanak.aspx?id=2160148|title=U Rijeci potvr\u0111en tre\u0107i slu\u010daj koronavirusa u Hrvatskoj|website=www.index.hr|language=hr|access-date=2020-02-26}}</ref>\nOn 26 February, the man's twin brother tested positive and was admitted to the same hospital. A Croatian man who worked in [[Parma]], Italy also tested positive and was admitted to a hospital in [[Rijeka]].<ref name=\":4\" />\n\n'''[[Cyprus]]''' \u2013\nOne of the country's first two cases had a travel history to Milan.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cyprus-mail.com/2020/03/10/hospital-close-to-shutdown-after-doctor-with-virus-treated-patients-update-5/|title=Hospital close to shutdown after doctor with virus treated patients (Update 5)|first=Peter|last=Michael|date=9 March 2020|accessdate=10 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Czech Republic]]''' \u2013\nOn 1 March, Czech Republic confirmed its first three cases.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mzcr.cz/dokumenty/koronavirus-2019-ncov-aktualni-data_18455_4122_1.html|title=COVID-19: aktu\u00e1ln\u00ed data|website=DR|language=cs|access-date=2020-03-02}}</ref> As of 8 March 24 of 31 confirmed cases in the country have links to Italy, leading the government to institute a mandatory quarantine for all persons with a history of recent travel to Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.idnes.cz/zpravy/domaci/koronavirus-nemocnice-bulovka-pocet-potvrzenych-pripadu.A200308_124539_domaci_remy|title=Koronavirus: 32 p\u0159\u00edpad\u016f, kontroly na hranic\u00edch i omezen\u00ed v domovech senior\u016f|date=8 March 2020|website=iDNES.cz|accessdate=9 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Denmark]]''' \u2013\nOn 27 February, Denmark confirmed its first case, a man who had returned from a ski holiday in [[Valmalenco]], [[Sondrio]] and was tested at [[Zealand University Hospital, Roskilde]] and quarantined at home.<ref name=Braagaard2020>{{cite news | last=Braagaard | first=Natali | date=27 February 2020 | title=Dansker smittet med coronavirus | url=https://nyheder.tv2.dk/samfund/2020-02-27-dansker-smittet-med-coronavirus | publisher=[[TV 2 (Denmark)|TV2 News]] | language=Danish | trans-title=Dane infected with coronavirus | accessdate=27 February 2020 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dr.dk/nyheder/indland/foerste-dansker-smittet-med-coronavirus-vi-er-selvfoelgelig-dybt-rystede|title=F\u00f8rste dansker smittet med coronavirus: 'Vi er selvf\u00f8lgelig dybt rystede'|website=DR|language=da-DK|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref>\nOn 28 February, a man who had returned from a ski holiday in Northern Italy on 15 February tested positive at [[Rigshospitalet]] in Copenhagen and was placed in home quarantine.<ref name=\"sst28February\">{{cite web|url=https://www.sst.dk/da/Nyheder/2020/En-person-der-er-blevet-undersoegt-paa-Rigshospitalet-er-det-andet-bekraeftede-tilfaelde-af-COVID-19|title=En person, der er blevet unders\u00f8gt p\u00e5 Rigshospitalet, er det andet bekr\u00e6ftede tilf\u00e6lde af COVID-19 i Danmark|date=28 February 2020|work=Sundhedsstyrelsen (Danish Health Authority)|language=da|trans-title=A person, that has been tested at Rigshospitalet, is the second confirmed case of COVID-19 in Denmark|url-status=live|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref>\nOn 29 February, an employee at the [[Aarhus University Hospital]] who had been to a conference in Munich, Germany, where he had met an infected person from Italy, tested positive.<ref name=Ingvorsen2020>{{cite news | last=Ingvorsen | first=Emil S\u00f8nderg\u00e5rd | date=29 February 2020 | title=Nyt coronatilf\u00e6lde er en medarbejder p\u00e5 Aarhus Universitetshospital | url=https://www.dr.dk/nyheder/indland/nyt-coronatilfaelde-er-en-medarbejder-paa-aarhus-universitetshospital | publisher=[[DR (broadcaster)|DR]] | language=Danish | trans-title=New corona case is a worker at Aahus university hospital | accessdate=29 February 2020 }}</ref> On 3 March, five people who had returned from Northern Italy tested positive.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Andreasen|first=Kasper B.|url=https://nyheder.tv2.dk/samfund/2020-03-03-femte-og-sjette-dansker-smittet-med-coronavirus|title=Femte og sjette dansker smittet med coronavirus|date=3 March 2020|work=TV 2|access-date=3 March 2020|url-status=live|language=da}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=Hagemann-Nielsen|first=Frederik|url=https://www.dr.dk/nyheder/indland/sundhedsminister-mindst-10-herhjemme-er-nu-smittet-med-corona|title=Sundhedsminister: Mindst 10 herhjemme er nu smittet med corona|date=3 March 2020|work=DR|access-date=3 March 2020|url-status=live|language=da}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Estonia]]''' \u2013\nOn 3 March, Estonia confirmed its second case, a patient who had arrived on 29 February from Bergamo and was travelling through [[Riga Airport]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Second case of coronavirus diagnosed in Estonia |url=https://news.err.ee/1059432/second-case-of-coronavirus-diagnosed-in-estonia |publisher=ERR |accessdate=4 March 2020|date=3 March 2020 }}</ref> Two other Estonian passengers from the same flight and one returnee from Bergamo arriving through Tallinn Airport tested positive on 5 March.<ref>{{cite web |title=Third coronavirus case confirmed in Estonia |url=https://news.err.ee/1059950/third-coronavirus-case-confirmed-in-estonia |publisher=ERR |accessdate=5 March 2020|date=5 March 2020 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Kahel Bergamost naasnud tallinlasel tuvastati koroonaviirus |url=https://www.err.ee/1060498/kahel-bergamost-naasnud-tallinlasel-tuvastati-koroonaviirus |publisher=ERR |accessdate=5 March 2020 |language=Estonian| trans-title=Two Tallinners returning from Bergamo infected with coronavirus|date=5 March 2020 }}</ref> Two cases in [[Saaremaa]] were confirmed on 10 March: the patients had been in contact with the [[Power Volley Milano]] team members during the [[2019\u201320 CEV Challenge Cup]] matches held in Saaremaa on 4 and 5 March.<ref>{{cite news |title=Lisandus veel kolm koroonasse nakatunut |language=Estonian |trans-title=Three new corona cases |url= https://www.err.ee/1062388/lisandus-veel-kolm-koroonasse-nakatunut |publisher=ERR |accessdate=11 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=17th person diagnosed with coronavirus in Estonia |url=https://news.err.ee/1062618/17th-person-diagnosed-with-coronavirus-in-estonia |publisher=ERR |accessdate=12 March 2020}}</ref> On 9 March 5 Milan players had been diagnosed with fever before a league match.<ref>{{cite news |title=Volley, febbre al termoscanner: Milano-Padova non si gioca |language=Italian |trans-title=Volleyball, thermoscanner fever: Milan-Padua is not played |url=https://sport.sky.it/volley/2020/03/08/coronavirus-volley-partita-sospesa-milano-padova |publisher=Sky Sport |accessdate=11 March 2020}}</ref> The infected in Saaremaa included the CEO of the [[Saaremaa VK]] volleyball club.<ref>{{cite news |title=Koroonaviiruse saanud Saaremaa v\u00f5rkpallimeeskonna juht: loodan, et see olukord laheneb v\u00f5imalikult kiiresti |language=Estonian |trans-title=Infected head of Saaremaa volleyball team: I hope this situation gets resolved as soon as possible |url= https://sport.delfi.ee/news/vorkpall/eesti/koroonaviiruse-saanud-saaremaa-vorkpallimeeskonna-juht-loodan-et-see-olukord-laheneb-voimalikult-kiiresti?id=89199023 |publisher=Delfi |accessdate=11 March 2020}}</ref> [[Saare County]] quickly became the worst hit part of the country.<ref>{{cite web |title=Number of coronavirus cases in Estonia rises to 692 |url=https://news.err.ee/1070484/number-of-coronavirus-cases-in-estonia-rises-to-692 |publisher=ERR |accessdate=30 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Finland]]''' \u2013\nOn 26 February, Finland confirmed that a Finnish woman who had visited Milan and was back in Finland on 22 February tested positive at the [[Helsinki University Central Hospital]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://yle.fi/uutiset/osasto/news/woman_in_helsinki_tests_positive_for_novel_coronavirus/11229433|title=Woman in Helsinki tests positive for novel coronavirus|website=Yle Uutiset|language=en|access-date=2020-02-26}}</ref>\nOn 28 February, a Finnish woman who had travelled to Northern Italy tested positive at the Helsinki and Uusimaa Hospital District and was placed in home isolation.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://yle.fi/uutiset/osasto/news/new_coronavirus_infection_confirmed_in_helsinki/11234516|title=New coronavirus infection confirmed in Helsinki|website=Yle Uutiset|language=en|access-date=2020-03-01}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://yle.fi/uutiset/osasto/news/new_coronavirus_infection_confirmed_in_helsinki/11234516|title=New coronavirus infection confirmed in Helsinki|website=Yle Uutiset|language=en|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref>\n\n'''[[France]]''' \u2013\nOn 25 February, France confirmed that a 64-year-old man from [[La Balme-de-Sillingy]] who had returned from a trip to Lombardy on 15 February tested positive and was treated at Centre Hospitalier Annecy-Genevois, [[\u00c9pagny-Metz-Tessy]].<ref name=\"Repubblica_25Feb_Europe\"/><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-france-idUSKBN20J2CG|title=France reports two new coronavirus infections, one returning from Italy|date=2020-02-25|work=Reuters|access-date=2020-02-26|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ladepeche.fr/2020/02/25/direct-coronavirus-loms-evoque-un-risque-de-pandemie-pour-la-premiere-fois,8754380.php|title=DIRECT. Coronavirus : deux nouveaux cas identifi\u00e9s en France|website=ladepeche.fr|language=fr|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref> His wife also tested positive and was admitted to the same hospital.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ledauphine.com/faits-divers-justice/2020/02/26/haute-savoie-le-cas-de-coronavirus-avere-dans-la-region-est-hospitalise-a-annecy|title=Haute-Savoie. Coronavirus : l'\u00e9pouse du patient hospitalis\u00e9 \u00e0 Annecy \u00e9galement infect\u00e9e|website=www.ledauphine.com|language=FR-fr|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.francetvinfo.fr/sante/maladie/coronavirus/direct-covid-19-le-virus-touche-de-plus-en-plus-de-pays-le-monde-n-est-pas-pret-a-y-faire-face-selon-l-oms_3841703.html|title=DIRECT. Covid-19 : le service de r\u00e9animation de l'h\u00f4pital de Creil, o\u00f9 a \u00e9t\u00e9 hospitalis\u00e9 le patient d\u00e9c\u00e9d\u00e9, ferme pendant 14 jours|date=2020-02-26|website=Franceinfo|language=fr|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref>\nOn 26 February 2020, a 36-year-old man who had made multiple trips to Lombardy tested positive and was treated at Nouvel H\u00f4pital Civil, [[Strasbourg]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-france-toll-idUSKCN20K187|title=France reports second coronavirus death, Italian link in another case|date=2020-02-26|work=Reuters|access-date=2020-02-26|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.france24.com/en/20200226-france-reports-first-citizen-to-die-from-coronavirus-as-three-new-cases-confirmed|title=France reports first citizen to die from coronavirus as three new cases confirmed|date=2020-02-26|website=France 24|language=en|access-date=2020-02-26}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dna.fr/techniques/2020/02/26/kehl-un-bus-en-provenance-de-strasbourg-stoppe-a-la-frontiere|title=Sant\u00e9. Un premier cas de coronavirus confirm\u00e9 en Alsace|website=www.dna.fr|language=FR-fr|access-date=2020-02-26}}</ref>\nOn 27 February 2020, a daughter and a friend of the infected couple from La Balme-de-Sillingy were confirmed positive.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ledauphine.com/sante/2020/02/27/haute-savoie-d-autres-cas-de-coronavirus-a-la-balme-de-sillingy-la-reunion-publique-annulee|title=Sant\u00e9. Haute-Savoie : le directeur g\u00e9n\u00e9ral de la sant\u00e9 confirme 4 cas de coronavirus \u00e0 la Balme de Sillingy|website=www.ledauphine.com|language=FR-fr|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref> A Italian man living in [[Montpellier]] w