=el |trans-title=Coronavirus: Fourth Case - 36-year-old Professor in Athens }}</ref>\n\n'''[[Hungary]]''' \u2013\nThree of the seven cases in Hungary reported to date are linked to Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://koronavirus.gov.hu/cikkek/hetre-nott-koronavirus-fertozottek-szama-tegnap-esti-eredmenyek-szerint|title=H\u00e9tre n\u0151tt a koronav\u00edrus-fert\u0151z\u00f6ttek sz\u00e1ma a tegnap esti eredm\u00e9nyek szerint|language=hu|date=7 March 2020|accessdate=8 March 2020|via=koronavirus.gov.hu}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://koronavirus.gov.hu/cikkek/diagnosztizaltak-az-otodik-koronavirus-fertozottet-idos-magyar-beteg-ferfi|title=Diagnosztiz\u00e1lt\u00e1k az \u00f6t\u00f6dik koronav\u00edrus-fert\u0151z\u00f6ttet \u2013 id\u0151s, magyar, beteg f\u00e9rfi|date=7 March 2020|language=hu|accessdate=8 March 2020|via=koronavirus.gov.hu}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Iceland]]''' \u2013\nOn 28 February 2020, Iceland confirmed its first case, an Icelandic male in his 50s who had previously been to Northern Italy and was placed in solitary confinement in [[Landsp\u00edtali]] in [[Reykjav\u00edk]].<ref name=\"ruv.is\">{{cite web|url=https://www.ruv.is/frett/fyrsta-tilfelli-covid-19-greint-a-islandi|title=Fyrsta tilfelli COVID-19 greint \u00e1 \u00cdslandi|date=28 February 2020|website=R\u00daV}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://bnonews.com/index.php/2020/02/the-latest-coronavirus-cases/|title=Tracking coronavirus: Map, data and timeline|first=B. N. O.|last=News|date=18 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mbl.is/frettir/innlent/2020/02/28/fyrsta_tilfelli_koronuveiru_greinist_a_islandi/|title=Fyrsta tilfelli k\u00f3r\u00f3nuveiru greinist \u00e1 \u00cdslandi|website=www.mbl.is|language=is|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref>\nOn 5 March, a total of 34 cases had been confirmed in Iceland, most of which are imported cases from Italy.\n\n'''[[Ireland]]''' \u2013\nOn 27 February 2020, Ireland's first case was confirmed by the [[Health Protection Surveillance Centre]]. The male patient had travelled to an affected region in Northern Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rte.ie/news/coronavirus/2020/0229/1119357-coronavirus-ireland/ |title=First case of Covid-19 diagnosed in east of Ireland |date=1 March 2020 |access-date=4 March 2020 |publisher=www.rte.ie }}</ref> A second, unrelated case was confirmed on 3 March, a female in the eastern portion of Ireland who had travelled to Italy.<ref>{{cite web|first1=Paul|last1=Cullen|accessdate=2020-03-03|title=Second case of coronavirus is confirmed in east of Ireland|url=https://www.irishtimes.com/news/health/second-case-of-coronavirus-is-confirmed-in-east-of-ireland-1.4191961|website=The Irish Times}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Latvia]]''' \u2013\nOn 2 March, Latvia confirmed its first case, a person who had travelled from Milan to Munich and then to [[Riga]] on 29 February.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://eng.lsm.lv/article/society/health/first-case-of-covid-19-coronavirus-confirmed-in-latvia.a350338/|title=First case of COVID-19 coronavirus confirmed in Latvia|website=lsm.lv|language=en|access-date=2020-03-03}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Lithuania]]''' \u2013\nOn 28 February, Lithuania confirmed its first case, a 39-year-old woman who arrived in [[Kaunas]] from [[Verona]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.15min.lt/naujiena/aktualu/lietuva/koronavirusas-pasieke-lietuva-uzfiksuotas-pirmasis-atvejis-56-1282110|title=Lietuvoje patvirtintas pirmasis koronaviruso atvejis \u2013 susirgo 39 met\u0173 moteris, atskridusi \u012f Kaun\u0105|website=15min.lt|language=lt|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Luxembourg]]''' \u2013\nThe nation's second and fourth cases were persons who had travelled to Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://5minutes.rtl.lu/actu/luxembourg/a/1479054.html|title=RTL 5minutes - Il revenait d'Italie: Un deuxi\u00e8me cas de coronavirus confirm\u00e9 au Luxembourg|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://5minutes.rtl.lu/actu/luxembourg/a/1479918.html|title=Sant\u00e9: Un 4e cas de coronavirus valid\u00e9 au Luxembourg|website=5minutes.rtl.lu|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Malta]]''' \u2013\nA 12-year-old Italian brought the infection to Malta.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/world/covid19-malta-first-coronavirus-case-italian-girl-12512852|title=Italian girl becomes Malta's first coronavirus case|website=CNA|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Moldova]]''' \u2013\nOn 7 March, Moldova confirmed its first case, a 48-year-old woman who had returned from [[Italy]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deschide.md/ro/stiri/social/62248/BREAKING-NEWS-Primul-caz-de-coronavirus-depistat-%C3%AEn-Republica-Moldova-O-femeie-de-48-de-ani-infectat%C4%83.htm|title=BREAKING NEWS// Primul caz de coronavirus depistat \u00een Republica Moldova. O femeie de 48 de ani, infectat\u0103|trans-title=BREAKING NEWS// First coronavirus case detected in Republic of Moldova. A 48-year-old woman, infected|language=ro|website=Deschide.md|date=2020-03-07|access-date=2020-03-07}}</ref> Moldova confirmed the existence of imported case from diseased Italy on 11 March.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://stiri.md/article/incidente/al-patrulea-caz-de-coronavirus-confirmat-in-r-moldova|title=Al patrulea caz de coronavirus, confirmat \u00een R. Moldova|website=stiri.md|accessdate=13 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Netherlands]]''' \u2013\nOn 27 February, the Netherlands confirmed its first case, a man who had been in Lombardy and was admitted to Elisabeth-TweeSteden Hospital in [[Tilburg]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rivm.nl/nieuws/patient-met-nieuw-coronavirus-in-nederland|title=Pati\u00ebnt met nieuw coronavirus in Nederland {{!}} RIVM|website=www.rivm.nl|access-date=2020-03-01}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraaf.nl/nieuws/214089776/rivm-eerste-coronageval-in-nederland|title=RIVM: eerste coronageval in Nederland|date=2020-02-27|website=Telegraaf|language=nl|access-date=2020-03-01}}</ref>\nOn 28 February, a woman from [[Amsterdam]] who had visited Lombardy was in home isolation in [[Diemen]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rivm.nl/nieuws/tweede-patient-in-nederland-met-covid-19|title=Tweede pati\u00ebnt in Nederland met COVID-19 {{!}} RIVM|website=www.rivm.nl|access-date=2020-03-01}}</ref>\n\n'''[[North Macedonia]]''' \u2013\nOn 26 February, North Macedonia confirmed its first case, a woman who tested positive at the Clinic for Infectious Diseases, [[Skopje]]. She had stayed in Italy for a month and had been sick for two weeks. Upon returning to North Macedonia, she immediately reported to the clinic.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://vesti.mk/read/article/https%3A%2F%2Freporter.mk%2Fgjuture%2Fpotvrden-prv-sluchaj-od-koronavirus-vo-makedonija%2F|title=\u041f\u043e\u0442\u0432\u0440\u0434\u0435\u043d \u043f\u0440\u0432 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0458 \u043e\u0434 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u0432\u043e \u041c\u0430\u043a\u0435\u0434\u043e\u043d\u0438\u0458\u0430 |trans-title=First confirmed case of coronavirus in Macedonia |last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=|language=Macedonian}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://a1on.mk/macedonia/prv-sluchaj-na-zabolen-od-koronavirus-vo-makedonija/|title=\u041f\u0440\u0432 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0458 \u043d\u0430 \u0437\u0430\u0431\u043e\u043b\u0435\u043d \u043e\u0434 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u0432\u043e \u041c\u0430\u043a\u0435\u0434\u043e\u043d\u0438\u0458\u0430|date=2020-02-26|website=\u04101\u043e\u043d|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-26}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Norway]]''' \u2013\nOn 27 February, Norway confirmed that two people who tested positive were linked to the outbreak in Italy. They were quarantined at home in [[Oslo]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fhi.no/nyheter/2020/tre-nye-personer-har-testet-positivt-pa-koronavirus/|title=Tre nye personer har testet positivt p\u00e5 koronavirus|website=Folkehelseinstituttet|language=no|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref>\nOn 28 February, an individual from Bergen and an employee of [[Oslo University Hospital, Ullev\u00e5l]] tested positive and were placed in home isolation. Both had visited Northern Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nrk.no/vestland/over-hundre-kan-ha-hatt-kontakt-med-koronasmittet-ulleval-ansatt-1.14922358|title=Over hundre kan ha hatt kontakt med koronasmittet Ullev\u00e5l-ansatt|last=Olsson|first=Svein Vestrum|date=2020-02-28|website=NRK|language=nb-NO|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fhi.no/nyheter/2020/ytterligere-to-personer-har-testet-positivt-pa-koronavirus/|title=Ytterligere to personer har testet positivt p\u00e5 koronavirus|website=Folkehelseinstituttet|language=no|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref>\nOn 6 March, the Norwegian Institute of Public Health reported that 79 of the 113 confirmed cases in Norway were linked to the outbreak in northern Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fhi.no/en/news/2020/status-coronavirus-friday-6.-mars-2020/|title=Status coronavirus Friday 6. mars 2020|website=Folkehelseinstituttet|date=2020-03-06|language=en|access-date=2020-03-07}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Poland]]''' \u2013\nOf the country's first five cases, two were from Italy, two were from Germany and one was from the UK.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://polandin.com/47007012/four-new-coronavirus-cases-confirmed-in-poland|title=Four new coronavirus cases confirmed in Poland|first=Telewizja Polska|last=S.A|website=polandin.com|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''[[Portugal]]''' \u2013\nOn 2 March, a doctor who had travelled to Northern Italy and became ill on 29 February was confirmed positive at Hospital de S\u00e3o Jo\u00e3o in [[Porto]]. On 4 March, a 44-year-old man who had travelled to Italy was confirmed positive at the same hospital.\n\n'''[[Romania]]''' \u2013\nOn 26 February, Romania confirmed its first case, a man from [[Gorj County|Gorj]] who tested positive after having come in contact with an 71-year-old man from [[Cattolica]], Italy. The Italian man visited his wife's family and had several business meetings in Romania from 18 to 22 February. The Romanian man was admitted to National Institute of Infectious Diseases Prof. Dr. Matei Bal\u0219 in [[Bucharest]].<ref name=\":5\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hotnews.ro/stiri-sanatate-23687251-primul-caz-infectie-coronavirus-confirmat-oficial-romania.htm|title=ULTIMA OR\u0102 LIVEVIDEOTEXT Primul caz de infec\u021bie cu coronavirus, confirmat oficial \u00een Rom\u00e2nia: Un b\u0103rbat din Gorj care a intrat \u00een contact cu italianul care a vizitat recent \u021bara noastr\u0103 - Sanatate - HotNews.ro|date=2020-02-26|website=www.hotnews.ro|language=ro|access-date=2020-02-26}}</ref>\nOn 28 February, a 45-year-old man from [[Maramure\u0219]] who had returned from Italy on 25 February was admitted to the Clinic of Infectious Diseases and then transferred to [[Cluj County|Cluj]].<ref name=\":9\">{{cite web|url=https://www.digi24.ro/stiri/actualitate/doua-noi-posibile-cazuri-de-coronavirus-in-romania-1267704|title=Dou\u0103 noi cazuri de coronavirus confirmate \u00een Rom\u00e2nia|website=www.digi24.ro|language=ro|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref> A 38-year-old woman who had returned from Bergamo tested positive was admitted to a hospital in [[Timi\u0219oara]].<ref name=\":9\" />\nOn 3 March, a 47-year-old man who had travelled in the same plane with the 38-year-old woman was confirmed positive and admitted to the same hospital.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.digi24.ro/stiri/actualitate/al-patrulea-caz-de-coronavirus-confirmat-in-romania-1269577|title=Al patrulea caz de coronavirus a fost confirmat \u00een Rom\u00e2nia|trans-title=Fourth coronavirus case was confirmed in Romania|language=ro|website=Digi24|date=2020-03-03|access-date=2020-03-03}}</ref>\nThe majority of confirmed cases in Romania are related to Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.digi24.ro/stiri/actualitate/informatii-oficiale-despre-coronavirus-ministerul-de-interne-26-de-persoane-s