0605/https://www.polygon.com/2019/12/18/21026895/mandalorian-episode-7-recap-timeline-return-of-jedi-force-awakens |archive-date=December 19, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\"Young1218\">{{cite news |last=Young |first=Bryan |title='The Mandalorian' Moves the Pieces Into Place for a Killer Climax With \"The Reckoning\" |work=[[/Film]] |date=December 18, 2019 |url=https://www.slashfilm.com/the-mandalorian-the-reckoning-review/ |accessdate=January 20, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191219132331/https://www.slashfilm.com/the-mandalorian-the-reckoning-review/ |archive-date=December 19, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nThe proposal is a trap, and Greef plans to ambush and kill the Mandalorian and return the Child to the Client.<ref name=\"Raymond0107\" /><ref name=\"Young1218\" /><ref name=\"Snowden1218\">{{cite news |last=Snowden |first=Scott |title='The Mandalorian' Episode 7 Is an Action-Packed First Half of a 2-Part Finale |work=[[Space.com]] |date=December 18, 2019 |url=https://www.space.com/star-wars-mandalorian-episode-7-review.html |accessdate=January 19, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200110212139/https://www.space.com/star-wars-mandalorian-episode-7-review.html |archive-date=January 10, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Nevertheless, the Mandalorian accepts the offer and returns to the planet along with the Child and his allies [[Cara Dune]] ([[Gina Carano]]), [[Kuiil]] ([[Nick Nolte]]), and the recently-rebuilt IG-11, whom Kuiil has reprogrammed to be a nurse droid and protector for the Child.<ref name=\"Scribner1218\" /><ref name=\"Hall1218\" /><ref name=\"Snowden1218\" /> During their voyage, the party is attacked by [[Pterodactylus|pterodactyl]]-like creatures and Greef receives what would have been a fatal injury, but the Child uses the Force to heal him.<ref name=\"Hall1218\" /><ref name=\"Keane1219\">{{cite news |last=Keane |first=Sean |title=Baby Yoda offers a cool link between The Rise of Skywalker and The Mandalorian |work=[[CNET]] |date=December 19, 2019 |url=https://www.cnet.com/news/baby-yoda-offers-a-cool-link-between-the-rise-of-skywalker-the-mandalorian-star-wars/ |accessdate=January 19, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191220214410/https://www.cnet.com/news/baby-yoda-offers-a-cool-link-between-the-rise-of-skywalker-the-mandalorian-star-wars/ |archive-date=December 20, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Britt |first=Ryan |title=Baby Yoda Totally Sets Up 'The Rise of Skywalker' |work=[[Fatherly]] |date=December 18, 2019 |url=https://www.fatherly.com/play/baby-yoda-force-healing-mandalorian-7-rise-of-skywalker-spoilers/ |accessdate=January 19, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191218213017/https://www.fatherly.com/play/baby-yoda-force-healing-mandalorian-7-rise-of-skywalker-spoilers/ |archive-date=December 18, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Greef is so moved that he has a change of heart and informs the others about the trap.<ref name=\"Raymond0107\" /><ref name=\"Keane1219\" /><ref name=\"Pham1231\" /> They devise a new plan in which Kuiil will bring the Child back to the Mandalorian's ship, while the others will kill the Client and his troops.<ref name=\"Hall1218\" /><ref name=\"Young1218\" /><ref name=\"Snowden1218\" /> The plan goes wrong and Kuiil is killed by [[Stormtrooper (Star Wars)|Imperial Scout Troopers]],<ref>{{cite news |last=Holman |first=Leo |title=The Mandalorian: Kuiil Was the Series' Best Character \u2013 Here's Why |work=[[Comic Book Resources]] |date=January 2, 2020 |url=https://www.cbr.com/the-mandalorian-kuiil-series-best-character/ |accessdate=January 21, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200103140349/https://www.cbr.com/the-mandalorian-kuiil-series-best-character/ |archive-date=January 3, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Kain |first=Erik |title=Star Wars 'The Mandalorian' Episode 7 Recap And Review: 'The Reckoning' Is The Best Episode Yet |work=[[Forbes (magazine)|